TotalSensibleLoadHistory.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
TotalSensibleLoadHistory.name: Total Sensible Load History
TotalSensibleLoadHistory.Definition: Total energy added or removed from air that affects its temperature. If a value is less than zero (negative), then the thermal load is lost from the space. If a value is greater than zero (positive), then the thermal load is a gain to the space.

VentilationIndoorAirHistory.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
VentilationIndoorAirHistory.name: Ventilation Indoor Air History

VentilationOutdoorAirHistory.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
VentilationOutdoorAirHistory.name: Ventilation Outdoor Air History

AppliancePercentLoadToRadiant.name: Appliance Percent Load to Radiant
AppliancePercentLoadToRadiant.Definition: Percent of sensible load to radiant heat.

LightingLoadIntensity.name: Lighting Load Intensity
LightingLoadIntensity.Definition: Average lighting load intensity in the space per unit area (Power MeasureIfc Area Measure).

LightingPercentLoadToReturnAir.name: Lighting Percent Load to Return Air
LightingPercentLoadToReturnAir.Definition: Percent of lighting load to the return air plenum.

OccupancyDiversity.name: Occupancy Diversity
OccupancyDiversity.Definition: Diversity factor that may be applied to the number of people in the space.

OutsideAirPerPerson.name: Outside Air Per Person
OutsideAirPerPerson.Definition: Design quantity of outside air to be provided per person in the space.

ReceptacleLoadIntensity.name: Receptacle Load Intensity
ReceptacleLoadIntensity.Definition: Average power use intensity of appliances and other non-HVAC equipment in the space per unit area.(Power MeasureIfc Area Measure).

TotalCoolingLoad.name: Total Cooling Load
TotalCoolingLoad.Definition: The peak total cooling load for the building, zone or space.

TotalHeatingLoad.name: Total Heating Load
TotalHeatingLoad.Definition: The peak total heating load for the building, zone or space.

LongName.name: Long Name
LongName.Definition: Long name for a spatial structure element, used for informal purposes. It should be used, if available, in conjunction with the inherited Name attribute.

ElementType.name: Element Type
ElementType.Definition: The type denotes a particular type that indicates the object further. The use has to be established at the level of instantiable subtypes. In particular it holds the user defined type, if the enumeration of the attribute Predefined Type is set to USERDEFINED.

IfcSpatialElementType.Definition: Ifc Spatial Element Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a spatial structure element and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a spatial element specification (the specific element information, that is common to all occurrences of that element type).
IfcSpatialElementType.Name: Spatial Element Type

IfcSpatialStructureElement.Definition: A spatial structure element is the generalization of all spatial elements that might be used to define a spatial structure. The spatial structure can be used to provide a spatial organization of a project.A spatial project structure might define as many levels of decomposition as necessary for the project. Elements within the spatial project structure aresite as Ifc Site
IfcSpatialStructureElement.Name: Spatial Structure Element

AgreementDate.name: Agreement Date
AgreementDate.Definition: The date on which the version of the agreement became applicable.

AgreementType.name: Agreement Type
AgreementType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of property agreement from which the type required may be set.

AgreementVersion.name: Agreement Version
AgreementVersion.Definition: The version number of the agreement that is identified.

CommencementDate.name: Commencement Date
CommencementDate.Definition: Date on which the agreement commences.

ConditionCommencement.name: Condition Commencement
ConditionCommencement.Definition: Condition of property provided on commencement of the agreement e.g. cold shell, warm lit shell, broom clean, turn-key.

ConditionTermination.name: Condition Termination
ConditionTermination.Definition: Condition of property required on termination of the agreement e.g. cold shell, warm lit shell, broom clean, turn-key.

Options.name: Options
Options.Definition: A statement of the options available in the agreement.

PropertyName.name: Property Name
PropertyName.Definition: Addressing details of the property as stated within the agreement.

Restrictions.name: Restrictions
Restrictions.Definition: Restrictions that may be placed by a competent authority.

TerminationDate.name: Termination Date
TerminationDate.Definition: Date on which the agreement terminates.

TrackingIdentifier.name: Tracking Identifier
TrackingIdentifier.Definition: The identifier assigned to the agreement for the purposes of tracking.

CompositionType.Definition: Denotes, whether the predefined spatial structure element represents itself, or an aggregate (complex) or a part (part). The interpretation is given separately for each subtype of spatial structure element. If no Composition Type is asserted, the default value ELEMENT applies.IFC4 CHANGE Attribute made optional.

IfcSpatialStructureElementType.Definition: The element type (Ifc Spatial Structure Element Type) defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a spatial structure element and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define an element specification (i.e. the specific element information, that is common to all occurrences of that element type).
IfcSpatialStructureElementType.Name: Spatial Structure Element Type

IfcSpatialZone.Definition: A spatial zone is a non-hierarchical and potentially overlapping decomposition of the project under some functional consideration. A spatial zone might be used to represent a thermal zone, a construction zone, a lighting zone, a usable area zone. A spatial zone might have its independent placement and shape representation.The Ifc Spatial Zone inherits and declares these attributes that shall have the following meaningName A number or designator provided by the user or system for the spatial element
IfcSpatialZone.Name: Spatial Zone

AirPressurization.name: Air Pressurization
AirPressurization.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have pressurized air (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

FireExit.name: Fire Exit
FireExit.Definition: Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

FireRiskFactor.name: Fire Risk Factor
FireRiskFactor.Definition: Fire Risk factor assigned to the space according to local building regulations. It defines the fire risk of the space at several levels of fire hazard.

FlammableStorage.name: Flammable Storage
FlammableStorage.Definition: Indication whether the space is intended to serve as a storage of flammable material (which is regarded as such by the presiding building code. (TRUE) indicates yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

SprinklerProtection.name: Sprinkler Protection
SprinklerProtection.Definition: Indication whether this object is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

SprinklerProtectionAutomatic.name: Sprinkler Protection Automatic
SprinklerProtectionAutomatic.Definition: Indication whether this object has an automatic sprinkler protection (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirConditioning.name: Air Conditioning
AirConditioning.Definition: Indication whether this space requires air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirConditioningCentral.name: Air Conditioning Central
AirConditioningCentral.Definition: Indication whether the space requires a central air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirHandlingName.name: Air Handling Name
AirHandlingName.Definition: The name of the air side system.Ifc Rel Services Buildings should be used to reference the correct Air Handling System (Ifc System)

DiscontinuedHeating.name: Discontinued Heating
DiscontinuedHeating.Definition: Indication whether discontinued heating is requireddesirable from userdesigner view point. (TRUE) if yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

HumidityMax.name: Humidity Max
HumidityMax.Definition: Maximal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

HumidityMin.name: Humidity Min
HumidityMin.Definition: Minimal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

HumiditySetPoint.name: Humidity Set Point
HumiditySetPoint.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period. Provide this property, if no humidity range (Min-Max) is available.

HumiditySummer.name: Humidity Summer
HumiditySummer.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

HumidityWinter.name: Humidity Winter
HumidityWinter.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

MechanicalVentilation.name: Mechanical Ventilation
MechanicalVentilation.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have mechanical ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

MechanicalVentilationRate.name: Mechanical Ventilation Rate
MechanicalVentilationRate.Definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular mechanical air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

NaturalVentilation.name: Natural Ventilation
NaturalVentilation.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have natural ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

NaturalVentilationRate.name: Natural Ventilation Rate
NaturalVentilationRate.Definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular natural air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

TemperatureMax.name: Temperature Max
TemperatureMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

TemperatureMin.name: Temperature Min
TemperatureMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

TemperatureSetPoint.name: Temperature Set Point
TemperatureSetPoint.Definition: The temperature setpoint range and default setpoint.

TemperatureSummerMax.name: Temperature Summer Max
TemperatureSummerMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

TemperatureSummerMin.name: Temperature Summer Min
TemperatureSummerMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

TemperatureWinterMax.name: Temperature Winter Max
TemperatureWinterMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

TemperatureWinterMin.name: Temperature Winter Min
TemperatureWinterMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

ArtificialLighting.name: Artificial Lighting
ArtificialLighting.Definition: Indication whether this space requires artificial lighting (as natural lighting would be not sufficient). (TRUE) indicates yes (FALSE) otherwise.

Illuminance.name: Illuminance
Illuminance.Definition: Required average illuminance value for this space.

AreaPerOccupant.name: Area Per Occupant
AreaPerOccupant.Definition: Design occupancy loading for this type of usage assigned to this space.

IsOutlookDesirable.name: Is Outlook Desirable
IsOutlookDesirable.Definition: An indication of whether the outlook is desirable (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE)

MinimumHeadroom.name: Minimum Headroom
MinimumHeadroom.Definition: Headroom required for the activity assigned to this space.

OccupancyNumber.name: Occupancy Number
OccupancyNumber.Definition: Number of people required for the activity assigned to this space.

OccupancyNumberPeak.name: Occupancy Number Peak
OccupancyNumberPeak.Definition: Maximal number of people required for the activity assigned to this space in peak time.

OccupancyTimePerDay.name: Occupancy Time Per Day
OccupancyTimePerDay.Definition: The amount of time during the day that the activity is required within this space.

IsExternal.name: Is External
IsExternal.Definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

AirSideSystemDistributionType.name: Air Side System Distribution Type
AirSideSystemDistributionType.Definition: This enumeration defines the basic types of air side systems (e.g., Single Duct, Dual Duct, Multizone, etc.).

AirSideSystemType.name: Air Side System Type
AirSideSystemType.Definition: This enumeration specifies the basic types of possible air side systems (e.g., Constant Volume, Variable Volume, etc.).

CoolingTemperatureDelta.name: Cooling Temperature Delta
CoolingTemperatureDelta.Definition: Cooling temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

EnergyGainSensible.name: Energy Gain Sensible
EnergyGainSensible.Definition: The sum of total energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level sensible energy gains.

EnergyGainTotal.name: Energy Gain Total
EnergyGainTotal.Definition: The total amount of energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level total energy gains.

EnergyLoss.name: Energy Loss
EnergyLoss.Definition: The sum of energy losses for the spaces served by the system during the peak heating conditions.

FanPower.name: Fan Power
FanPower.Definition: Fan motor loads contributing to the cooling load.

HeatingTemperatureDelta.name: Heating Temperature Delta
HeatingTemperatureDelta.Definition: Heating temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

LongName.name: Long Name
LongName.Definition: Long name for a spatial zone type, used for informal purposes. It should be used, if available, in conjunction with the inherited Name attribute.

IfcSpatialZoneType.Definition: The Ifc Spatial Zone Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a space and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a space specification (i.e. the specific space information, that is common to all occurrences of that space type).
IfcSpatialZoneType.Name: Spatial Zone Type

IfcSystem.Definition: A system is an organized combination of related parts within an AEC product, composed for a common purpose or function or to provide a service. A system is essentially a functionally related aggregation of products. The grouping relationship to one or several instances of Ifc Product (the system members) is handled by Ifc Rel Assigns To Group.
IfcSystem.Name: System

AcceptanceDate.name: Acceptance Date
AcceptanceDate.Definition: Date on which the element is accepted by the manager or administrator.

InstallationDate.name: Installation Date
InstallationDate.Definition: Date on which the element is installed.

PutIntoOperationDate.name: Put Into Operation Date
PutIntoOperationDate.Definition: Date on which the element is put into operation.

RepairContent.name: Repair Content
RepairContent.Definition: Content of repair, reason and nature can be given, e.g. display faults, communication failure, display exchange.

RepairDate.name: Repair Date
RepairDate.Definition: Date on which the last repair is done on the asset.

AssessmentCondition.name: Assessment Condition
AssessmentCondition.Definition: The overall condition of a product based on an assessment of the contributions to the overall condition made by the various criteria considered. The meanings given to the values of assessed condition should be agreed and documented by local agreements. For instance, is overall condition measured on a scale of 1 - 10 or by assigning names such as Good, OK, Poor.

AssessmentDate.name: Assessment Date
AssessmentDate.Definition: Date on which the overall condition is assessed

AssessmentFrequency.name: Assessment Frequency
AssessmentFrequency.Definition: Indicates how often the equipment should be assessed, to have a clear estimation on its working state, based on which the maintenance staff can decide whether it requires maintenance or requires to be updated or replaced.

AssessmentMethod.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssessmentMethod.name: Assessment Method
AssessmentMethod.Definition: External reference to assessment method or application used to perform the assessment.

AssessmentType.name: Assessment Type
AssessmentType.Definition: Category of latest condition assessment report of the asset.

LastAssessmentReport.name: Last Assessment Report
LastAssessmentReport.Definition: Reference to latest condition (state of health) report.

AccidentResponse.name: Accident Response
AccidentResponse.Definition: Accident response chosen for the asset

AssetCriticality.name: Asset Criticality
AssetCriticality.Definition: Rating of the assets criticality to the operation of the facility

AssetFrailty.name: Asset Frailty
AssetFrailty.Definition: Rating of the assets frailty to breakage or deterioration

AssetPriority.name: Asset Priority
AssetPriority.Definition: Combined criticality and frailty rating indicating the operational and maintenance priority of the asset

MonitoringType.name: Monitoring Type
MonitoringType.Definition: Monitoring strategy chosen for the asset

ConditionDisposalLevel.name: Condition Disposal Level
ConditionDisposalLevel.Definition: Condition that will trigger a disposal process

ConditionReplacementLevel.name: Condition Replacement Level
ConditionReplacementLevel.Definition: Condition that will trigger a replacement process

DurationDisposalLevel.name: Duration Disposal Level
DurationDisposalLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which disposal is performed

DurationMaintenanceLevel.name: Duration Maintenance Level
DurationMaintenanceLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which maintenance is performed

DurationReplacementLevel.name: Duration Replacement Level
DurationReplacementLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which replacement is performed

DurationTargetPerformance.name: Duration Target Performance
DurationTargetPerformance.Definition: Target time to failure of the asset

DisposalLevel.name: Disposal Level
DisposalLevel.Definition: Performance level at which disposal takes place

PerformanceMaintenanceLevel.name: Performance Maintenance Level
PerformanceMaintenanceLevel.Definition: Performance level at which maintenance takes place

ReplacementLevel.name: Replacement Level
ReplacementLevel.Definition: Performance level at which replacement takes place

TargetPerformance.name: Target Performance
TargetPerformance.Definition: Target capacity or performance of the asset. Units of the performance value are specified through the property Value units attribute.

DesignLevel.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DesignLevel.name: Design Level
DesignLevel.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of design level employed.

IndoorEnvironment.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
IndoorEnvironment.name: Indoor Environment
IndoorEnvironment.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the indoor environment (where appropriate).

InUseConditions.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
InUseConditions.name: In Use Conditions
InUseConditions.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the conditions in which components are operating.

MaintenanceLevel.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
MaintenanceLevel.name: Maintenance Level
MaintenanceLevel.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the level or degree of maintenance applied to dcomponents.

OutdoorEnvironment.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
OutdoorEnvironment.name: Outdoor Environment
OutdoorEnvironment.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the outdoor environment (where appropriate)

QualityOfComponents.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
QualityOfComponents.name: Quality of Components
QualityOfComponents.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the quality of components used.

WorkExecutionLevel.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
WorkExecutionLevel.name: Work Execution Level
WorkExecutionLevel.Definition: Adjustment of the service life resulting from the effect of the quality of work executed.

IfcTransportationDevice.Definition: Abstract intermediate supertype for transportation devices.
IfcTransportationDevice.Name: Transportation Device

EnergyConversionEfficiency.name: Energy Conversion Efficiency
EnergyConversionEfficiency.Definition: Measure of the efficiency of conversion of fuel energy to mechanical energy

EnergySourceLabel.name: Energy Source Label
EnergySourceLabel.Definition: Type of energy source e.g. Electricity, Diesel, LPG etc. utilised by the element.

CarbonDioxideEmissions.name: Carbon Dioxide Emissions
CarbonDioxideEmissions.Definition: Rate of emission of carbon dioxide

NitrogenOxidesEmissions.name: Nitrogen Oxides Emissions
NitrogenOxidesEmissions.Definition: Rate of emission of nitrogen oxides

ParticulateMatterEmissions.name: Particulate Matter Emissions
ParticulateMatterEmissions.Definition: Rate of emission of particulate matter

SulphurDioxideEmissions.name: Sulphur Dioxide Emissions
SulphurDioxideEmissions.Definition: Rate of emission of sulphur dioxide

DownstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DownstreamConnections.name: Downstream Connections
DownstreamConnections.Definition: Names of downstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

ProcessCapacity.name: Process Capacity
ProcessCapacity.Definition: The number of units that can be processed in the time defined in Process Performance

ProcessItem.name: Process Item
ProcessItem.Definition: The type of item (and its measurement method) being modelled within a process. This can be cargo, passengers or vehicles that pass through the system.

ProcessPerformance.name: Process Performance
ProcessPerformance.Definition: Minimum time to accept or dispatch the entire item capacity.

UpstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
UpstreamConnections.name: Upstream Connections
UpstreamConnections.Definition: Names of upstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

CapacityPeople.name: Capacity People
CapacityPeople.Definition: Capacity of the transportation element measured in numbers of person.

CapacityWeight.name: Capacity Weight
CapacityWeight.Definition: Capacity of the transport element measured by weight.

FireExit.name: Fire Exit
FireExit.Definition: Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

IfcTransportElement.Definition: A transport element is a generalization of all transport related objects that move people, animals or goods within a Facility. The Ifc Transport Element defines the occurrence of a transport element, that (if given), is expressed by the Ifc Transport Element Type.
IfcTransportElement.Name: Transport Element

IfcTransportElementType.Definition: The element type Ifc Transport Element Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of transport elements. The set of shared information may includecommon properties within shared property sets
IfcTransportElementType.Name: Transport Element Type

IfcVehicle.Definition: Piece of equipment designed to transport people or cargo.
IfcVehicle.Name: Vehicle

IfcVibrationDamper.Definition: A vibration damper is a device used to minimize the effects of vibration in a structure by dissipating kinetic energy. The damper may be passive (elastic, frictional, inertia) or active (in a system using sensors and actuators).
IfcVibrationDamper.Name: Vibration Damper

IfcVibrationDamperType.Definition: The Ifc Vibration Damper Type provides the type information for Ifc Vibration Damper occurrences.
IfcVibrationDamperType.Name: Vibration Damper Type

IfcVirtualElement.Definition: A virtual element is a special element used to provide imaginary, placeholder, or provisional areas, volumes, and boundaries. Virtual elements are usually not displayed and do not have quantities, associated materials, and other measures.Uses of Ifc Virtual Element includeAn imaginary boundary such as between two adjacent, but not separated, spaces. The Ifc Virtual Element may provide the 2D curve or 3D surface representation of the virtual space connection and is referenced by two instances of Ifc Rel Space Boundary, each pointing to one of the two adjacent Ifc Spaces. The boundary is exchanged using Predefined Type BOUNDARY.
IfcVirtualElement.Name: Virtual Element

IfcZone.Definition: A zone is a group of spaces, partial spaces or other zones. These spaces may or may not be adjacent. A zone does not have its own shape representation. Zone structures may not be hierarchical (in contrary to the spatial structure of a project - see Ifc Spatial Structure Element), i.e. one individual Ifc Space may be associated with zero, one, or several Ifc Zones. Ifc Spaces are grouped into an Ifc Zone by using the objectified relationship Ifc Rel Assigns To Group as specified at the supertype Ifc Group. For example, a zone might be used to represent an apartment as a group of spaces.
IfcZone.Name: Qtospace Base Quantities

DownstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DownstreamConnections.name: Downstream Connections
DownstreamConnections.Definition: Names of downstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

ProcessCapacity.name: Process Capacity
ProcessCapacity.Definition: The number of units that can be processed in the time defined in Process Performance

ProcessItem.name: Process Item
ProcessItem.Definition: The type of item (and its measurement method) being modelled within a process. This can be cargo, passengers or vehicles that pass through the system.

ProcessPerformance.name: Process Performance
ProcessPerformance.Definition: Minimum time to accept or dispatch the entire item capacity.

UpstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
UpstreamConnections.name: Upstream Connections
UpstreamConnections.Definition: Names of upstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

AirPressurization.name: Air Pressurization
AirPressurization.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have pressurized air (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

FireExit.name: Fire Exit
FireExit.Definition: Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

FireRiskFactor.name: Fire Risk Factor
FireRiskFactor.Definition: Fire Risk factor assigned to the space according to local building regulations. It defines the fire risk of the space at several levels of fire hazard.

FlammableStorage.name: Flammable Storage
FlammableStorage.Definition: Indication whether the space is intended to serve as a storage of flammable material (which is regarded as such by the presiding building code. (TRUE) indicates yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

SprinklerProtection.name: Sprinkler Protection
SprinklerProtection.Definition: Indication whether this object is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

SprinklerProtectionAutomatic.name: Sprinkler Protection Automatic
SprinklerProtectionAutomatic.Definition: Indication whether this object has an automatic sprinkler protection (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirConditioning.name: Air Conditioning
AirConditioning.Definition: Indication whether this space requires air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirConditioningCentral.name: Air Conditioning Central
AirConditioningCentral.Definition: Indication whether the space requires a central air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

AirHandlingName.name: Air Handling Name
AirHandlingName.Definition: The name of the air side system.Ifc Rel Services Buildings should be used to reference the correct Air Handling System (Ifc System)

DiscontinuedHeating.name: Discontinued Heating
DiscontinuedHeating.Definition: Indication whether discontinued heating is requireddesirable from userdesigner view point. (TRUE) if yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

HumidityMax.name: Humidity Max
HumidityMax.Definition: Maximal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

HumidityMin.name: Humidity Min
HumidityMin.Definition: Minimal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

HumiditySetPoint.name: Humidity Set Point
HumiditySetPoint.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period. Provide this property, if no humidity range (Min-Max) is available.

HumiditySummer.name: Humidity Summer
HumiditySummer.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

HumidityWinter.name: Humidity Winter
HumidityWinter.Definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

MechanicalVentilation.name: Mechanical Ventilation
MechanicalVentilation.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have mechanical ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

MechanicalVentilationRate.name: Mechanical Ventilation Rate
MechanicalVentilationRate.Definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular mechanical air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

NaturalVentilation.name: Natural Ventilation
NaturalVentilation.Definition: Indication whether the space is required to have natural ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

NaturalVentilationRate.name: Natural Ventilation Rate
NaturalVentilationRate.Definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular natural air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

TemperatureMax.name: Temperature Max
TemperatureMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

TemperatureMin.name: Temperature Min
TemperatureMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from userdesigner view point. If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

TemperatureSetPoint.name: Temperature Set Point
TemperatureSetPoint.Definition: The temperature setpoint range and default setpoint.

TemperatureSummerMax.name: Temperature Summer Max
TemperatureSummerMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

TemperatureSummerMin.name: Temperature Summer Min
TemperatureSummerMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

TemperatureWinterMax.name: Temperature Winter Max
TemperatureWinterMax.Definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

TemperatureWinterMin.name: Temperature Winter Min
TemperatureWinterMin.Definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from userdesigner view point and provided as requirement for heating.

ArtificialLighting.name: Artificial Lighting
ArtificialLighting.Definition: Indication whether this space requires artificial lighting (as natural lighting would be not sufficient). (TRUE) indicates yes (FALSE) otherwise.

Illuminance.name: Illuminance
Illuminance.Definition: Required average illuminance value for this space.

AreaPerOccupant.name: Area Per Occupant
AreaPerOccupant.Definition: Design occupancy loading for this type of usage assigned to this space.

IsOutlookDesirable.name: Is Outlook Desirable
IsOutlookDesirable.Definition: An indication of whether the outlook is desirable (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE)

MinimumHeadroom.name: Minimum Headroom
MinimumHeadroom.Definition: Headroom required for the activity assigned to this space.

OccupancyNumber.name: Occupancy Number
OccupancyNumber.Definition: Number of people required for the activity assigned to this space.

OccupancyNumberPeak.name: Occupancy Number Peak
OccupancyNumberPeak.Definition: Maximal number of people required for the activity assigned to this space in peak time.

OccupancyTimePerDay.name: Occupancy Time Per Day
OccupancyTimePerDay.Definition: The amount of time during the day that the activity is required within this space.

GrossPlannedArea.name: Gross Planned Area
GrossPlannedArea.Definition: Total planned gross area of the spatial structure element. Used for programming the spatial structure element.

HandicapAccessible.name: Handicap Accessible
HandicapAccessible.Definition: Indication that this object is designed to be accessible by the handicapped. Set to (TRUE) if this object is rated as handicap accessible according to the local building codes, otherwise (FALSE). It is giving according to the requirements of the national building code.

IsExternal.name: Is External
IsExternal.Definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

NetPlannedArea.name: Net Planned Area
NetPlannedArea.Definition: Total planned net area of the object. Used for programming the object.

PubliclyAccessible.name: Publicly Accessible
PubliclyAccessible.Definition: Indication whether this space (in case of e.g., a toilet) is designed to serve as a publicly accessible space, e.g., for a public toilet (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

AirSideSystemDistributionType.name: Air Side System Distribution Type
AirSideSystemDistributionType.Definition: This enumeration defines the basic types of air side systems (e.g., Single Duct, Dual Duct, Multizone, etc.).

AirSideSystemType.name: Air Side System Type
AirSideSystemType.Definition: This enumeration specifies the basic types of possible air side systems (e.g., Constant Volume, Variable Volume, etc.).

CoolingTemperatureDelta.name: Cooling Temperature Delta
CoolingTemperatureDelta.Definition: Cooling temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

EnergyGainSensible.name: Energy Gain Sensible
EnergyGainSensible.Definition: The sum of total energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level sensible energy gains.

EnergyGainTotal.name: Energy Gain Total
EnergyGainTotal.Definition: The total amount of energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level total energy gains.

EnergyLoss.name: Energy Loss
EnergyLoss.Definition: The sum of energy losses for the spaces served by the system during the peak heating conditions.

FanPower.name: Fan Power
FanPower.Definition: Fan motor loads contributing to the cooling load.

HeatingTemperatureDelta.name: Heating Temperature Delta
HeatingTemperatureDelta.Definition: Heating temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

LongName.name: Long Name
LongName.Definition: Long name for a zone, used for informal purposes. It should be used, if available, in conjunction with the inherited Name attribute.

IfcArbitraryClosedProfileDef.Definition: The closed profile Ifc Arbitrary Closed Profile Def defines an arbitrary two-dimensional profile for the use within the swept surface geometry, the swept area solid or a sectioned spine. It is given by an outer boundary from which the surface or solid can be constructed.
IfcArbitraryClosedProfileDef.Name: Arbitrary Closed Profile Def

FlangeBaseFillet.name: Flange Base Fillet
FlangeBaseFillet.Definition: Flange base fillet of the profile.

FlangeTopFillet.name: Flange Top Fillet
FlangeTopFillet.Definition: Flange top fillet of the profile.

LeftFlangeWidth.name: Left Flange Width
LeftFlangeWidth.Definition: Left flange width of the profile.

RightFlangeWidth.name: Right Flange Width
RightFlangeWidth.Definition: Right flange width of the profile.

StemBaseChamfer.name: Stem Base Chamfer
StemBaseChamfer.Definition: Stem base chamfer of the profile.

StemBaseFillet.name: Stem Base Fillet
StemBaseFillet.Definition: Stem base fillet of the profile.

StemBaseWidth.name: Stem Base Width
StemBaseWidth.Definition: Stem base width of the profile.

StemTopChamfer.name: Stem Top Chamfer
StemTopChamfer.Definition: Stem top chamfer of the profile.

StemTopFillet.name: Stem Top Fillet
StemTopFillet.Definition: Stem top fillet of the profile.

StemTopWidth.name: Stem Top Width
StemTopWidth.Definition: Stem top width of the profile.

IfcArbitraryOpenProfileDef.Definition: The open profile Ifc Arbitrary Open Profile Def defines an arbitrary two-dimensional open profile for the use within the swept surface geometry. It is given by an open boundary from which the surface can be constructed.
IfcArbitraryOpenProfileDef.Name: Arbitrary Open Profile Def

IfcArbitraryProfileDefWithVoids.Definition: The Ifc Arbitrary Profile Def With Voids defines an arbitrary closed two-dimensional profile with holes. It is given by an outer boundary and inner boundaries. A common usage of Ifc Arbitrary Profile Def With Voids is as the cross section for the creation of swept surfaces or swept solids.
IfcArbitraryProfileDefWithVoids.Name: Arbitrary Profile Def With Voids

CenterCoreBaseHeight.name: Center Core Base Height
CenterCoreBaseHeight.Definition: Center core base height of the profile.

CenterCoreBaseWidth.name: Center Core Base Width
CenterCoreBaseWidth.Definition: Center core base width of the profile.

CenterCoreMiddleHeight.name: Center Core Middle Height
CenterCoreMiddleHeight.Definition: Center core middle height of the profile.

CenterCoreSpacing.name: Center Core Spacing
CenterCoreSpacing.Definition: Center core spacing of the profile.

CenterCoreTopHeight.name: Center Core Top Height
CenterCoreTopHeight.Definition: Center core top height of the profile.

CenterCoreTopWidth.name: Center Core Top Width
CenterCoreTopWidth.Definition: Center core top width of the profile.

CoreBaseHeight.name: Core Base Height
CoreBaseHeight.Definition: Core base height of the profile.

CoreBaseWidth.name: Core Base Width
CoreBaseWidth.Definition: Core base width of the profile.

CoreMiddleHeight.name: Core Middle Height
CoreMiddleHeight.Definition: Core middle height of the profile.

CoreTopHeight.name: Core Top Height
CoreTopHeight.Definition: Core top height of the profile.

CoreTopWidth.name: Core Top Width
CoreTopWidth.Definition: Core top width of the profile.

DraftBaseOffset.name: Draft Base Offset
DraftBaseOffset.Definition: Draft base offset of the profile.

DraftSideOffset.name: Draft Side Offset
DraftSideOffset.Definition: Draft side offset of the profile.

IfcAsymmetricIShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Asymmetric IShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a singly symmetric I-shaped section. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.The overall width of the profile is implicitly given by the maximum of the bottom flange width and the top flange width.Ifc Asymmetric IShape Profile Def can also be used to model rail profiles if the application scenario does not require a full explicit shape model of the rail profile. Alternatively, Ifc Arbitrary Closed Profile Def can be used to provide the exact shape of rail profiles. Either way, a reference to an external document or library should be provided to further define the profile as described at Ifc Profile Def.
IfcAsymmetricIShapeProfileDef.Name: Asymmetric Ishape Profile Def

BottomFlangeEdgeRadius.name: Bottom Flange Edge Radius
BottomFlangeEdgeRadius.Definition: Radius of the upper edges of the bottom flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

BottomFlangeFilletRadius.name: Bottom Flange Fillet Radius
BottomFlangeFilletRadius.Definition: The fillet between the web and the bottom flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

BottomFlangeSlope.name: Bottom Flange Slope
BottomFlangeSlope.Definition: Slope of the upper faces of the bottom flange. Non-zero in case of of tapered bottom flange, 0 in case of parallel bottom flange, omitted if unknown.

BottomFlangeThickness.name: Bottom Flange Thickness
BottomFlangeThickness.Definition: Flange thickness of the bottom flange.

BottomFlangeWidth.name: Bottom Flange Width
BottomFlangeWidth.Definition: Extent of the bottom flange, defined parallel to the x axis of the position coordinate system.

OverallDepth.name: Overall Depth
OverallDepth.Definition: Total extent of the depth, defined parallel to the y axis of the position coordinate system.

TopFlangeEdgeRadius.name: Top Flange Edge Radius
TopFlangeEdgeRadius.Definition: Radius of the lower edges of the top flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

TopFlangeFilletRadius.name: Top Flange Fillet Radius
TopFlangeFilletRadius.Definition: The fillet between the web and the top flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

TopFlangeSlope.name: Top Flange Slope
TopFlangeSlope.Definition: Slope of the lower faces of the top flange. Non-zero in case of of tapered top flange, 0 in case of parallel top flange, omitted if unknown.

TopFlangeThickness.name: Top Flange Thickness
TopFlangeThickness.Definition: Flange thickness of the top flange. This attribute is formally optional for historic reasons only. Whenever the flange thickness is known, it shall be provided by value.

TopFlangeWidth.name: Top Flange Width
TopFlangeWidth.Definition: Extent of the top flange, defined parallel to the x axis of the position coordinate system.

WebThickness.name: Web Thickness
WebThickness.Definition: Thickness of the web of the I-shape. The web is centred on the x-axis and the y-axis of the position coordinate system.

IfcCenterLineProfileDef.Definition: The profile Ifc Center Line Profile Def defines an arbitrary two-dimensional open, not self intersecting profile for the use within the swept solid geometry. It is given by an area defined by applying a constant thickness to a centerline, generating an area from which the solid can be constructed.Among else, Ifc Center Line Profile Def is used to model cold-formed steel or aluminium sections (Sigma, Zeta, Omega, and similar sections which are not covered by subtypes of Ifc Parameterized Profile Def). However, since Ifc Center Line Profile Def does not provide shape parameters except for the thickness, there is generally a need to further specify the profile definition by means ofthe name,
IfcCenterLineProfileDef.Name: Center Line Profile Def

Thickness.name: Thickness
Thickness.Definition: Constant thickness applied along the center line.

IfcCircleHollowProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Circle Hollow Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a circular hollow section (tube) to be used by the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration.The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box (for symmetric profiles identical with the centre of gravity).
IfcCircleHollowProfileDef.Name: Circle Hollow Profile Def

WallThickness.name: Wall Thickness
WallThickness.Definition: Thickness of the material, it is the difference between the outer and inner radius.

IfcCircleProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Circle Profile Def defines a circle as the profile definition used by the swept surface geometry or by the swept area solid. It is given by its Radius attribute and placed within the 2D position coordinate system, established by the Position attribute.
IfcCircleProfileDef.Name: Circle Profile Def

IfcCompositeProfileDef.Definition: The Ifc Composite Profile Def defines the profile by composition of other profiles. The composition is given by a set of at least two other profile definitions. Any profile definition (except for another composite profile) can be used to construct the composite.
IfcCompositeProfileDef.Name: Composite Profile Def

Label.name: Label
Label.Definition: The name by which the composition may be referred to. The actual meaning of the name has to be defined in the context of applications.

IfcCShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc CShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a C-shaped section to be used by the swept area solid. This section is typically produced by cold forming steel. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.
IfcCShapeProfileDef.Name: Cshape Profile Def

Depth.name: Depth
Depth.Definition: Profile depth, see illustration above ( h).

Girth.name: Girth
Girth.Definition: Lengths of girth, see illustration above ( c).

InternalFilletRadius.name: Internal Fillet Radius
InternalFilletRadius.Definition: Internal fillet radius according the above illustration ( r1).

WallThickness.name: Wall Thickness
WallThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of profile ( ts).

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: Profile width, see illustration above ( b).

IfcDerivedProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Derived Profile Def defines the profile by transformation from the parent profile. The transformation is given by a two dimensional transformation operator. Transformation includes translation, rotation, mirror and scaling. The latter can be uniform or non uniform. The derived profiles may be used to define swept surfaces, swept area solids or sectioned spines.The transformation effects the position, rotation, mirroring or scale of the profile at the underlying coordinate system, i.e. the coordinate system defined by the swept surface or swept area solid that uses the profile definition. It is the xy plane of eitherIfc Swept Surface.Position
IfcDerivedProfileDef.Name: Derived Profile Def

Label.name: Label
Label.Definition: The name by which the transformation may be referred to. The actual meaning of the name has to be defined in the context of applications.

IfcEllipseProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Ellipse Profile Def defines an ellipse as the profile definition used by the swept surface geometry or the swept area solid. It is given by its semi axis attributes and placed within the 2D position coordinate system, established by the Position attribute.
IfcEllipseProfileDef.Name: Ellipse Profile Def

SemiAxis1.name: Semi Axis1
SemiAxis1.Definition: The first radius of the ellipse. It is measured along the direction of Position.P1.

SemiAxis2.name: Semi Axis2
SemiAxis2.Definition: The second radius of the ellipse. It is measured along the direction of Position.P2.

IfcIShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc IShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of an I or H section. The I-shape profile has values for its overall depth, width and its web and flange thicknesses. Additionally a fillet radius, flange edge radius, and flange slope may be given. This profile definition represents an I-section which is symmetrical about its major and minor axes top and bottom flanges are equal and centred on the web.
IfcIShapeProfileDef.Name: Ishape Profile Def

FilletRadius.name: Fillet Radius
FilletRadius.Definition: The fillet between the web and the flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

FlangeEdgeRadius.name: Flange Edge Radius
FlangeEdgeRadius.Definition: Radius of the lower edges of the top flange and the upper edges of the bottom flange. 0 if sharp-edged, omitted if unknown.

FlangeSlope.name: Flange Slope
FlangeSlope.Definition: Slope of the lower faces of the top flange and of the upper faces of the bottom flange. Non-zero in case of tapered flanges, 0 in case of parallel flanges, omitted if unknown.

FlangeThickness.name: Flange Thickness
FlangeThickness.Definition: Flange thickness of the I-shape. Both, the upper and the lower flanges have the same thickness and they are centred on the y-axis of the position coordinate system.

OverallDepth.name: Overall Depth
OverallDepth.Definition: Total extent of the depth, defined parallel to the y axis of the position coordinate system.

OverallWidth.name: Overall Width
OverallWidth.Definition: Total extent of the width, defined parallel to the x axis of the position coordinate system.

WebThickness.name: Web Thickness
WebThickness.Definition: Thickness of the web of the I-shape. The web is centred on the x-axis and the y-axis of the position coordinate system.

IfcLShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc LShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of an L-shaped section (equilateral L profiles are also covered by this entity) to be used by the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The shorter leg has the same direction as the positive Position.P1-axis, the longer or equal leg the same as the positive Position.P2-axis. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.
IfcLShapeProfileDef.Name: Lshape Profile Def

Depth.name: Depth
Depth.Definition: Leg length, see illustration above ( h). Same as the overall depth.

EdgeRadius.name: Edge Radius
EdgeRadius.Definition: Edge radius according the above illustration ( r2).

FilletRadius.name: Fillet Radius
FilletRadius.Definition: Fillet radius according the above illustration ( r1).

LegSlope.name: Leg Slope
LegSlope.Definition: Slope of the inner face of each leg of the profile.

Thickness.name: Thickness
Thickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of profile, see illustration above ( ts).

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: Leg length, see illustration above ( b). Same as the overall width. This attribute is formally optional for historic reasons only. Whenever the width is known, it shall be provided by value.

IfcMirroredProfileDef.Definition: The Ifc Mirrored Profile Def defines the profile by mirroring the parent profile about the y axis of the parent profile coordinate system. That is, left and right of the parent profile are swapped.NotesIfc Mirrored Profile Def is primarily useful together with Ifc CShape Profile Def, Ifc LShape Profile Def, Ifc UShape Profile Def, or Ifc ZShape Profile Def as parent profile but can be used with other parent profile types as well.Mirroring of an Ifc Parameterized Profile Def is performed after translation and rotation according to its Position attribute. For example, if the parent profiles Position offsets it by half of its width to the right, then the mirrored profile will be offset by half of its width to the left.Mirroring about the x axis, i.e. swapping top and bottom, can be achieved by mirroring about the y axis coupled with 180 degree rotation about the z axis. In general, rotation happens in a containing object such as Ifc Swept Area Solid, i.e. after mirroring by Ifc Mirrored Profile Def was performed. If the parent profile is an Ifc Parameterized Profile Def, rotation can alternatively happen already in the parent profile by means of its Position attribute, i.e. before mirroring by Ifc Mirrored Profile Def was performed.
IfcMirroredProfileDef.Name: Mirrored Profile Def

IfcOpenCrossProfileDef.Definition: A two-dimensional open profile defined by widths and slopes for the use within the swept surface geometry, in Sectioned Surface in particular. The underlying coordinate system is defined by the swept surface that uses the profile definition when used in Sectioned Surface it is the XY plane of each list member of Sectioned Surface.Cross Section Positions where the profile X axis is oriented perpendicularly to the left of the Directrix (same direction as positive Lateral Offset at Ifc Point By Distance Expression) as facing forward along the directrix, and the profile Y axis is oriented upwards or vertically perpendicular to the Directrix depending on the usage in the Sectioned Surface.
IfcOpenCrossProfileDef.Name: Open Cross Profile Def

HorizontalWidths.name: Horizontal Widths
HorizontalWidths.Definition: Indicates if the widths shall be measured horizontally or along the slopes.

Widths.name: Widths
Widths.Definition: The horizontal widths (when Horizontal Widths.T.) or distances along the Slope (when Horizontal Widths.F.) for the segments in the profile. And if Horizontal.T. the Slopes shall not be - 90 deg.

IfcParameterizedProfileDef.Definition: The parameterized profile definition defines a 2D position coordinate system to which the parameters of the different profiles relate to. All profiles are defined centric to the origin of the position coordinate system, or more specific, the origin 0.,0. shall be in the center of the bounding box of the profile.The Position attribute of Ifc Parameterized Profile Def is used to position the profile within the XY plane of the underlying coordinate system of the swept surface geometry, the swept area solid or the sectioned spine. It can be used to position the profile at any point which becomes the origin 0.,0.,0. of the extruded or rotated surface or solid.The Position attribute should not be used if the transformation can be specified in a containing object instead. In particular, this applies if the Ifc Parameterized Profile Def is referenced as Swept Area in subtypes of Ifc Swept Area Solid or as Cross Sections in Ifc Sectioned Spine.Several subtypes of Ifc Parameterized Profile Def provide shape parameters which are optional. Sending systems should always provide values for these parameters if possible. If these parameters are left unspecified, receiving systems may retrieve values for them by external reference (if a reference to an external document or library is given see guidance at Ifc Profile Def), or estimate them, or simply assume zero values.
IfcParameterizedProfileDef.Name: Parameterized Profile Def

IfcProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Profile Def is the supertype of all definitions of standard and arbitrary profiles within IFC. It is used to define a standard set of commonly used section profiles by their parameters or by their explicit curve geometry.Parameterized profiles are 2D primitives, which are used within the industry to describe cross sections by a description of its parameters.
IfcProfileDef.Name: Profile Def

CentreOfGravityInX.name: Centre of Gravity In X
CentreOfGravityInX.Definition: Location of the profiles centre of gravity (geometric centroid), measured along xp.

CentreOfGravityInY.name: Centre of Gravity In Y
CentreOfGravityInY.Definition: Location of the profiles centre of gravity (geometric centroid), measured along yp.

CrossSectionArea.name: Cross Section Area
CrossSectionArea.Definition: Total area of the cross section (or profile) of the object.

MassPerLength.name: Mass Per Length
MassPerLength.Definition: Mass per length, i.e. mass of a beam with a unit length of extrusion. For example measured in kgm.

MaximumPlateThickness.name: Maximum Plate Thickness
MaximumPlateThickness.Definition: This value may be needed for stress analysis and to handle buckling problems. It can also be derived from the given profile geometry or classification and therefore it is only an optional feature allowing for an explicit description. For example measured in mm.

MaximumSectionModulusY.name: Maximum Section Modulus Y
MaximumSectionModulusY.Definition: Bending resistance about the ys axis at the point with maximum zs ordinate. For example measured in mm³.

MaximumSectionModulusZ.name: Maximum Section Modulus Z
MaximumSectionModulusZ.Definition: Bending resistance about the zs axis at the point with maximum ys ordinate. For example measured in mm³.

MinimumPlateThickness.name: Minimum Plate Thickness
MinimumPlateThickness.Definition: This value may be needed for stress analysis and to handle buckling problems. It can also be derived from the given profile geometry or classification and therefore it is only an optional feature allowing for an explicit description. For example measured in mm.

MinimumSectionModulusY.name: Minimum Section Modulus Y
MinimumSectionModulusY.Definition: Bending resistance about the ys axis at the point with minimum zs ordinate. For example measured in mm³.

MinimumSectionModulusZ.name: Minimum Section Modulus Z
MinimumSectionModulusZ.Definition: Bending resistance about the zs axis at the point with minimum ys ordinate. For example measured in mm³.

MomentOfInertiaY.name: Moment of Inertia Y
MomentOfInertiaY.Definition: Moment of inertia about ys (second moment of area, about ys). For example measured in mm4.

MomentOfInertiaYZ.name: Moment of Inertia Yz
MomentOfInertiaYZ.Definition: Moment of inertia about ys and zs (product moment of area). For example measured in mm4.

MomentOfInertiaZ.name: Moment of Inertia Z
MomentOfInertiaZ.Definition: Moment of inertia about zs (second moment of area, about zs). For example measured in mm4

PlasticShapeFactorY.name: Plastic Shape Factor Y
PlasticShapeFactorY.Definition: Ratio of plastic versus elastic bending moment capacity about the section analysis axis ys. A dimensionless value.

PlasticShapeFactorZ.name: Plastic Shape Factor Z
PlasticShapeFactorZ.Definition: Ratio of plastic versus elastic bending moment capacity about the section analysis axis zs. A dimensionless value.

ShearAreaY.name: Shear Area Y
ShearAreaY.Definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear stress due to shear force parallel to the section analysis axis ys. For example measured in mm². If given, the shear area ys shall be non-negative.

ShearAreaZ.name: Shear Area Z
ShearAreaZ.Definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear stress due to shear force parallel to the section analysis axis zs. For example measured in mm². If given, the shear area zs shall be non-negative.

ShearCentreY.name: Shear Centre Y
ShearCentreY.Definition: Location of the profiles shear centre, measured along ys.

ShearCentreZ.name: Shear Centre Z
ShearCentreZ.Definition: Location of the profiles shear centre, measured along zs.

ShearDeformationAreaY.name: Shear Deformation Area Y
ShearDeformationAreaY.Definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear deformation due to a shear force parallel to ys. For example measured in mm². If given, the shear deformation area ys shall be non-negative.

ShearDeformationAreaZ.name: Shear Deformation Area Z
ShearDeformationAreaZ.Definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear deformation due to a shear force parallel to zs. For example measured in mm². If given, the shear deformation area zs shall be non-negative.

TorsionalConstantX.name: Torsional Constant X
TorsionalConstantX.Definition: Torsional constant about xs. For example measured in mm4.

TorsionalSectionModulus.name: Torsional Section Modulus
TorsionalSectionModulus.Definition: Torsional resistance (about xs). For example measured in mm³.

WarpingConstant.name: Warping Constant
WarpingConstant.Definition: Warping constant of the profile for torsional action. For example measured in mm6.

ProfileName.name: Profile Name
ProfileName.Definition: Human-readable name of the profile, for example according to a standard profile table. As noted above, machine-readable standardized profile designations should be provided in Ifc External Reference.Item Reference.

ProfileType.Definition: Defines the type of geometry into which this profile definition shall be resolved, either a curve or a surface area. In case of curve the profile should be referenced by a swept surface, in case of area the profile should be referenced by a swept area solid.

IfcRectangleHollowProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Rectangle Hollow Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a rectangular (or square) hollow section to be used by the swept surface geometry or the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. A square hollow section can be defined by equal values for h and b. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box (for symmetric profiles identical with the centre of gravity). Normally, the longer sides are parallel to the y-axis, the shorter sides parallel to the x-axis.
IfcRectangleHollowProfileDef.Name: Rectangle Hollow Profile Def

IfcRectangleProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Rectangle Profile Def defines a rectangle as the profile definition used by the swept surface geometry or the swept area solid. It is given by its X extent and its Y extent, and placed within the 2D position coordinate system, established by the Position attribute. It is placed centric within the position coordinate system.
IfcRectangleProfileDef.Name: Rectangle Profile Def

XDim.name: Xdim
XDim.Definition: The extent of the rectangle in the direction of the x-axis.

YDim.name: Ydim
YDim.Definition: The extent of the rectangle in the direction of the y-axis.

IfcRoundedRectangleProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Rounded Rectangle Profile Def defines a rectangle with equally rounded corners as the profile definition used by the swept surface geometry or the swept area solid. It is given by the X extent, the Y extent, and the radius for the rounded corners, and placed within the 2D position coordinate system, established by the Position attribute. It is placed centric within the position coordinate system, that is, in the center of the bounding box.
IfcRoundedRectangleProfileDef.Name: Rounded Rectangle Profile Def

RoundingRadius.name: Rounding Radius
RoundingRadius.Definition: Radius of the circular arcs by which all four corners of the rectangle are equally rounded.

IfcTrapeziumProfileDef.Definition: Ifc Trapezium Profile Def defines a trapezium as the profile definition used by the swept surface geometry or the swept area solid. It is given by its Top X and Bottom X extent and its Y extent as well as by the offset of the Top X extend, and placed within the 2D position coordinate system, established by the Position attribute. It is placed centric within the position coordinate system, that is, in the center of the bounding box.
IfcTrapeziumProfileDef.Name: Trapezium Profile Def

BottomXDim.name: Bottom Xdim
BottomXDim.Definition: The extent of the bottom line measured along the implicit x-axis.

TopXDim.name: Top Xdim
TopXDim.Definition: The extent of the top line measured along the implicit x-axis.

TopXOffset.name: Top Xoffset
TopXOffset.Definition: Offset from the beginning of the top line to the bottom line, measured along the implicit x-axis.

YDim.name: Ydim
YDim.Definition: The extent of the distance between the parallel bottom and top lines measured along the implicit y-axis.

IfcTShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc TShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a T-shaped section to be used by the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.
IfcTShapeProfileDef.Name: Tshape Profile Def

Depth.name: Depth
Depth.Definition: Web lengths, see illustration above ( h).

FilletRadius.name: Fillet Radius
FilletRadius.Definition: Fillet radius according the above illustration ( r1).

FlangeEdgeRadius.name: Flange Edge Radius
FlangeEdgeRadius.Definition: Edge radius according the above illustration ( r2).

FlangeSlope.name: Flange Slope
FlangeSlope.Definition: Slope of web of the profile.

FlangeThickness.name: Flange Thickness
FlangeThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of flange ( tg).

FlangeWidth.name: Flange Width
FlangeWidth.Definition: Flange lengths, see illustration above ( b).

WebEdgeRadius.name: Web Edge Radius
WebEdgeRadius.Definition: Edge radius according the above illustration ( r3).

WebSlope.name: Web Slope
WebSlope.Definition: Slope of flange of the profile.

WebThickness.name: Web Thickness
WebThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of web ( ts).

IfcUShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc UShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a U-shape (channel) section to be used by the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.
IfcUShapeProfileDef.Name: Ushape Profile Def

Depth.name: Depth
Depth.Definition: Web lengths, see illustration above ( h).

EdgeRadius.name: Edge Radius
EdgeRadius.Definition: Edge radius according the above illustration ( r2).

FilletRadius.name: Fillet Radius
FilletRadius.Definition: Fillet radius according the above illustration ( r1).

FlangeSlope.name: Flange Slope
FlangeSlope.Definition: Slope of flange of the profile.

FlangeThickness.name: Flange Thickness
FlangeThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of flange ( tg).

FlangeWidth.name: Flange Width
FlangeWidth.Definition: Flange lengths, see illustration above ( b).

WebThickness.name: Web Thickness
WebThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of web ( ts).

IfcZShapeProfileDef.Definition: Ifc ZShape Profile Def defines a section profile that provides the defining parameters of a Z-shape section to be used by the swept area solid. Its parameters and orientation relative to the position coordinate system are according to the following illustration. The centre of the position coordinate system is in the profiles centre of the bounding box.
IfcZShapeProfileDef.Name: Profile Mechanical

Depth.name: Depth
Depth.Definition: Web length, see illustration above ( h).

EdgeRadius.name: Edge Radius
EdgeRadius.Definition: Edge radius according the above illustration ( r2).

FilletRadius.name: Fillet Radius
FilletRadius.Definition: Fillet radius according the above illustration ( r1).

FlangeThickness.name: Flange Thickness
FlangeThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of flange, see illustration above ( tg).

FlangeWidth.name: Flange Width
FlangeWidth.Definition: Flange length, see illustration above ( b).

WebThickness.name: Web Thickness
WebThickness.Definition: Constant wall thickness of web, see illustration above ( ts).

IfcRail.Definition: A rail is a predominately linear built element that has a special section profile. Rail is distinctive from built elements with similar geometric shapes (e.g. beam, member) that its major function is to ensure guidance of moving for vehicles or other kinds of machineries.
IfcRail.Name: Rail

IfcRailType.Definition: The element type Ifc Rail Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of rails. The set of shared information may include
IfcRailType.Name: Rail Type

IfcRailway.Definition: An Ifc Railway is a spatial structure element as a route from one location to another for guided passage of wheeled vehicles on rails. An Ifc Railway acts as a basic spatial structure element that supports to break down a railway project into manageable parts.
IfcRailway.Name: Railway

IfcTrackElement.Definition: A track element is a built element used specifically in the track domain in railway.
IfcTrackElement.Name: Track Element

IfcTrackElementType.Definition: The element type Ifc Track Element Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of track elements. The set of shared information may include
IfcTrackElementType.Name: Qtospatial Zone Base Quantities

IfcKerb.Definition: A border of stone, concrete or other rigid material formed at the edge of the carriageway or footway.
IfcKerb.Name: Kerb

CombinedKerbGutter.name: Combined Kerb Gutter
CombinedKerbGutter.Definition: Indicating the use of a combined kerb and gutter.

Mountable.name: Mountable
Mountable.Definition: Specifies whether the kerb can be readily climbed by a vehicle or not.

Upstand.name: Upstand
Upstand.Definition: The height difference between the two separated surfaces.

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

StoneFinishes.name: Stone Finishes
StoneFinishes.Definition: Eg. Polished, Bush Hammered, Split, Sawn, Flamed

TypeDesignation.name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. Bull nose, Half batter, Dropper, Chamfer etc

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

TypeDesignation.name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. Bull nose, Half batter, Dropper, Chamfer etc

CurveShape.name: Curve Shape
CurveShape.Definition: Shape according to Curve Shape Enum

Radius.name: Radius
Radius.Definition: The radius of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcKerbType.Definition: The Ifc Kerb Type provides the type information for the Ifc Kerb element.
IfcKerbType.Name: Kerb Type

IfcRoad.Definition: A route built on land to allow travel from one location to another, including highways, streets, cycle and foot paths, but excluding railways. As a type of Facility, Road provides the basic element in the project structure hierarchy for the components of a road project (i.e. any undertaking such as design, construction or maintenance).
IfcRoad.Name: Road

Crossfall.name: Crossfall
Crossfall.Definition: Specifies the nominal crossfall as a ratio measure (slope) at the location of the event.

DesignSpeed.name: Design Speed
DesignSpeed.Definition: Speed selected in designing a new road or in modernizing, strengthening or rehabilitating an existing road section, to determine the various geometric design features of the carriageway that allow a car to travel safely at that speed, under normal road surface and weather conditions.

DesignTrafficVolume.name: Design Traffic Volume
DesignTrafficVolume.Definition: The traffic volume used for planning and design purposes specified as the number of vehicles per day . Typically given as AADT - Average Annual Daily Traffic

DesignVehicleClass.name: Design Vehicle Class
DesignVehicleClass.Definition: A vehicle designator with content according to local standards.

LaneWidth.name: Lane Width
