VerticalBarPitch.name: Vertical Bar Pitch
VerticalBarPitch.Definition: The pitch length of the vertical bar.

IfcWallStandardCase.Definition: The Ifc Wall Standard Case defines a wall with certain constraints for the provision of parameters and with certain constraints for the geometric representation. The Ifc Wall Standard Case handles all cases of walls, that are extruded verticallyalong the positive z axis of the wall object coordinate system, and
IfcWallStandardCase.Name: Wall Standard Case

IfcWallType.Definition: The element type Ifc Wall Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of walls. The set of shared information may includecommon properties within shared property sets
IfcWallType.Name: Wall Type

IfcWindow.Definition: The window is a building element that is predominately used to provide natural light and fresh air. It includes vertical opening but also horizontal opening such as skylights or light domes. It includes constructions with swinging, pivoting, sliding, or revolving panels and fixed panels. A window consists of a lining and one or several panels. A window canbe a free standing window, contained in an Ifc Spatial Element such as an Ifc Building Storey.
IfcWindow.Name: Window

FrameDepth.name: Frame Depth
FrameDepth.Definition: The length (or depth) of the frame.

OperationType.name: Operation Type
OperationType.Definition: Type of operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

FirstMullionOffset.name: First Mullion Offset
FirstMullionOffset.Definition: Offset of the mullion centerline, measured along the x-axis of the window placement coordinate system. An offset value 0.5 indicates that the mullion is positioned in the middle of the window.

FirstTransomOffset.name: First Transom Offset
FirstTransomOffset.Definition: Offset of the transom centerline, measured along the z-axis of the window placement coordinate system. An offset value 0.5 indicates that the transom is positioned in the middle of the window.

LiningToPanelOffsetX.name: Lining to Panel Offset X
LiningToPanelOffsetX.Definition: Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the x-axis of the local placement.

LiningToPanelOffsetY.name: Lining to Panel Offset Y
LiningToPanelOffsetY.Definition: Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the y-axis of the local placement.

SecondMullionOffset.name: Second Mullion Offset
SecondMullionOffset.Definition: Offset of the mullion centerline for the second mullion, measured along the x-axis of the window placement co-ordinate system. An offset value 0.666 indicates that the second mullion is positioned at twothird of the window.

SecondTransomOffset.name: Second Transom Offset
SecondTransomOffset.Definition: Offset of the transom centerline for the second transom, measured along the x-axis of the window placement co-ordinate system. An offset value 0.666 indicates that the second transom is positioned at twothird of the window.

FrameDepth.name: Frame Depth
FrameDepth.Definition: The length (or depth) of the frame.

OperationType.name: Operation Type
OperationType.Definition: Type of operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

FillGas.name: Fill Gas
FillGas.Definition: Name of the gas by which the gap between two glass layers is filled. It is given for information purposes only.

GlassColour.name: Glass Colour
GlassColour.Definition: Colour (tint) selection for this glazing. It is given for information purposes only.

GlassLayers.name: Glass Layers
GlassLayers.Definition: Number of glass layers within the frame. E.g. 2 for double glazing.

GlassThickness1.name: Glass Thickness1
GlassThickness1.Definition: Thickness of the first (inner) glass layer.

GlassThickness2.name: Glass Thickness2
GlassThickness2.Definition: Thickness of the second (intermediate or outer) glass layer.

GlassThickness3.name: Glass Thickness3
GlassThickness3.Definition: Thickness of the third (outer) glass layer.

IsCoated.name: Is Coated
IsCoated.Definition: Indication whether the glass is coated with a material (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

IsLaminated.name: Is Laminated
IsLaminated.Definition: Indication whether the glass is layered with other materials (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

IsTempered.name: Is Tempered
IsTempered.Definition: Indication whether the glass is tempered (TRUE) or not (FALSE) .

IsWired.name: Is Wired
IsWired.Definition: Indication whether the glass includes a contained wire mesh to prevent break-in (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

ShadingCoefficient.name: Shading Coefficient
ShadingCoefficient.Definition: (SC) The measure of the ability of a glazing to transmit solar heat, relative to that ability for 3 mm (18-inch) clear, double-strength, single glass. Shading coefficient is being phased out in favor of the solar heat gain coefficient (SHGC), and is approximately equal to the SHGC multiplied by 1.15. The shading coefficient is expressed as a number without units between 0 and 1.

SolarAbsorption.name: Solar Absorption
SolarAbsorption.Definition: (Asol) The ratio of incident solar radiation that is absorbed by a glazing system. It is the sum of the absorption distributed to the exterior (a) and to the interior (qi). Note the following equation Asol Rsol Tsol 1

SolarHeatGainTransmittance.name: Solar Heat Gain Transmittance
SolarHeatGainTransmittance.Definition: (SHGC) The ratio of incident solar radiation that contributes to the heat gain of the interior, it is the solar radiation that directly passes (Tsol or τe) plus the part of the absorbed radiation that is distributed to the interior (qi). The SHGC is referred to also as g-value (g τe qi).

SolarReflectance.name: Solar Reflectance
SolarReflectance.Definition: (Rsol) The ratio of incident solar radiation that is reflected by a glazing system (also named ρe). Note the following equation Asol Rsol Tsol 1

SolarTransmittance.name: Solar Transmittance
SolarTransmittance.Definition: The ratio of incident solar radiation that directly passes through a system (also named τe). Note the following equation Asol Rsol Tsol 1

ThermalTransmittanceSummer.name: Thermal Transmittance Summer
ThermalTransmittanceSummer.Definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of a material.

ThermalTransmittanceWinter.name: Thermal Transmittance Winter
ThermalTransmittanceWinter.Definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of a material.

VisibleLightReflectance.name: Visible Light Reflectance
VisibleLightReflectance.Definition: Fraction of the visible light that is reflected by the glazing at normal incidence. It is a value without unit.

VisibleLightTransmittance.name: Visible Light Transmittance
VisibleLightTransmittance.Definition: Fraction of the visible light that passes the object at normal incidence. It is a value without unit.

FireExit.name: Fire Exit
FireExit.Definition: Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

FireRating.name: Fire Rating
FireRating.Definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

GlazingAreaFraction.name: Glazing Area Fraction
GlazingAreaFraction.Definition: Fraction of the glazing area relative to the total area of the filling element.

HasDrive.name: Has Drive
HasDrive.Definition: Indication whether this object has an automatic drive to operate it (TRUE) or no drive (FALSE)

HasSillExternal.name: Has Sill External
HasSillExternal.Definition: Indication whether the window opening has an external sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

HasSillInternal.name: Has Sill Internal
HasSillInternal.Definition: Indication whether the window opening has an internal sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Infiltration.name: Infiltration
Infiltration.Definition: Infiltration flowrate of outside air for the filler object based on the area of the filler object at a pressure level of 50 Pascals. It shall be used, if the length of all joints is unknown.

IsExternal.name: Is External
IsExternal.Definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

MechanicalLoadRating.name: Mechanical Load Rating
MechanicalLoadRating.Definition: Mechanical load rating for this object.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

SecurityRating.name: Security Rating
SecurityRating.Definition: Index based rating system indicating security level.

SmokeStop.name: Smoke Stop
SmokeStop.Definition: Indication whether the object is designed to provide a smoke stop (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

ThermalTransmittance.name: Thermal Transmittance
ThermalTransmittance.Definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

WaterTightnessRating.name: Water Tightness Rating
WaterTightnessRating.Definition: Water tightness rating for this object.

WindLoadRating.name: Wind Load Rating
WindLoadRating.Definition: Wind load resistance rating for this object.

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

OverallHeight.name: Overall Height
OverallHeight.Definition: Overall measure of the height, it reflects the Z Dimension of a bounding box, enclosing the window opening. If omitted, the Overall Height should be taken from the geometric representation of the Ifc Opening Element in which the window is inserted.

OverallWidth.name: Overall Width
OverallWidth.Definition: Overall measure of the width, it reflects the X Dimension of a bounding box, enclosing the window opening. If omitted, the Overall Width should be taken from the geometric representation of the Ifc Opening Element in which the window is inserted.

PartitioningType.Definition: Type defining the general layout of the window type in terms of the partitioning of panels.

UserDefinedPartitioningType.name: User Defined Partitioning Type
UserDefinedPartitioningType.Definition: Designator for the user defined partitioning type, shall only be provided, if the value of Partitioning Type is set to USERDEFINED.

ParameterTakesPrecedence.name: Parameter Takes Precedence
ParameterTakesPrecedence.Definition: The Boolean value reflects, whether the parameter given in the attached lining and panel properties exactly define the geometry (TRUE), or whether the attached style shape take precedence (FALSE). In the last case the parameter have only informative value. If not provided, no such information can be inferred.

IfcWindowType.Definition: The element type Ifc Window Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of windows. The set of shared information may includecommon properties within shared property sets
IfcWindowType.Name: Qtowindow Base Quantities

IfcDistributionChamberElement.Definition: A distribution chamber element defines a place at which distribution systems and their constituent elements may be inspected or through which they may travel.An Ifc Distribution Chamber Element is a formed volume used in a distribution system, such as a sump, trench or manhole. Instances of Ifc Distribution System or Ifc Distribution Flow Element may be related to the Ifc Distribution Chamber Element enabling their location in or at the chamber to be determined.
IfcDistributionChamberElement.Name: Distribution Chamber Element

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

GrossSurfaceArea.name: Gross Surface Area
GrossSurfaceArea.Definition: Total gross area of the object, normally generated as perimeter length 2 cross section area. It is the sum of Outer Surface Area (2 x Cross Section Area) and shall only be given, if the Outer Surface Area and Cross Section Area cannot be established separately.

GrossVolume.name: Gross Volume
GrossVolume.Definition: Total gross volume of the object. Openings, recesses, enclosed objects and projections are not taken into account.

NetSurfaceArea.name: Net Surface Area
NetSurfaceArea.Definition: Net surface area of the object, normally generated as perimeter length 2 cross section area taking into account possible processing features (cut-outs, etc.) or openings and recesses.

NetVolume.name: Net Volume
NetVolume.Definition: Total net volume of the object, taking into account possible processing features (cut-outs, etc.) or openings and recesses.

IfcDistributionChamberElementType.Definition: The distribution flow element type Ifc Distribution Chamber Element Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of distribution chamber elements. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcDistributionChamberElementType.Name: Distribution Chamber Element Type

IfcDistributionCircuit.Definition: A distribution circuit is a partition of a distribution system that is conditionally switched such as an electrical circuit.
IfcDistributionCircuit.Name: Distribution Circuit

IfcDistributionControlElement.Definition: The distribution element Ifc Distribution Control Element defines occurrence elements of a building automation control system that are used to impart control over elements of a distribution system.Ifc Distribution Control Element defines elements of a building automation control system. These are typically used to control distribution system elements to maintain variables such as temperature, humidity, pressure, flow, power, or lighting levels, through the modulation, staging or sequencing of mechanical or electrical devices. The three general functional categories of control elements are as followsImpart control over flow control elements (Ifc Flow Controller) in a distribution system such as dampers, valves, or relays, typically through the use of actuation (Ifc Actuator).
IfcDistributionControlElement.Name: Distribution Control Element

IfcDistributionControlElementType.Definition: The element type Ifc Distribution Control Element Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of an element and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define an element specification (the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type).Distribution control element types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Distribution Control Element Type are represented by instances of Ifc Distribution Control Element or its subtypes.
IfcDistributionControlElementType.Name: Distribution Control Element Type

IfcDistributionFlowElement.Definition: The distribution element Ifc Distribution Flow Element defines occurrence elements of a distribution system that facilitate the distribution of energy or matter, such as air, water or power.
IfcDistributionFlowElement.Name: Distribution Flow Element

SoundCurve.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
SoundCurve.name: Sound Curve

IfcDistributionFlowElementType.Definition: The element type Ifc Distribution Flow Element Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of an element and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define an element specification (the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type).Distribution flow element types (orthe instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Distribution Flow Element Type are represented by instances of Ifc Distribution Flow Element or its subtypes.
IfcDistributionFlowElementType.Name: Distribution Flow Element Type

IfcDistributionPort.Definition: A distribution port is an inlet or outlet of a product through which a particular substance may flow.Distribution ports are used for passage of solid, liquid, or gas substances, as well as electricity for power or communications. Flow segments (pipes, ducts, cables) may be used to connect ports across products. Distribution ports are defined by system type and flow direction such that for two ports to be connected, they must share the same system type and have opposite flow directions (one side being a SOURCE and the other being a SINK). Ports are similar to openings in that they do not have any visible geometry such geometry is captured at the shape representation of the enclosing element or element type. Ports may have placement that indicates the position and orientation of the connection.Ports are assigned the distribution systems in order to indicate its role in a particular system, e.g. cold water inlet.
IfcDistributionPort.Name: Distribution Port

ColourCode.name: Colour Code
ColourCode.Definition: Name of a colour for identifying the connector, if applicable.

PortNumber.name: Port Number
PortNumber.Definition: The port index for logically ordering the port within the containing element or element type.

FlowDirection.Definition: Enumeration that identifies if this port is a Sink (inlet), a Source (outlet) or both a Sink And Source.

SystemType.Definition: Enumeration that identifies the system type. If a system type is defined, the port may only be connected to other ports having the same system type.

IfcDistributionSystem.Definition: A distribution system is a network designed to receive, store, maintain, distribute, or control the flow of a distribution media. A common example is a heating hot water system that consists of a pump, a tank, and an interconnected piping system for distributing hot water to terminals.The group Ifc Distribution System defines the occurrence of a specialized system for use within the context of building services or utilities for built facilities.Important functionalities for the description of a distribution system are derived from existing IFC entitiesFrom Ifc System it inherits the ability to couple the built system via Ifc Rel Referenced In Spatial Structure to one or more Ifc Spatial Element subtypes as necessary.
IfcDistributionSystem.Name: Distribution System

DownstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DownstreamConnections.name: Downstream Connections
DownstreamConnections.Definition: Names of downstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

ProcessCapacity.name: Process Capacity
ProcessCapacity.Definition: The number of units that can be processed in the time defined in Process Performance

ProcessItem.name: Process Item
ProcessItem.Definition: The type of item (and its measurement method) being modelled within a process. This can be cargo, passengers or vehicles that pass through the system.

ProcessPerformance.name: Process Performance
ProcessPerformance.Definition: Minimum time to accept or dispatch the entire item capacity.

UpstreamConnections.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
UpstreamConnections.name: Upstream Connections
UpstreamConnections.Definition: Names of upstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

LongName.name: Long Name
LongName.Definition: Long name for a distribution system, used for informal purposes. It should be used, if available, in conjunction with the inherited Name attribute.

IfcEnergyConversionDevice.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Energy Conversion Device defines the occurrence of a device used to perform energy conversion or heat transfer and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by Ifc Energy Conversion Device Type or its subtypes.
IfcEnergyConversionDevice.Name: Energy Conversion Device

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcEnergyConversionDeviceType.Definition: The element type Ifc Energy Conversion Device Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of an energy conversion device and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define an energy conversion device specification (the specific product information, that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A energy conversion type is used to define the common properties of a energy conversion device that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. An energy conversion device is a building systems device that converts energy from one form into another such as a boiler (combusting gas to heat water), chiller (using a refrigeration cycle to cool a liquid), or a cooling coil (using the phase-change characteristics of a refrigerant to cool air). Energy conversion types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.Occurrences of the Ifc Energy Conversion Device Type are represented by instances of Ifc Energy Conversion Device or its subtypes.
IfcEnergyConversionDeviceType.Name: Energy Conversion Device Type

IfcFlowController.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Controller defines the occurrence of elements of a distribution system that are used to regulate flow through a distribution system. Examples include dampers, valves, switches, and relays. Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Controller Type or subtypes.
IfcFlowController.Name: Flow Controller

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcFlowControllerType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Controller Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow controller and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow controller specification (i.e. the specific product information, that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow controller type is used to define the common properties of a flow controller that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. A flow controller is a device that regulates flow within a distribution system, such as a valve in a piping system, modulating damper in an air distribution system, or electrical switch in an electrical distribution system. Flow controller types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.Occurrences of the Ifc Flow Controller Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Controller or its subtypes.
IfcFlowControllerType.Name: Flow Controller Type

IfcFlowFitting.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Fitting defines the occurrence of a junction or transition in a flow distribution system, such as an elbow or tee. Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Fitting Type or its subtypes.
IfcFlowFitting.Name: Flow Fitting

IfcFlowFittingType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Fitting Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow fitting and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow fitting specification (i.e. the specific product information, that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow fitting type is used to define the common properties of a flow fitting that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. A flow fitting is a device that is used to interconnect flow segments or other fittings within a distribution system, such as a tee in a ducted system that branches flow into two directions, or a junction box in an electrical distribution system. Flow fitting types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.Occurrences of the Ifc Flow Fitting Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Fitting or its subtypes.
IfcFlowFittingType.Name: Flow Fitting Type

IfcFlowMovingDevice.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Moving Device defines the occurrence of an apparatus used to distribute, circulate or perform conveyance of fluids, including liquids and gases (such as a pump or fan), and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Moving Device Type or its subtypes.
IfcFlowMovingDevice.Name: Flow Moving Device

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcFlowMovingDeviceType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Moving Device Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow moving device and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow moving device specification (i.e. the specific product information, that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow moving type is used to define the common properties of a flow moving device that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. A flow moving device is a device that is used to produce a pressure differential in a distribution system, such as a pump, fan, or compressor. Flow moving types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Flow Moving Device Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Moving Device or its subtypes.
IfcFlowMovingDeviceType.Name: Flow Moving Device Type

IfcFlowSegment.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Segment defines the occurrence of a segment of a flow distribution system.The Ifc Flow Segment defines a particular occurrence of a segment inserted in the spatial context of a project. The parameters defining the type of the segment andor its shape are defined by the Ifc Flow Segment Type, which is related by the inverse relationship Is Defined By pointing to Ifc Rel Defines By Type.
IfcFlowSegment.Name: Flow Segment

IfcFlowSegmentType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Segment Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow segment and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow segment specification (the specific product information, that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow segment type is used to define the common properties of a flow segment that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. A flow segment is a section of a distribution system, such as a duct, pipe, or conduit, that typically has only two ports. Flow segment types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.Occurrences of the Ifc Flow Segment Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Segment or its subtypes.
IfcFlowSegmentType.Name: Flow Segment Type

IfcFlowStorageDevice.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Storage Device defines the occurrence of a device that participates in a distribution system and is used for temporary storage (such as a tank). Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Storage Device Type or its subtypes.
IfcFlowStorageDevice.Name: Flow Storage Device

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcFlowStorageDeviceType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Storage Device Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow storage device and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow storage device specification (the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow storage device is a device used for the temporary storage of a fluid (such as a tank) or the voltage potential induced by the induced electron flow (such as a battery). Flow storage types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Flow Storage Device Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Storage Device or its subtypes.
IfcFlowStorageDeviceType.Name: Flow Storage Device Type

IfcFlowTerminal.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Terminal defines the occurrence of a permanently attached element that acts as a terminus or beginning of a distribution system (such as an air outlet, drain, water closet, or sink). A terminal is typically a point at which a system interfaces with an external environment. Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Terminal Type or its subtypes.
IfcFlowTerminal.Name: Flow Terminal

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcFlowTerminalType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Terminal Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow terminal and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow terminal specification (the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow terminal type is used to define the common properties of a flow terminal that may be applied to many occurrences of that type. A flow terminal acts as a terminus or beginning element in a distribution system such as a ceiling register in a ducted air distribution system, a sink in a waste-water system, or a light fixture in an electrical lighting system. Flow terminal types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Flow Terminal Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Terminal or its subtypes.
IfcFlowTerminalType.Name: Flow Terminal Type

IfcFlowTreatmentDevice.Definition: The distribution flow element Ifc Flow Treatment Device defines the occurrence of a device typically used to remove unwanted matter from a fluid, either liquid or gas, and typically participates in a flow distribution system. Its type is defined by Ifc Flow Treatment Device Type or its subtypes.
IfcFlowTreatmentDevice.Name: Flow Treatment Device

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcFlowTreatmentDeviceType.Definition: The element type Ifc Flow Treatment Device Type defines a list of commonly shared property set definitions of a flow treatment device and an optional set of product representations. It is used to define a flow treatment device specification (the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type).A flow treatment device is a device used to change the physical properties of the medium, such as an air, oil or water filter (used to remove particulates from the fluid), or a duct silencer (used to attenuate noise). Flow treatment types (or the instantiable subtypes) may be exchanged without being already assigned to occurrences.The occurrences of the Ifc Flow Treatment Device Type are represented by instances of Ifc Flow Treatment Device or its subtypes.
IfcFlowTreatmentDeviceType.Name: Flow Treatment Device Type

IfcRelFlowControlElements.Definition: This objectified relationship between a distribution flow element occurrence and one-to-many control element occurrences indicates that the control element(s) sense or control some aspect of the flow element. It is applied to Ifc Distribution Flow Element and Ifc Distribution Control Element.This relationship may be used to indicate an operational relationship such as an actuator operating a valve, damper, or switch. It may also be used to indicate a sensing relationship such as a sensor detecting conditions of fluid flow.This relationship implies a sensing or controlling relationship if elements are merely connected without any control relationship, then Ifc Rel Connects Elements should be used.
IfcRelFlowControlElements.Name: Qtodistribution Chamber Element Base Quantities

IfcBuildingElementPart.Definition: Ifc Building Element Part represents major components as subordinate parts of a building element. Typical usage examples include precast concrete sandwich walls, where the layers may have different geometry representations. In this case the layered material representation does not sufficiently describe the element. Each layer is represented by an own instance of the Ifc Building Element Part with its own geometry description.The kind of building element part is further specified by a corresponding instance of Ifc Building Element Part Type, referred to by Ifc Rel Defines By Type.
IfcBuildingElementPart.Name: Building Element Part

IfcBuildingElementPartType.Definition: The building element part type defines lists of commonly shared property set definitions and representation maps of parts of a building element.
IfcBuildingElementPartType.Name: Building Element Part Type

IfcDiscreteAccessory.Definition: A discrete accessory is a representation of different kinds of accessories included in or added to elements.
IfcDiscreteAccessory.Name: Discrete Accessory

CornerFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneX.name: Corner Fixing Plate Flange Width In Plane X
CornerFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneX.Definition: The flange width of the L-shaped corner plate in plane X.

CornerFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneZ.name: Corner Fixing Plate Flange Width In Plane Z
CornerFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneZ.Definition: The flange width of the L-shaped corner plate in plane Z.

CornerFixingPlateLength.name: Corner Fixing Plate Length
CornerFixingPlateLength.Definition: The length of the L-shaped corner plate.

CornerFixingPlateThickness.name: Corner Fixing Plate Thickness
CornerFixingPlateThickness.Definition: The thickness of the L-shaped corner plate.

DiagonalTrussBaseBarDiameter.name: Diagonal Truss Base Bar Diameter
DiagonalTrussBaseBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the base bar.

DiagonalTrussCrossBarDiameter.name: Diagonal Truss Cross Bar Diameter
DiagonalTrussCrossBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the diagonal cross-bars.

DiagonalTrussCrossBarSpacing.name: Diagonal Truss Cross Bar Spacing
DiagonalTrussCrossBarSpacing.Definition: The spacing between diagonal cross-bar sections.

DiagonalTrussHeight.name: Diagonal Truss Height
DiagonalTrussHeight.Definition: The overall height of the truss connector.

DiagonalTrussLength.name: Diagonal Truss Length
DiagonalTrussLength.Definition: The overall length of the truss connector.

DiagonalTrussSecondaryBarDiameter.name: Diagonal Truss Secondary Bar Diameter
DiagonalTrussSecondaryBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the secondary bar.

EdgeFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneX.name: Edge Fixing Plate Flange Width In Plane X
EdgeFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneX.Definition: The flange width of the L-shaped edge plate in plane X.

EdgeFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneZ.name: Edge Fixing Plate Flange Width In Plane Z
EdgeFixingPlateFlangeWidthInPlaneZ.Definition: The flange width of the L-shaped edge plate in plane Z.

EdgeFixingPlateLength.name: Edge Fixing Plate Length
EdgeFixingPlateLength.Definition: The length of the L-shaped edge plate.

EdgeFixingPlateThickness.name: Edge Fixing Plate Thickness
EdgeFixingPlateThickness.Definition: The thickness of the L-shaped edge plate.

FixingSocketHeight.name: Fixing Socket Height
FixingSocketHeight.Definition: The overall height of the fixing socket.

FixingSocketThreadDiameter.name: Fixing Socket Thread Diameter
FixingSocketThreadDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the thread.

FixingSocketThreadLength.name: Fixing Socket Thread Length
FixingSocketThreadLength.Definition: The length of the threaded part of the fixing socket.

FixingSocketTypeReference.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
FixingSocketTypeReference.name: Fixing Socket Type Reference
FixingSocketTypeReference.Definition: Type reference for the fixing socket according to local standards.

LadderTrussBaseBarDiameter.name: Ladder Truss Base Bar Diameter
LadderTrussBaseBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the base bar.

LadderTrussCrossBarDiameter.name: Ladder Truss Cross Bar Diameter
LadderTrussCrossBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the straight cross-bars.

LadderTrussCrossBarSpacing.name: Ladder Truss Cross Bar Spacing
LadderTrussCrossBarSpacing.Definition: The spacing between the straight cross-bars.

LadderTrussHeight.name: Ladder Truss Height
LadderTrussHeight.Definition: The overall height of the truss connector.

LadderTrussLength.name: Ladder Truss Length
LadderTrussLength.Definition: The overall length of the truss connector.

LadderTrussSecondaryBarDiameter.name: Ladder Truss Secondary Bar Diameter
LadderTrussSecondaryBarDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the secondary bar.

StandardFixingPlateDepth.name: Standard Fixing Plate Depth
StandardFixingPlateDepth.Definition: The depth of the standard fixing plate.

StandardFixingPlateThickness.name: Standard Fixing Plate Thickness
StandardFixingPlateThickness.Definition: The thickness of the standard fixing plate.

StandardFixingPlateWidth.name: Standard Fixing Plate Width
StandardFixingPlateWidth.Definition: The width of the standard fixing plate.

WireDiameter.name: Wire Diameter
WireDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter of the wire.

WireEmbeddingLength.name: Wire Embedding Length
WireEmbeddingLength.Definition: The length of the part of wire which is embedded in the precast concrete element.

WireLoopBasePlateLength.name: Wire Loop Base Plate Length
WireLoopBasePlateLength.Definition: The length of the base plate.

WireLoopBasePlateThickness.name: Wire Loop Base Plate Thickness
WireLoopBasePlateThickness.Definition: The thickness of the base plate.

WireLoopBasePlateWidth.name: Wire Loop Base Plate Width
WireLoopBasePlateWidth.Definition: The width of the base plate.

WireLoopLength.name: Wire Loop Length
WireLoopLength.Definition: The length of the fastening loop part of the wire.

IfcDiscreteAccessoryType.Definition: The element component type Ifc Discrete Accessory Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of discrete accessories. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcDiscreteAccessoryType.Name: Discrete Accessory Type

IfcElementComponent.Definition: An element component is a representation for minor items included in, added to or connecting to or between elements, which usually are not of interest from the overall building structure viewpoint. However, these small parts may have vital and load carrying functions within the construction. These items do not provide any actual space boundaries. Typical examples of Ifc Element Components include different kinds of fasteners and various accessories.One or several instances of subtypes of Ifc Element Component should always be accompanied by a defining instance of a respective subtype of Ifc Element Component Type. The type object holds shape and material information.
IfcElementComponent.Name: Element Component

CorrosionTreatment.name: Corrosion Treatment
CorrosionTreatment.Definition: Determines corrosion treatment for metal components. This property is provided if the requirement needs to be expressed (a) independently of a material specification and (b) as a mere requirements statement rather than a workshop design processing feature.

DeliveryType.name: Delivery Type
DeliveryType.Definition: Determines how the accessory will be delivered to the site.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

IfcElementComponentType.Definition: The element type Ifc Element Component Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of element components. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcElementComponentType.Name: Element Component Type

IfcFastener.Definition: Representations of fixing parts which are used as fasteners to connect or join elements with other elements. Excluded are mechanical fasteners which are modeled by a separate entity (Ifc Mechanical Fastener).
IfcFastener.Name: Fastener

IfcFastenerType.Definition: The element component type Ifc Fastener Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of fasteners. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcFastenerType.Name: Fastener Type

IfcMechanicalFastener.Definition: A mechanical fasteners connecting building elements or parts mechanically. A single instance of this class may represent one or many of actual mechanical fasteners, for example an array of bolts or a row of nails.
IfcMechanicalFastener.Name: Mechanical Fastener

NominalDiameter.name: Nominal Diameter
NominalDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter describing the cross-section size of the fastener type.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal length describing the longitudinal dimensions of the fastener type.

IfcMechanicalFastenerType.Definition: The element component type Ifc Mechanical Fastener Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of mechanical fasteners. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcMechanicalFastenerType.Name: Mechanical Fastener Bolt

IfcAsset.Definition: An asset is a uniquely identifiable grouping of elements acting as a single entity that has a financial value or that can be operated on as a single unit.An asset is generally the level of granularity at which maintenance operations are undertaken. An asset is a group that can contain one or more elements. Whilst the financial value of a component or element can be defined, financial value is also defined for accounting purposes at the level of the asset.There are a number of actors that can be associated with an asset, each actor having a role. Actors within the scope of the project are indicated using the Ifc Rel Assigns To Actor relationship in which case roles should be defined through the Ifc Actor Role class otherwise principal actors are identified as attributes of the class. In the existence of both, direct attributes take precedence.There are a number of costs that can be associated with an asset, each cost having a role. These are specified through the Original Value, Current Value, Total Replacement Cost and Depreciated Value attributes.
IfcAsset.Name: Asset

AcceptanceDate.name: Acceptance Date
AcceptanceDate.Definition: Date on which the element is accepted by the manager or administrator.

InstallationDate.name: Installation Date
InstallationDate.Definition: Date on which the element is installed.

PutIntoOperationDate.name: Put Into Operation Date
PutIntoOperationDate.Definition: Date on which the element is put into operation.

RepairContent.name: Repair Content
RepairContent.Definition: Content of repair, reason and nature can be given, e.g. display faults, communication failure, display exchange.

RepairDate.name: Repair Date
RepairDate.Definition: Date on which the last repair is done on the asset.

AssetAccountingType.name: Asset Accounting Type
AssetAccountingType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of risk from which the type required may be set.

AssetInsuranceType.name: Asset Insurance Type
AssetInsuranceType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of insurance rating from which the type required may be set.

AssetStatus.name: Asset Status
AssetStatus.Definition: Current status or stage in life cycle.

AssetTaxType.name: Asset Tax Type
AssetTaxType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of taxation group from which the type required may be set.

AssetUse.name: Asset Use
AssetUse.Definition: General use category of the asset

AssessmentCondition.name: Assessment Condition
AssessmentCondition.Definition: The overall condition of a product based on an assessment of the contributions to the overall condition made by the various criteria considered. The meanings given to the values of assessed condition should be agreed and documented by local agreements. For instance, is overall condition measured on a scale of 1 - 10 or by assigning names such as Good, OK, Poor.

AssessmentDate.name: Assessment Date
AssessmentDate.Definition: Date on which the overall condition is assessed

AssessmentFrequency.name: Assessment Frequency
AssessmentFrequency.Definition: Indicates how often the equipment should be assessed, to have a clear estimation on its working state, based on which the maintenance staff can decide whether it requires maintenance or requires to be updated or replaced.

AssessmentMethod.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssessmentMethod.name: Assessment Method
AssessmentMethod.Definition: External reference to assessment method or application used to perform the assessment.

AssessmentType.name: Assessment Type
AssessmentType.Definition: Category of latest condition assessment report of the asset.

LastAssessmentReport.name: Last Assessment Report
LastAssessmentReport.Definition: Reference to latest condition (state of health) report.

AccidentResponse.name: Accident Response
AccidentResponse.Definition: Accident response chosen for the asset

AssetCriticality.name: Asset Criticality
AssetCriticality.Definition: Rating of the assets criticality to the operation of the facility

AssetFrailty.name: Asset Frailty
AssetFrailty.Definition: Rating of the assets frailty to breakage or deterioration

AssetPriority.name: Asset Priority
AssetPriority.Definition: Combined criticality and frailty rating indicating the operational and maintenance priority of the asset

MonitoringType.name: Monitoring Type
MonitoringType.Definition: Monitoring strategy chosen for the asset

ConditionDisposalLevel.name: Condition Disposal Level
ConditionDisposalLevel.Definition: Condition that will trigger a disposal process

ConditionReplacementLevel.name: Condition Replacement Level
ConditionReplacementLevel.Definition: Condition that will trigger a replacement process

DurationDisposalLevel.name: Duration Disposal Level
DurationDisposalLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which disposal is performed

DurationMaintenanceLevel.name: Duration Maintenance Level
DurationMaintenanceLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which maintenance is performed

DurationReplacementLevel.name: Duration Replacement Level
DurationReplacementLevel.Definition: Duration interval at which replacement is performed

DurationTargetPerformance.name: Duration Target Performance
DurationTargetPerformance.Definition: Target time to failure of the asset

DisposalLevel.name: Disposal Level
DisposalLevel.Definition: Performance level at which disposal takes place

PerformanceMaintenanceLevel.name: Performance Maintenance Level
PerformanceMaintenanceLevel.Definition: Performance level at which maintenance takes place

ReplacementLevel.name: Replacement Level
ReplacementLevel.Definition: Performance level at which replacement takes place

TargetPerformance.name: Target Performance
TargetPerformance.Definition: Target capacity or performance of the asset. Units of the performance value are specified through the property Value units attribute.

Identification.name: Identification
Identification.Definition: A unique identification assigned to an asset that enables its differentiation from other assets.

IncorporationDate.name: Incorporation Date
IncorporationDate.Definition: The date on which an asset was incorporated into the works, installed, constructed, erected or completed.

IfcFurniture.Definition: Furniture defines complete furnishings such as a table, desk, chair, or cabinet, which may or may not be permanently attached to a building structure.Occurrences of furniture that are built in (where the property PsetFurniture Type Common.Is Built In is asserted to be TRUE) should have their connection relationship with a building element occurrence defined through the Ifc Rel Connects Elements relationship.
IfcFurniture.Name: Furniture

IsBuiltIn.name: Is Built In
IsBuiltIn.Definition: Indicates whether the furniture type is intended to be built in i.e. physically attached to a building or facility ( TRUE) or not i.e. Loose and movable ( FALSE).

MainColour.name: Main Colour
MainColour.Definition: The main colour of the furniture of this type.

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

AssemblyPlace.Definition: A designation of where the assembly is intended to take place. A selection of alternatives s provided in an enumerated list.

IfcFurnitureType.Definition: The furnishing element type Ifc Furniture Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of furnitures. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcFurnitureType.Name: Furniture Type

IfcInventory.Definition: An inventory is a list of items within an enterprise.Various types of inventory can be included. These are identified by the range of values within the inventory type enumeration which includes space, asset, and furniture. User defined inventories can also be defined for lists of particular types of element such as may be required in operating and maintenance instructions. Such inventories should be constrained to contain a list of elements of a restricted type.There are a number of actors that can be associated with an inventory, each actor having a role. Actors within the scope of the project are indicated using the Ifc Rel Assigns To Actor relationship in which case roles should be defined through the Ifc Actor Role class otherwise principal actors are identified as attributes of the class. In the existence of both, direct attributes take precedence.There are a number of costs that can be associated with an inventory, each cost having a role. These are specified through the Current Value and Original Value attributes.
IfcInventory.Name: Inventory

LastUpdateDate.name: Last Update Date
LastUpdateDate.Definition: The date on which the last update of the inventory was carried out. IFC4 CHANGE Type changed from Ifc Date Time Select.

IfcOccupant.Definition: An occupant is a type of actor that defines the form of occupancy of a property.The principal purpose of Ifc Occupant is to determine the nature of occupancy of a property for a particular actor. All characteristics relating to the actor (name and organization details) are inherited from the Ifc Actor entity.
IfcOccupant.Name: Occupant

IfcSystemFurnitureElement.Definition: A system furniture element defines components of modular furniture which are not directly placed in a building structure but aggregated inside furniture.
IfcSystemFurnitureElement.Name: System Furniture Element

Finishing.name: Finishing
Finishing.Definition: The finishing applied to system furniture elements of this type e.g. walnut, fabric.

IsUsed.name: Is Used
IsUsed.Definition: Indicates whether the element is being used in a workstation ( TRUE) or not.( FALSE).

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcSystemFurnitureElementType.Definition: The furnishing element type Ifc System Furniture Element Type defines commonly shared information for occurrences of system furniture elements. The set of shared information may includecommon properties with shared property sets
IfcSystemFurnitureElementType.Name: Warranty

IfcBorehole.Definition: Representation of the concept of a linear geological and geotechnical model, usually an interpretation but sometimes created direct from ground penetrating measurement
IfcBorehole.Name: Borehole

BoreholeState.name: Borehole State
BoreholeState.Definition: The state the borehole or trial pit has been left in. (borehole ML).

CapMaterial.name: Cap Material
CapMaterial.Definition: Cap material or NOT CAPPED or UNKNOWN (borehole ML).

FillingMaterial.name: Filling Material
FillingMaterial.Definition: Filling material or NOT FILLED or UNKNOWN (borehole ML).

LiningMaterial.name: Lining Material
LiningMaterial.Definition: Lining material or NOT LINED or UNKNOWN (borehole ML).

IfcCourse.Definition: A built element whose length greatly exceeds its thickness and often also its width, usually of a single material laid on site on top of another horizontal or nearly horizontal built element. A course is distinctive from a earthworks element in that a course is a graded granular (which can be bound or unbound) material that is generally processed in some fashion, where as earthworks elements are soil earthen based structure that can be formed by removal and transport of general ground material.
IfcCourse.Name: Course

SpreadingRate.name: Spreading Rate
SpreadingRate.Definition: The nominal overall mass of material per area covered by the course.

ApplicationTemperature.name: Application Temperature
ApplicationTemperature.Definition: Indicates the ambient temperature at which the course is applied

WeatherConditions.name: Weather Conditions
WeatherConditions.Definition: Indicates the weather conditions during the application of the course

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalThickness.name: Nominal Thickness
NominalThickness.Definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

GrossVolume.name: Gross Volume
GrossVolume.Definition: Total gross volume of the object. Openings, recesses, enclosed objects and projections are not taken into account.

Thickness.name: Thickness
Thickness.Definition: The geometric thickness of the object.

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcCourseType.Definition: The Ifc Course Type provides the type information for Ifc Course occurrences.
IfcCourseType.Name: Course Type

IfcEarthworksCut.Definition: The resulting void from modification of existing terrain or road structure by excavation or by other means of removing material.
IfcEarthworksCut.Name: Earthworks Cut

LooseVolume.name: Loose Volume
LooseVolume.Definition: Volume of the earthworks when in a loose piled state

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcEarthworksElement.Definition: A type of built element created by earthwork activities to build subgrade, to raise the level of the ground in general or reinforce or stabilize soil by some mechanical or chemical method.
IfcEarthworksElement.Name: Earthworks Element

IfcEarthworksFill.Definition: A type of earthworks element created by earthwork activities to build subgrade or to raise the level of the ground in general.
IfcEarthworksFill.Name: Earthworks Fill

CompactedVolume.name: Compacted Volume
CompactedVolume.Definition: Volume of the earthworks when finished and compacted in place.

LooseVolume.name: Loose Volume
LooseVolume.Definition: Volume of the earthworks when in a loose piled state

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcGeomodel.Definition: Representation of the concept of a volumetric geological and geotechnical model, usually an interpretation but sometimes created direct from ground penetrating measurement.
IfcGeomodel.Name: Geomodel

IfcGeoslice.Definition: Representation of the concept of a sectional planar geological and geotechnical model, usually an interpretation but sometimes created direct from ground penetrating measurement. The assembly may contain one of more strata and anthropic elements. The contained subtypes of Ifc Geotechnical Stratum will have shape representations made from polygons reflecting the visible section or poly lines if a Yabuki top surface model is being used.
IfcGeoslice.Name: Geoslice

IfcGeotechnicalAssembly.Definition: Representation of the abstract concept of a geological and geotechnical model, usually an interpretation but sometimes created direct from ground penetrating measurement.
IfcGeotechnicalAssembly.Name: Geotechnical Assembly

BoreHolePurpose.name: Bore Hole Purpose
BoreHolePurpose.Definition: Purpose for which the borehole, section or volumetric model was created. (EU Inspire, borehole ML)

Methodology.name: Methodology
Methodology.Definition: Methodology used to prepare the contents of the geotechnical assembly.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

IfcGeotechnicalStratum.Definition: Representation of the concept of an identified discrete almost homogeneous geological feature with either an irregular solid or Yabuki top surface shape or a regular voxel cubic shape. A stratum is represented as a discrete entity, specialised (sub typed) from Ifc Element. A stratum may be broken down into smaller entities if properties vary across the stratum or alternatively properties may be described with bounded numeric ranges. A stratum may carry information about the physical form and its interpretation as a Geological Item (GML).
IfcGeotechnicalStratum.Name: Geotechnical Stratum

IsTopographic.name: Is Topographic
IsTopographic.Definition: Is the stratum ever topmost and so a visible topographic feature

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

PlanLength.name: Plan Length
PlanLength.Definition: Projected plan length of upper edge of slice.

Mass.name: Mass
Mass.Definition: Mass represented, if lower surface of stratum known.

PlanArea.name: Plan Area
PlanArea.Definition: Projected plan area of upper surface of model.

IfcPavement.Definition: Type of built element in a road or other paved area to provide an even surface sustaining loads from vehicles or pedestrians, usually comprising several courses.
IfcPavement.Name: Pavement

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalThickness.name: Nominal Thickness
NominalThickness.Definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalThicknessEnd.name: Nominal Thickness End
NominalThicknessEnd.Definition: The nominal thickness of the object after a transition from its original value. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.Definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type A-1), Also referred to as construction type. It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the object type, if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Status.name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as New - element designed as new addition, Existing - element exists and remains, Demolish - element existed but is to be demolished, Temporary - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

StructuralSlope.name: Structural Slope
StructuralSlope.Definition: The nominal side slope (allowable steepness) of the pavement structure (not including side slope fill) as a positive ratio measure. The slope information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters take precedence. Value is typically less than 1.0 (11) but may be greater than that for steeper slopes.

StructuralSlopeType.name: Structural Slope Type
StructuralSlopeType.Definition: User defined description on the type of slope used for the pavement structure (not including side slope fill) . Examples are Even or Stepped.

PavementRoughness.name: Pavement Roughness
PavementRoughness.Definition: An assessment of the functional condition of the pavement surface indicated as an index according to the International Roughness Index (IRI).

PavementTexture.name: Pavement Texture
PavementTexture.Definition: Characterization of pavement texture by mean profile depth

Permeability.name: Permeability
Permeability.Definition: Ratio of the permeability of the ceiling.

TileLength.name: Tile Length
TileLength.Definition: Length of ceiling tiles. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

TileWidth.name: Tile Width
TileWidth.Definition: Width of ceiling tiles. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

GrossArea.name: Gross Area
GrossArea.Definition: Gross Area of the object. Openings, recesses, projections and cut-outs are not taken into account.

GrossVolume.name: Gross Volume
GrossVolume.Definition: Total gross volume of the object. Openings, recesses, enclosed objects and projections are not taken into account.

NetArea.name: Net Area
NetArea.Definition: Total net area of the object. Openings, recesses and cut-outs are taken into account by subtraction, projections by addition.

NetVolume.name: Net Volume
NetVolume.Definition: Total net volume of the object, taking into account possible processing features (cut-outs, etc.) or openings and recesses.

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcPavementType.Definition: The Ifc Pavement Type provides the type information for Ifc Pavement occurrences.
IfcPavementType.Name: Pavement Type

IfcReinforcedSoil.Definition: Soil reinforced or stabilized by some mechanical or chemical method.
IfcReinforcedSoil.Name: Reinforced Soil

Width.name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcSign.Definition: A sign is a notice on display that gives information or instructions in a written, symbolic or other form. Signs are passive with the most common form of a pictorial panel. An instance of Ifc Sign refers to the occurrence of an individual panel which can be applied to a surface such as a wall or be aggregated within a Signal Assembly which can include multiple sign occurrences and the associated supporting structural elements (see Signal Assembly for examples).
IfcSign.Name: Sign

AppliesToTrainCategory.name: Applies to Train Category
AppliesToTrainCategory.Definition: Sign information relative to train category, e.g. freight, passenger.

SignalAspectSymbol.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
SignalAspectSymbol.name: Signal Aspect Symbol
SignalAspectSymbol.Definition: Content which is shown on the signal or sign, e.g. text, number, arrow or icon.

SignalAspectType.name: Signal Aspect Type
SignalAspectType.Definition: The type of aspect, e.g. 2-display aspect for distant signal, 3-display aspect for block signal.

SignLegend.name: Sign Legend
SignLegend.Definition: Text information written on the signal or sign.

SignalSightingAchievableDistance.name: Signal Sighting Achievable Distance
SignalSightingAchievableDistance.Definition: Reading distance of the signal, which is achievable with the help of mitigation works.

SignalSightingAvailableDistance.name: Signal Sighting Available Distance
SignalSightingAvailableDistance.Definition: Reading distance of the signal without having any mitigation works.

SignalSightingCombinedWithRepeater.name: Signal Sighting Combined With Repeater
SignalSightingCombinedWithRepeater.Definition: Combined reading distance for the signal and any associated repeaters.

SignalSightingMinimum.name: Signal Sighting Minimum
SignalSightingMinimum.Definition: Minimal distance in which the signal has to be readable.

SignalSightingPreferred.name: Signal Sighting Preferred
SignalSightingPreferred.Definition: Preferred distance in which the signal shall be readable.

SignalSightingRouteIndicator.name: Signal Sighting Route Indicator
SignalSightingRouteIndicator.Definition: Required reading distance for the route indicator.

SignalViewingMinimumInFront.name: Signal Viewing Minimum In Front
SignalViewingMinimumInFront.Definition: Smallest distance where the signal has to be readable (for train very close to the signal).

Category.name: Category
Category.Definition: Designation of the category into which the actors in the population belong.
