CurrentCarryingCapacity.Definition: Maximum value of electric current which can be carried continuously by a conductor, a device or an apparatus, under specified conditions without its steady-state temperature exceeding a specified value. Based on IEC60826-11-13.

DesignAmbientTemperature.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DesignAmbientTemperature.name: Design Ambient Temperature
DesignAmbientTemperature.Definition: The highest and lowest local ambient temperature likely to be encountered.

ElectricalClearanceDistance.name: Electrical Clearance Distance
ElectricalClearanceDistance.Definition: The distance between two conductive parts along a string stretched the shortest way between these conductive parts. (IEV ref 441-17-31)

IfcCableSegment.CONTACTWIRESEGMENT.Definition: An electric conductor of an overhead contact line with which the current collectors make contact.
IfcCableSegment.CONTACTWIRESEGMENT.Name: Contact Wire Segment

CrossSectionalArea.name: Cross Sectional Area
CrossSectionalArea.Definition: Cross section area of the phase(s) lead(s).

CurrentCarryingCapacity.name: Current Carrying Capacity
CurrentCarryingCapacity.Definition: Maximum value of electric current which can be carried continuously by a conductor, a device or an apparatus, under specified conditions without its steady-state temperature exceeding a specified value. Based on IEC60826-11-13.

DCResistance.name: Dcresistance
DCResistance.Definition: The resistance under direct current and 20 degrees centigrade.

MassPerLength.name: Mass Per Length
MassPerLength.Definition: Mass per length, i.e. mass of a beam with a unit length of extrusion. For example measured in kgm.

TensileStrength.name: Tensile Strength
TensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the ability to withstand breakage apart under applied force.

ThermalExpansionCoefficient.name: Thermal Expansion Coefficient
ThermalExpansionCoefficient.Definition: Quantity characterizing the variation with thermodynamic temperature T of the distance l between two points of a body, under given conditions (IEC 113-04-27). The ratio is defined per Kelvin.

YoungModulus.name: Young Modulus
YoungModulus.Definition: A measure of the Youngs modulus of elasticity of the material.

IfcCableSegment.CORESEGMENT.Definition: A self contained element of a cable that comprises one or more conductors and sheathing.The core of one lead is normally single wired or multiwired which are intertwined.
IfcCableSegment.CORESEGMENT.Name: Core Segment

CoreIdentifier.name: Core Identifier
CoreIdentifier.Definition: The core identification used Identifiers may be used such as by color (Black, Brown, Grey) or by number (1, 2, 3) or by IEC phase reference (L1, L2, L3) etc.

CurrentCarryingCapacity.name: Current Carrying Capacity
CurrentCarryingCapacity.Definition: Maximum value of electric current which can be carried continuously by a conductor, a device or an apparatus, under specified conditions without its steady-state temperature exceeding a specified value. Based on IEC60826-11-13.

DCResistance.name: Dcresistance
DCResistance.Definition: The resistance under direct current and 20 degrees centigrade.

FunctionReliable.name: Function Reliable
FunctionReliable.Definition: Element (such as cable, bus, core) maintain given propertiesfunctions over a given (tested) time and conditions. According to IEC standard.

HalogenProof.name: Halogen Proof
HalogenProof.Definition: Produces small amount of smoke and irritating DeaeratorGas.

LayRatio.name: Lay Ratio
LayRatio.Definition: The ratio between lay length and the diameter of the single conductor.

MassPerLength.name: Mass Per Length
MassPerLength.Definition: Mass per length, i.e. mass of a beam with a unit length of extrusion. For example measured in kgm.

OverallDiameter.name: Overall Diameter
OverallDiameter.Definition: The overall diameter of a object.

RatedTemperature.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
RatedTemperature.name: Rated Temperature
RatedTemperature.Definition: The range of allowed temperature that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

RatedVoltage.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
RatedVoltage.name: Rated Voltage
RatedVoltage.Definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

ScreenDiameter.name: Screen Diameter
ScreenDiameter.Definition: The diameter of the screen around an object (if present).

SelfExtinguishing60332_1.name: Self Extinguishing603321
SelfExtinguishing60332_1.Definition: Self Extinguishing cablecore according to IEC 60332.1.

SelfExtinguishing60332_3.name: Self Extinguishing603323
SelfExtinguishing60332_3.Definition: Self Extinguishing cablecore according to IEC 60332.3.

SheathColours.name: Sheath Colours
SheathColours.Definition: Colour of the core (derived from IEC 60757). Note that the combined color Green And Yellow shall be used only as Protective Earth (PE) conductors according to the requirements of IEC 60446.

Standard.name: Standard
Standard.Definition: The designation of the standard applicable for the definition of the object used.

StrandingMethod.name: Stranding Method
StrandingMethod.Definition: Specifies the method used to strand the cable. Stranding is the process where a particular number of stranding elements are joined together while winding them round a common axis.

TensileStrength.name: Tensile Strength
TensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the ability to withstand breakage apart under applied force.

ThermalExpansionCoefficient.name: Thermal Expansion Coefficient
ThermalExpansionCoefficient.Definition: Quantity characterizing the variation with thermodynamic temperature T of the distance l between two points of a body, under given conditions (IEC 113-04-27). The ratio is defined per Kelvin.

UltimateTensileStrength.name: Ultimate Tensile Strength
UltimateTensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the maximum stress that a material or element can withstand before breaking while being stretched or pulled.

YoungModulus.name: Young Modulus
YoungModulus.Definition: A measure of the Youngs modulus of elasticity of the material.

IfcCableSegment.FIBERSEGMENT.Definition: A fiber segment is an individual optical fiber used in telecommunication systems to transmit data by means of optical signals.
IfcCableSegment.FIBERSEGMENT.Name: Fiber Segment

InUse.name: In Use
InUse.Definition: Indicates whether the fiber has been assigned to some specific use.

FiberColour.name: Fiber Colour
FiberColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of a single fiber.

FiberType.name: Fiber Type
FiberType.Definition: Indicates the type of the single fiber.

HasTightJacket.name: Has Tight Jacket
HasTightJacket.Definition: Indicates whether the fiber has a tight jacket or not.

IfcCableSegment.FIBERTUBE.Definition: A fiber tube is semi-rigid hollow plastic tube with a very small radius that houses and protects a certain number of optical fiber segments. An optical cable segment may contain many fiber tubes.
IfcCableSegment.FIBERTUBE.Name: Fiber Tube

FiberTubeColour.name: Fiber Tube Colour
FiberTubeColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of a single fiber tube.

NumberOfFibers.name: Number of Fibers
NumberOfFibers.Definition: Indicates the number of fibers in the single tube or cable.

IfcCableSegment.OPTICALCABLESEGMENT.Definition: An optical cable segment is a cable segment that contains a variable number of optical fiber segments.
IfcCableSegment.OPTICALCABLESEGMENT.Name: Optical Cable Segment

NumberOfFibers.name: Number of Fibers
NumberOfFibers.Definition: Indicates the number of fibers in the single tube or cable.

NumberOfMultiModeFibers.name: Number of Multi Mode Fibers
NumberOfMultiModeFibers.Definition: Total number of multi-mode fibers in the optical fiber cable.

NumberOfSingleModeFibers.name: Number of Single Mode Fibers
NumberOfSingleModeFibers.Definition: Total number of single-mode fibers in the optical fiber cable.

OpticalCableStructure.name: Optical Cable Structure
OpticalCableStructure.Definition: Distinguishes between different structures of an optical fiber cable.

FiberType.name: Fiber Type
FiberType.Definition: Indicates the type of the single fiber.

JacketColour.name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

JacketColour.name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

IfcCableSegment.STITCHWIRE.Definition: A stitch wire consists of auxiliary wires and different components (clamp) used in stitched suspension.
IfcCableSegment.STITCHWIRE.Name: Stitchwire

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system equipment facility is assembled.

MechanicalTension.name: Mechanical Tension
MechanicalTension.Definition: Nominal value of mechanical force applied to a flow segment.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

TensileStrength.name: Tensile Strength
TensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the ability to withstand breakage apart under applied force.

UltimateTensileStrength.name: Ultimate Tensile Strength
UltimateTensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the maximum stress that a material or element can withstand before breaking while being stretched or pulled.

IfcCableSegment.WIREPAIRSEGMENT.Definition: A pair of conductors contained in a copper cable. The pair is always used together to form a circuit to transmit data by means of electric signals.
IfcCableSegment.WIREPAIRSEGMENT.Name: Wire Pair Segment

CharacteristicImpedance.name: Characteristic Impedance
CharacteristicImpedance.Definition: A quantity defined for a mode of propagation at a given frequency in a specific uniform transmission line or uniform waveguide by one of the three following relations

ConductorDiameter.name: Conductor Diameter
ConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the conductor diameter. It is only used for twisted and untwisted wire pair.

CoreConductorDiameter.name: Core Conductor Diameter
CoreConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the core conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

JacketColour.name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

ShieldConductorDiameter.name: Shield Conductor Diameter
ShieldConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the shielded conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

WirePairType.name: Wire Pair Type
WirePairType.Definition: Indicates the type of wire pair, i.e., twisted, untwisted or coaxial pair.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ANTENNA.Definition: A transducer designed to transmit or receive electromagnetic waves.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ANTENNA.Name: Antenna

AntennaGain.name: Antenna Gain
AntennaGain.Definition: Indicates the antenna gain, which is a ratio of the power transmitted by an antenna in a specific direction compared to an isotropic antenna.

PolarizationMode.name: Polarization Mode
PolarizationMode.Definition: Indicates the polarization mode of antenna.

RadiationPattern.name: Radiation Pattern
RadiationPattern.Definition: Indicates the radiation pattern of antenna.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.AUTOMATON.Definition: A self-acting artificial device, the behaviour of which is governed either in a stepwise manner by given decision rules or continuously in time by defined relationships, while the output variables of which are created from its input and state variables.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.AUTOMATON.Name: Automaton

InputSignalType.name: Input Signal Type
InputSignalType.Definition: The type of the input signal.

OutputSignalType.name: Output Signal Type
OutputSignalType.Definition: The type of the output signal.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.COMPUTER.Definition: A desktop, laptop, tablet, or other type of computer that can be moved from one place to another and connected to an electrical supply via a plugged outlet.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.COMPUTER.Name: Computer

StorageCapacity.name: Storage Capacity
StorageCapacity.Definition: Indicates the total data storage capacity of the device. It is defined by bytes.

UserInterfaceType.name: User Interface Type
UserInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the user interface of the computer.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.FAX.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of transmitting a facsimile copy of printed matter using a telephone line.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.FAX.Name: Fax

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.GATEWAY.Definition: A gateway connects multiple network segments with different protocols at all layers (layers 1-7) of the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) model.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.GATEWAY.Name: Gateway

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.INTELLIGENTPE.Definition: An intelligent peripheral is a device that offers a variety of specialized resources according to the corresponding service logical program under the control of SCP. These resources contain the receiver of DTMF (Dual-Tone Multi-Frequency, signal generator, record notice, etc.). An intelligent peripheral provides dedicated resource functions in the intelligent network, allocates, controls and manages various dedicated resources, communicates with other entities in the network, and completes SRF resource functions as well as the maintenance, management and statistics functions of resources.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.INTELLIGENTPE.Name: Intelligent Peripheral

UserCapacity.name: User Capacity
UserCapacity.Definition: Indicates the user capacity of the device, defined as the maximum number of users that can be active at the same time.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.IPNETWORKEQUI.Definition: An IP network equipment is a device that provides IP data transmission channel for telecom subsystems or other subsystems e.g., routers, network switches or firewalls.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.IPNETWORKEQUI.Name: Ip Network Equipment

EquipmentCapacity.name: Equipment Capacity
EquipmentCapacity.Definition: Indicates the equipment capacity of the appliance. The value is defined in bitss.

ManagingSoftware.name: Managing Software
ManagingSoftware.Definition: Indicates the type of software responsible for managing the equipment.

NumberOfCoolingFans.name: Number of Cooling Fans
NumberOfCoolingFans.Definition: Indicates the number of cooling fans in the equipment.

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

SupportedProtocol.name: Supported Protocol
SupportedProtocol.Definition: Indicates the protocol supported by the IP network equipment.

NumberOfPackets.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfPackets.name: Number of Packets
NumberOfPackets.Definition: Indicates the number of packets of the IP network equipment.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.LINESIDEELECT.Definition: The lineside electronic unit (LEU) is the interface between the balise and interlocking in railway. The LEU acquires the information from the interlocking, and sends the appropriate information to the balises in concordance with the lineside signalling (if available).
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.LINESIDEELECT.Name: Line Side Electronic Unit

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.MODEM.Definition: A modem (from modulator-demodulator) is a device that modulates an analog carrier signal to encode digital information, and also demodulates such a carrier signal to decode the transmitted information.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.MODEM.Name: Modem

CommonInterfaceType.name: Common Interface Type
CommonInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of the device common interfaces.

NumberOfCommonInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfCommonInterfaces.name: Number of Common Interfaces
NumberOfCommonInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the number of common interfaces on the device.

NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.name: Number of Traffic Interfaces
NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the number of traffic interfaces on the device.

TrafficInterfaceType.name: Traffic Interface Type
TrafficInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of the device traffic interfaces.

DataTransmissionUnitUsage.name: Data Transmission Unit Usage
DataTransmissionUnitUsage.Definition: Indicates the usage of the data transmission unit. It can be used to transmit data for different types of sensors.

SerialInterfaceType.name: Serial Interface Type
SerialInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of serial interface used by the device.

WorkingState.name: Working State
WorkingState.Definition: Indicates the working state of device or system.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKAPPLIA.Definition: A network appliance performs a dedicated function such as firewall protection, content filtering, load balancing, or equipment management.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKAPPLIA.Name: Network Appliance

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKBRIDGE.Definition: A network bridge connects multiple network segments at the data link layer (layer 2) of the OSI model, and the term layer 2 switch is very often used interchangeably with bridge.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKBRIDGE.Name: Network Bridge

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKHUB.Definition: A network hub connects multiple network segments at the physical layer (layer 1) of the OSI model.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKHUB.Name: Network Hub

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALLINETE.Definition: An optical line terminal is a service provider endpoint of a passive or active optical network. It is the terminal equipment for connecting fiber optic trunks.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALLINETE.Name: Opticalline Terminal

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALNETWOR.Definition: An optical network unit is a kind of optical transmission network connection equipment which is installed at user side.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALNETWOR.Name: Optical Network Unit

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

OpticalNetworkUnitType.name: Optical Network Unit Type
OpticalNetworkUnitType.Definition: Indicates the type of the optical network unit equipment.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.PRINTER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of printing text andor graphics onto paper or other media.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.PRINTER.Name: Printer

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.RADIOBLOCKCEN.Definition: A radio block center is a specialised computing device in railway with specification for generating Movement Authorities (MA) and transmitting it to trains. It gets information from signalling control and from the trains in its section.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.RADIOBLOCKCEN.Name: Radioblock Center

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.REPEATER.Definition: A repeater is an electronic device that receives a signal and retransmits it at a higher level andor higher power, or onto the other side of an obstruction, so that the signal can cover longer distances without degradation.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.REPEATER.Name: Repeater

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ROUTER.Definition: A router is a networking device whose software and hardware are usually tailored to the tasks of routing and forwarding information. For example, on the Internet, information is directed to various paths by routers.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ROUTER.Name: Router

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.SCANNER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of scanning the content of printed matter and converting it to digital format that can be stored in a computer.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.SCANNER.Name: Scanner

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELECOMMAND.Definition: A system sending command to control and monitor the switches and circuit breakers or systems directly or not connected (e.g. via wires) within the traction power system remotely.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELECOMMAND.Name: Telecommand

NumberOfCPUs.name: Number of Cpus
NumberOfCPUs.Definition: The number of CPUs used by the equipment.

NumberOfWorkstations.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfWorkstations.name: Number of Workstations
NumberOfWorkstations.Definition: Indicates the types or purposes of workstations and their number in the equipment. The defined purpose can be e.g. Diagnostic and maintenance, Traffic and electric traction, etc.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELEPHONYEXCH.Definition: A telephony exchange is a device that ensures the routing of telephone calls and communications.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELEPHONYEXCH.Name: Telephony Exchange

UserCapacity.name: User Capacity
UserCapacity.Definition: Indicates the user capacity of the device, defined as the maximum number of users that can be active at the same time.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSITIONCOM.Definition: A transition component is a minor active device that converts electric signals to optical signals at the sender, and converts optical signals to electric signals at the receiver.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSITIONCOM.Name: Transition Component

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPONDER.Definition: A transponder is a communication, monitoring, or control device that, upon receiving a signal, emits a different signal in response. Transponders can be either passive or active (e.g., electronic beacon, balise).
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPONDER.Name: Transponder

DetectionRange.name: Detection Range
DetectionRange.Definition: The detection range of the equipment.

InformationLength.name: Information Length
InformationLength.Definition: Indicates supported bytes of the data Information, e.g.127 bytes.

IP_Code.name: Ipcode
IP_Code.Definition: IP Code, the International Protection Marking, IEC 60529), classifies and rates the degree of protection provided against intrusion.

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

OperationalTemperatureRange.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
OperationalTemperatureRange.name: Operational Temperature Range
OperationalTemperatureRange.Definition: The temperature range in which the device operates normally.

TransmissionRate.name: Transmission Rate
TransmissionRate.Definition: Data transmission rate between the device and the receiving module in bits per second.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPORTEQUI.Definition: A transport equipment is a network element responsible for providing functionality of transport, multiplexing, switching, management and supervision of transmission channels between different hosts. The data transport service uses three specific metrics the bandwidth, the jitter, and the packet loss rate.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPORTEQUI.Name: Transport Equipment

ElectricalCrossCapacity.name: Electrical Cross Capacity
ElectricalCrossCapacity.Definition: Indicates the electrical cross capacity of the transport equipment.

IsUpgradable.name: Is Upgradable
IsUpgradable.Definition: Indicates whether the transport equipment can be upgraded or not.

TransportEquipmentAssemblyType.name: Transport Equipment Assembly Type
TransportEquipmentAssemblyType.Definition: Indicates the type of transport equipment assembly.

TransportEquipmentType.name: Transport Equipment Type
TransportEquipmentType.Definition: Indicates the type of transport equipment.

ChromaticDispersionTolerance.name: Chromatic Dispersion Tolerance
ChromaticDispersionTolerance.Definition: Indicates the tolerance of the transport equipment chromatic dispersion. The value is defined by picosecond per nanometer (psnm).

EquipmentCapacity.name: Equipment Capacity
EquipmentCapacity.Definition: Indicates the equipment capacity of the appliance. The value is defined in bitss.

MinimumOpticalSignalToNoiseRatio.name: Minimum Optical Signal to Noise Ratio
MinimumOpticalSignalToNoiseRatio.Definition: Indicates the minimum optical signal to noise ratio of the transport equipment.

PolarizationModeDispersionTolerance.name: Polarization Mode Dispersion Tolerance
PolarizationModeDispersionTolerance.Definition: Indicates the polarization mode dispersion tolerance of the transport equipment. It is usually measured by picosecond.

SingleChannelAveragePower.name: Single Channel Average Power
SingleChannelAveragePower.Definition: Indicates the average power of a single channel of the transport equipment.

SingleChannelPower.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
SingleChannelPower.name: Single Channel Power
SingleChannelPower.Definition: Indicates the power range of a single channel of the transport equipment.

SingleWaveTransmissionRate.name: Single Wave Transmission Rate
SingleWaveTransmissionRate.Definition: Indicates the single wave transmission rate of the transport equipment.

IfcDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNIT.Definition: A distribution point on the incoming electrical supply, typically in domestic premises, at which protective devices are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNIT.Name: Consumer Unit

IfcDistributionBoard.DISPATCHINGBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which voice and data communication signals are managed between communication devices.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISPATCHINGBOARD.Name: Dispatching Board

DispatchingBoardType.name: Dispatching Board Type
DispatchingBoardType.Definition: Indicates the type of dispatching board.

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which connections are made for distribution of electrical circuits usually through protective devices.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONBOARD.Name: Distribution Board

IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONFRAME.Definition: A distribution frame is used to interconnect and manage wiring between active equipment and subscriber. It might be composed of multiple distribution boards and other components.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONFRAME.Name: Distribution Frame

PortCapacity.name: Port Capacity
PortCapacity.Definition: Indicates the number of ports in the passive device that can be used to interconnect cables.

IfcDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTROLCENTRE.Definition: A distribution point at which starting and control devices for major plant items are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTROLCENTRE.Name: Motor Control Centre

IfcDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which switching devices are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Name: Switch Board

IfcElectricAppliance.DISHWASHER.Definition: An appliance that has the primary function of washing dishes.
IfcElectricAppliance.DISHWASHER.Name: Dishwasher

IfcElectricAppliance.ELECTRICCOOKER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food (including oven, hob, grill).
IfcElectricAppliance.ELECTRICCOOKER.Name: Electriccooker

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGELECTRI.Definition: An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide heat. A freestanding electric heater is a plugged appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGELECTRI.Name: Freestandingelectricheater

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGFAN.Definition: An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide ventilation. A freestanding fan is a plugged appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGFAN.Name: Freestandingfan

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERCO.Definition: A small, local electrical appliance for cooling water. A freestanding water cooler is a plugged appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERCO.Name: Freestanding Water Cooler

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERHE.Definition: A small, local electrical appliance for heating water. A freestanding water heater is a plugged appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERHE.Name: Freestanding Water Heater

IfcElectricAppliance.FREEZER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at temperatures below the freezing point of water.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREEZER.Name: Freezer

IfcElectricAppliance.FRIDGE_FREEZER.Definition: An electrical appliance that combines the functions of a freezer and a refrigerator through the provision of separate compartments.
IfcElectricAppliance.FRIDGE_FREEZER.Name: Fridge Freezer

IfcElectricAppliance.HANDDRYER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying hands.
IfcElectricAppliance.HANDDRYER.Name: Hand Dryer

IfcElectricAppliance.KITCHENMACHINE.Definition: A specialized appliance used in commercial kitchens such as a mixer.
IfcElectricAppliance.KITCHENMACHINE.Name: Kitchen Machine

IfcElectricAppliance.MICROWAVE.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food using microwaves.
IfcElectricAppliance.MICROWAVE.Name: Microwave

IfcElectricAppliance.PHOTOCOPIER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of reproduction of printed matter.
IfcElectricAppliance.PHOTOCOPIER.Name: Photocopier

IfcElectricAppliance.REFRIGERATOR.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at low temperature but above the freezing point of water.
IfcElectricAppliance.REFRIGERATOR.Name: Refrigerator

IfcElectricAppliance.TUMBLEDRYER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying clothes.
IfcElectricAppliance.TUMBLEDRYER.Name: Tumble Dryer

IfcElectricAppliance.VENDINGMACHINE.Definition: An appliance that stores and vends goods including food, drink, tickets, and goods of various types.
IfcElectricAppliance.VENDINGMACHINE.Name: Vending Machine

MoneyStuckRatio.name: Money Stuck Ratio
MoneyStuckRatio.Definition: Indicates the ratio of money being stuck or jammed in appliance.

PaymentMethod.Definition: Indicates the vending machine payment method.

TicketProductionSpeed.name: Ticket Production Speed
TicketProductionSpeed.Definition: Indicates the production speed of the ticket. It is measured by counting the number of tickets that can be produced per hour.

TicketStuckRatio.name: Ticket Stuck Ratio
TicketStuckRatio.Definition: Indicates the ratio of tickets being stuck or jammed in the appliance.

TicketVendingMachineType.name: Ticket Vending Machine Type
TicketVendingMachineType.Definition: Indicates the type of ticket vending machine.

VendingMachineUserInterface.name: Vending Machine User Interface
VendingMachineUserInterface.Definition: Indicates the type of vending machine user interface.

IfcElectricAppliance.WASHINGMACHINE.Definition: An appliance that has the primary function of washing clothes.
IfcElectricAppliance.WASHINGMACHINE.Name: Washing Machine

IfcElectricDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNI.Definition: A distribution point on the incoming electrical supply, typically in domestic premises, at which protective devices are located.
IfcElectricDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNI.Name: Consumer Unit

IfcElectricDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIO.Definition: A distribution point at which connections are made for distribution of electrical circuits usually through protective devices.
IfcElectricDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIO.Name: Distribution Board

IfcElectricDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTRO.Definition: A distribution point at which starting and control devices for major plant items are located.
IfcElectricDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTRO.Name: Motor Control Centre

IfcElectricDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which switching devices are located.
IfcElectricDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Name: Switch Board

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.BATTERY.Name: Battery

NominalSupplyCurrent.Definition: The nominal current of the supply.

VoltageRegulationRate.name: Voltage Regulation Rate
VoltageRegulationRate.Definition: When the input side voltage changes from the lowest allowable input value to the specified maximum value, the relative change value of the output voltage is the percentage of the rated output voltage.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITOR.Definition: A device that stores electric charge when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance. Two-terminal device characterized essentially by its capacitance.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITOR.Name: Capacitor

NumberOfPhases.name: Number of Phases
NumberOfPhases.Definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITORBA.Definition: A device that stores electrical energy when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITORBA.Name: Capacitorbank

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.COMPENSATOR.Definition: A device that is used to fix or adjust the parameter of electric energy, such as voltage loss, power factor and so on.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.COMPENSATOR.Name: Compensator

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.HARMONICFIL.Definition: A device that constantly injects currents that precisely correspond to the harmonic components drawn by the load.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.HARMONICFIL.Name: Harmonic Filter

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTOR.Definition: A device used in circuits or power systems due to their inductance, acting as a component of electric storage device.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTOR.Name: Inductor

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTORBAN.Definition: A device that stores electrical energy in a magnetic field using electrical property of inductance.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTORBAN.Name: Inductorbank

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.RECHARGER.Definition: A recharger or battery charger is a device used to put energy into a secondary cell or rechargeable battery by forcing an electric current through it.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.RECHARGER.Name: Recharger

NominalSupplyCurrent.name: Nominal Supply Current
NominalSupplyCurrent.Definition: The nominal current of the supply.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.UPS.Definition: A device that provides a time limited alternative source of power supply in the event of failure of the main supply.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.UPS.Name: UPS

IfcElectricFlowTreatmentDevice.ELECTRONI.Definition: Linear two-port device designed to transmit spectral components of the input quantity according to a specified law, generally in order to pass the components in certain frequency bands and to attenuate those in other bands
IfcElectricFlowTreatmentDevice.ELECTRONI.Name: Electronic Filter

NominalCurrent.name: Nominal Current
NominalCurrent.Definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

NominalPower.name: Nominal Power
NominalPower.Definition: A conventional value of apparent power determining a value of the rated current that may be carried with rated voltage applied, under specified conditions. ( IEV ref 421-04-04)

PrimaryFrequency.name: Primary Frequency
PrimaryFrequency.Definition: The frequency that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

RatedVoltage.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
RatedVoltage.name: Rated Voltage
RatedVoltage.Definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

SecondaryFrequency.name: Secondary Frequency
SecondaryFrequency.Definition: The frequency that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

IfcElectricGenerator.CHP.Definition: Combined heat and power supply, used not only as a source of electric energy but also as a heating source for the building. It may therefore be not only part of an electrical system but also of a heating system.
IfcElectricGenerator.CHP.Name: CHP

IfcElectricGenerator.ENGINEGENERATOR.Definition: Electrical generator with a fuel-driven engine, for example a diesel-driven emergency power supply.
IfcElectricGenerator.ENGINEGENERATOR.Name: Engine Generator

IfcElectricGenerator.STANDALONE.Definition: Electrical generator which does not include its source of kinetic energy, that is, a motor, engine, or turbine are all modeled separately.
IfcElectricGenerator.STANDALONE.Name: Standalone

IfcElectricMotor.DC.Definition: A motor using either generated or rectified Direct Current (DC) power.
IfcElectricMotor.DC.Name: DC

IfcElectricMotor.INDUCTION.Definition: An alternating current motor in which the primary winding on one member (usually the stator) is connected to the power source and a secondary winding or a squirrel-cage secondary winding on the other member (usually the rotor) carries the induced current. There is no physical electrical connection to the secondary winding, its current is induced.
IfcElectricMotor.INDUCTION.Name: Induction

IfcElectricMotor.POLYPHASE.Definition: A two or three-phase induction motor in which the windings, one for each phase, are evenly divided by the same number of electrical degrees.
IfcElectricMotor.POLYPHASE.Name: Polyphase

IfcElectricMotor.RELUCTANCESYNCHRONOUS.Definition: A synchronous motor with a special rotor design which directly lines the rotor up with the rotating magnetic field of the stator, allowing for no slip under load.
IfcElectricMotor.RELUCTANCESYNCHRONOUS.Name: Reluctance Synchronous

IfcElectricMotor.SYNCHRONOUS.Definition: A motor that operates at a constant speed up to full load. The rotor speed is equal to the speed of the rotating magnetic field of the stator there is no slip.
IfcElectricMotor.SYNCHRONOUS.Name: Synchronous

IfcElectricTimeControl.RELAY.Definition: Electromagnetically operated contactor for making or breaking a control circuit.
IfcElectricTimeControl.RELAY.Name: Relay

IfcElectricTimeControl.TIMECLOCK.Definition: A control that causes action to occur at set times.
IfcElectricTimeControl.TIMECLOCK.Name: Time Clock

IfcElectricTimeControl.TIMEDELAY.Definition: A control that causes action to occur following a set duration.
IfcElectricTimeControl.TIMEDELAY.Name: Time Delay

IfcJunctionBox.DATA.Definition: Contains cables, outlets, andor switches for communications use.
IfcJunctionBox.DATA.Name: Data

DataConnectionType.name: Data Connection Type
DataConnectionType.Definition: Indicates the data connection type of the junction box e.g. copper pair, fiber or others.

NumberOfBranches.name: Number of Branches
NumberOfBranches.Definition: Indicates the number of branches that can be supported by the optical splitter.

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

OpticalSplitterType.name: Optical Splitter Type
OpticalSplitterType.Definition: Indicates the type of optical splitter, single mode or multi-mode.

IfcJunctionBox.POWER.Definition: Contains cables, outlets, andor switches for electrical power.
IfcJunctionBox.POWER.Name: Power

IfcLamp.COMPACTFLUORESCENT.Definition: A fluorescent lamp having a compact form factor produced by shaping the tube.
IfcLamp.COMPACTFLUORESCENT.Name: Compactfluorescent

IfcLamp.FLUORESCENT.Definition: A typically tubular discharge lamp in which most of the light is emitted by one or several layers of phosphors excited by ultraviolet radiation from the discharge.
IfcLamp.FLUORESCENT.Name: Fluorescent

IfcLamp.HALOGEN.Definition: An incandescent lamp in which a tungsten filament is sealed into a compact transport envelope filled with an inert gas and a small amount of halogen such as iodine or bromine.
IfcLamp.HALOGEN.Name: Halogen

IfcLamp.HIGHPRESSUREMERCURY.Definition: A discharge lamp in which most of the light is emitted by exciting mercury at high pressure.
IfcLamp.HIGHPRESSUREMERCURY.Name: High Pressure Mercury

IfcLamp.HIGHPRESSURESODIUM.Definition: A discharge lamp in which most of the light is emitted by exciting sodium at high pressure.
IfcLamp.HIGHPRESSURESODIUM.Name: High Pressure Sodium

IfcLamp.LED.Definition: A solid state lamp that uses light-emitting diodes as the source of light.
IfcLamp.LED.Name: LED

IfcLamp.METALHALIDE.Definition: A discharge lamp in which most of the light is emitted by exciting a metal halide.
IfcLamp.METALHALIDE.Name: Metalhalide

IfcLamp.OLED.Definition: A solid state lamp that uses light-emitting diodes as the source of light whose emissive electroluminescent layer is composed of a film of organic compounds.
IfcLamp.OLED.Name: OLED

IfcLamp.TUNGSTENFILAMENT.Definition: A lamp that emits light by passing an electrical current through a tungsten wire filament in a near vacuum.
IfcLamp.TUNGSTENFILAMENT.Name: Tungstenfilament

IfcLightFixture.DIRECTIONSOURCE.Definition: A light fixture that is considered to have a length or surface area from which it emits light in a direction. A light fixture containing one or more fluorescent lamps is an example of a direction source.
IfcLightFixture.DIRECTIONSOURCE.Name: Direct Ionsource

IfcLightFixture.POINTSOURCE.Definition: A light fixture that is considered to have negligible area and that emit light with approximately equal intensity in all directions. A light fixture containing a tungsten, halogen or similar bulb is an example of a point source.
IfcLightFixture.POINTSOURCE.Name: Point Source

IfcLightFixture.SECURITYLIGHTING.Definition: A light fixture having specific purpose of directing occupants in an emergency, such as an illuminated exit sign or emergency flood light.
IfcLightFixture.SECURITYLIGHTING.Name: Security Lighting

BackupSupplySystem.name: Backup Supply System
BackupSupplySystem.Definition: The type of backup supply system.

FixtureHeight.name: Fixture Height
FixtureHeight.Definition: The height of the fixture, such as the text height of an exit sign.

SelfTestFunction.name: Self Test Function
SelfTestFunction.Definition: The type of self test function.

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.ACC.Definition: An access point is a device that allows wireless devices to connect to a wired network.
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.ACC.Name: Access Point

DataEncryptionType.name: Data Encryption Type

DataExchangeRate.name: Data Exchange Rate
DataExchangeRate.Definition: Indicates the data transfer rate of the access point in bit per second (bps).

This component is responsible for the internetworking between the GPRS network and external packet switched networks (e.g. the internet).
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.GAT.Name: Gateway GPRS Support Node

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.MAS.Definition: A master unit is a component of a repeater for coupling base station signals.

TransmittedFrequency.name: Transmitted Frequency
TransmittedFrequency.Definition: Indicates the transmitted frequency used by the master unit.

TransmittedSignal.Definition: Indicates the type or standard of signal transmitted by the master unit.

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.MOB.Definition: The mobile switching centre (MSC) constitutes the interface between the radio system and the fixed networks. It is an exchange which performs all the switching and signalling functions for mobile station located in a geographical area designated as the MSC area. It consists of a MSC server and a media gateway.
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.MOB.Name: Mobile Switching Center

MaximumNumberOfManagedBSCs.name: Maximum Number of Managed Bscs
MaximumNumberOfManagedBSCs.Definition: Indicates the maximum number of base station controller (BSC) that can be managed simultaneously by the mobile switching center (MSC).

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.MSC.Definition: The MSC server mainly comprises the call control (CC) and mobility control parts of a mobile switching center (MSC). An MSC server and a media gateway make up the full functionality of an MSC.

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.PAC.Definition: A packet control unit performs some of the processing tasks of the base station controller for packet data. It is responsible for data packet, wireless channel management, error sending detection and automatic retransmission.
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.PAC.Name: Packetcontrol Unit

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.REM.Definition: A remote radio unit is a component of a distributed base transceiver station that converts digital baseband signals into high-frequency (rf) signals and sends high-frequency (rf) signals to the antenna for radiation.
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.REM.Name: Remoteradio Unit

RUConnectionType.name: Ruconnection Type
RUConnectionType.Definition: Indicate the connection type between the remote unit and the master unit.

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.SER.Definition: The service GPRS support node (SGSN) is a component of the GPRS core network. It is the GPRS support node of mobile station service, and it can achieve mobility management and packet routing and transfer.
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.SER.Name: Service GPRS Support Node

IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.SUB.Definition: It is a database in charge of the management of mobile subscribers. It can be an authentication center (Au C) or a home location register (HLR).
IfcMobileTelecommunicationsAppliance.SUB.Name: Subscriber Server

IfcMotorConnection.BELTDRIVE.Definition: An indirect connection made through the medium of a shaped, flexible continuous loop.
IfcMotorConnection.BELTDRIVE.Name: Belt Drive

IfcMotorConnection.COUPLING.Definition: An indirect connection made through the medium of the viscosity of a fluid.
IfcMotorConnection.COUPLING.Name: Coupling

IfcMotorConnection.DIRECTDRIVE.Definition: A direct, physical connection made between the motor and the driven device.
IfcMotorConnection.DIRECTDRIVE.Name: Direct Drive

IfcOutlet.AUDIOVISUALOUTLET.Definition: An outlet used for an audio or visual device.

IfcOutlet.COMMUNICATIONSOUTLET.Definition: An outlet used for connecting communications equipment.

I1.name: I1
I1.Definition: The (thermal) lower testing current limit in x In, indicating that for currents lower than I1, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T2.

I2.name: I2
I2.Definition: The (thermal) upper testing current limit in x In, indicating that for currents larger than I2, the tripping time shall be shorter than the associated tripping time, T2.

I4.name: I4
I4.Definition: The lower electromagnetic testing current limit in x In, indicating that for currents lower than I4, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall not trip instantaneous.

I5.name: I5
I5.Definition: The upper electromagnetic testing current limit in x In, indicating that for currents larger than I5, the tripping time shall be shorter than or equal to the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall trip instantaneous.

T2.name: T2
T2.Definition: The (thermal) testing time in s associated with the testing currents I1 and I2.

T5.name: T5
T5.Definition: The electromagnetic testing time in s associated with the testing currents I4 and I5, i.e. electromagnetic tripping time

TemperatureFactor.name: Temperature Factor

N_Protection_50.name: Nprotection50
N_Protection_50.Definition: An indication whether the electronic tripping unit is tripping if the current in the N conductor is more than 50 of that of the phase conductors. The property is only asserted if the property NProtection is asserted.

N_Protection_Select.Definition: An indication whether the use of the NProtection can be selected by the user or not. If both the properties NProtection50 and NProtection100 are asserted, the value of NProtectionSelect property is set to TRUE. The property is only asserted if the property NProtection is asserted.

IfcAirToAirHeatRecovery.FIXEDPLATECROSSF.Name: Fixed Plate Cross Flow Exchanger

IfcAirToAirHeatRecovery.FIXEDPLATEPARALL.Name: Fixed Plate Parallel Flow Exchanger

IfcAirToAirHeatRecovery.HEATPIPE.Name: Heatpipe

IfcAirToAirHeatRecovery.ROTARYWHEEL.Name: Rotary Wheel

IfcAirToAirHeatRecovery.THERMOSIPHONSEAL.Name: Thermosiphonsealed Tube Heat Exchangers

NominalEfficiencyTable.name: Nominal Efficiency Table
NominalEfficiencyTable.Definition: The nominal efficiency of the boiler as defined by the manufacturer. For steam boilers, a function of inlet temperature versus steam pressure. Note as two variables are used, Defining Values and Defined Values are null, and values are stored in Ifc Table in the following order Inlet Temperature(Ifc Thermodynamic Temperature Measure) and Outlet Temperature(Ifc Thermodynamic Temperature Measure) in Defining Values, and Nominal Efficiency(Ifc Normalised Ratio Measure) in Defined Values. For example, Defininf Values(Inlet Temp, Outlet Temp), Defined Values(null, Nominal Efficiency). The Ifc Table is related to Ifc Property Table Value using Ifc Metric and Ifc Resource Constraint Relationship.

HeatOutput.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
HeatOutput.name: Heat Output
HeatOutput.Definition: Total nominal heat output as listed by the Boiler manufacturer.

NominalEfficiency.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NominalEfficiency.name: Nominal Efficiency
NominalEfficiency.Definition: Nominal object efficiency under nominal conditions.

IfcCoil.DXCOOLINGCOIL.Definition: Cooling coil using a refrigerant to cool the air stream directly.
IfcCoil.DXCOOLINGCOIL.Name: Dxcooling Coil

IfcCoil.ELECTRICHEATINGCOIL.Definition: Heating coil using electricity as a heating source.
IfcCoil.ELECTRICHEATINGCOIL.Name: Electric Heating Coil

IfcCoil.GASHEATINGCOIL.Definition: Heating coil using gas as a heating source.
IfcCoil.GASHEATINGCOIL.Name: Gas Heating Coil

IfcCoil.HYDRONICCOIL.Definition: Cooling or Heating coil that uses a hydronic fluid as a cooling or heating source.
IfcCoil.HYDRONICCOIL.Name: Hydronic Coil

IfcCoil.STEAMHEATINGCOIL.Definition: Heating coil using steam as heating source.
IfcCoil.STEAMHEATINGCOIL.Name: Steam Heating Coil

IfcCoil.WATERCOOLINGCOIL.Definition: Cooling coil using chilled water. HYDRONICCOIL supercedes this enumerator.
IfcCoil.WATERCOOLINGCOIL.Name: Water Cooling Coil

IfcCoil.WATERHEATINGCOIL.Definition: Heating coil using hot water as a heating source. HYDRONICCOIL supercedes this enumerator.
IfcCoil.WATERHEATINGCOIL.Name: Water Heating Coil

IfcCompressor.BOOSTER.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where pressure is increased by a booster.
IfcCompressor.BOOSTER.Name: Booster

IfcCompressor.DYNAMIC.Definition: The pressure of refrigerant vapor is increased by a continuous transfer of angular momentum from a rotating member to the vapor followed by conversion of this momentum into static pressure.
IfcCompressor.DYNAMIC.Name: Dynamic

IfcCompressor.HERMETIC.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the motor and compressor are contained within the same housing, with the motor shaft integral with the compressor crankshaft and the motor in contact with refrigerant.
IfcCompressor.HERMETIC.Name: Hermetic

IfcCompressor.OPENTYPE.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the shaft extends through a seal in the crankcase for an external drive.
IfcCompressor.OPENTYPE.Name: Opentype

IfcCompressor.RECIPROCATING.Definition: Positive-displacement compressor using a piston driven by a connecting rod from a crankshaft.
IfcCompressor.RECIPROCATING.Name: Reciprocating

IfcCompressor.ROLLINGPISTON.Definition: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with a single vane in the nonrotating cylindrical housing.
IfcCompressor.ROLLINGPISTON.Name: Rolling Piston

IfcCompressor.ROTARY.Definition: Positive-displacement compressor using a roller or rotor device.
IfcCompressor.ROTARY.Name: Rotary

IfcCompressor.ROTARYVANE.Definition: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with multiple vanes in the nontotating cylindrical housing.
IfcCompressor.ROTARYVANE.Name: Rotaryvane

IfcCompressor.SCROLL.Definition: Positive-displacement compressor using two inter-fitting, spiral-shaped scroll members.
IfcCompressor.SCROLL.Name: Scroll

IfcCompressor.SEMIHERMETIC.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the hermetic compressors use bolted construction amenable to field repair.
IfcCompressor.SEMIHERMETIC.Name: Semihermetic

IfcCompressor.SINGLESCREW.Definition: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a single cylindrical main rotor that works with a pair of gate rotors.
IfcCompressor.SINGLESCREW.Name: Single Screw

IfcCompressor.SINGLESTAGE.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where vapor is compressed in a single stage.
IfcCompressor.SINGLESTAGE.Name: Single Stage

IfcCompressor.TROCHOIDAL.Definition: Positive-displacement compressor using a rolling motion of one circle outside or inside the circumference of a basic circle and produce either epitrochoids or hypotrochoids.
IfcCompressor.TROCHOIDAL.Name: Trochoidal

IfcCompressor.TWINSCREW.Definition: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using two mating helically grooved rotors, male (lobes) and female (flutes) in a stationary housing with inlet and outlet gas ports.
IfcCompressor.TWINSCREW.Name: Twin Screw

IfcCompressor.WELDEDSHELLHERMETIC.Definition: Positive-displacement reciprocating compressor where the motor compressor is mounted inside a steel shell, which, in turn is sealed by welding.
IfcCompressor.WELDEDSHELLHERMETIC.Name: Welded Shell Hermetic

IfcCondenser.AIRCOOLED.Definition: A condenser in which heat is transferred to an air-stream.
IfcCondenser.AIRCOOLED.Name: Air Cooled

IfcCondenser.EVAPORATIVECOOLED.Definition: A condenser that is cooled evaporatively.
IfcCondenser.EVAPORATIVECOOLED.Name: Evaporative Cooled

IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDBRAZEDPLATE.Definition: Water-cooled condenser with plates brazed together to form an assembly of separate channels.
IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDBRAZEDPLATE.Name: Water Cooled Brazed Plate

IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDSHELLCOIL.Definition: Water-cooled condenser with cooling water circulated through one or more continuous or assembled coils contained within the shell.
IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDSHELLCOIL.Name: Water Cooled Shell Coil

IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDSHELLTUBE.Definition: Water-cooled condenser with cooling water circulated through one or more tubes contained within the shell.
IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDSHELLTUBE.Name: Water Cooled Shell Tube

IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDTUBEINTUBE.Definition: Water-cooled condenser consisting of one or more assemblies of two tubes, one within the other.
IfcCondenser.WATERCOOLEDTUBEINTUBE.Name: Water Cooled Tube In Tube

IfcCooledBeam.ACTIVE.Definition: An active or ventilated cooled beam provides cooling (and heating) but can also function as an air terminal in a ventilation system.
IfcCooledBeam.ACTIVE.Name: Active

AirFlowRate.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AirFlowRate.name: Air Flow Rate

AirPressureDropCurves.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AirPressureDropCurves.name: Air Pressure Drop Curves
AirPressureDropCurves.Definition: Air pressure drop as function of air flow rate.

Throw.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Throw.name: Throw
Throw.Definition: Distance cooled beam throws the air.

AirFlowConfiguration.name: Air Flow Configuration
AirFlowConfiguration.Definition: Air flow configuration type of cooled beam.

AirFlowRateRange.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AirFlowRateRange.name: Air Flow Rate Range
AirFlowRateRange.Definition: Possible range of airflow that can be delivered.

ConnectionSize.name: Connection Size
ConnectionSize.Definition: The connection size of the object.

SupplyAirConnectionType.name: Supply Air Connection Type
SupplyAirConnectionType.Definition: The manner in which the pipe connection is made to the cooled beam.

IfcCooledBeam.PASSIVE.Definition: A passive or static cooled beam provides cooling (and heating) to a room or zone.
IfcCooledBeam.PASSIVE.Name: Passive

IfcCoolingTower.MECHANICALFORCEDDRAFT.Definition: Air flow is produced by a mechanical device, typically one or more fans, located on the inlet air side of the cooling tower.
IfcCoolingTower.MECHANICALFORCEDDRAFT.Name: Mechanical Forced Draft

IfcCoolingTower.MECHANICALINDUCEDDRAFT.Definition: Air flow is produced by a mechanical device, typically one or more fans, located on the air outlet side of the cooling tower.
IfcCoolingTower.MECHANICALINDUCEDDRAFT.Name: Mechanical Induced Draft

IfcDamper.BACKDRAFTDAMPER.Definition: Damper used for purposes of manually balancing pressure differences. Commonly operated by mechanical adjustment.
IfcDamper.BACKDRAFTDAMPER.Name: Back Draft Damper

IfcDamper.BALANCINGDAMPER.Definition: Backdraft damper used to restrict the movement of air in one direction. Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
IfcDamper.BALANCINGDAMPER.Name: Balancing Damper

IfcDamper.BLASTDAMPER.Definition: Blast damper used to prevent protect occupants and equipment against overpressures resultant of an explosion. Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
IfcDamper.BLASTDAMPER.Name: Blast Damper

IfcDamper.CONTROLDAMPER.Definition: Control damper used to modulate the flow of air by adjusting the position of the blades. Commonly operated by an actuator of a building automation system.
IfcDamper.CONTROLDAMPER.Name: Control Damper

ControlDamperOperation.name: Control Damper Operation
ControlDamperOperation.Definition: The inherent characteristic of the control damper operation.

TorqueRange.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
TorqueRange.name: Torque Range
TorqueRange.Definition: Torque range minimum operational torque to maximum allowable torque.

IfcDamper.FIREDAMPER.Definition: Fire damper used to prevent the spread of fire for a specified duration. Commonly operated by fusable link that melts above a certain temperature.
IfcDamper.FIREDAMPER.Name: Fire Damper

ActuationType.name: Actuation Type
ActuationType.Definition: Enumeration that identifies the different types of dampers.

ClosureRatingEnum.name: Closure Rating Enum
ClosureRatingEnum.Definition: Enumeration that identifies the closure rating for the damper.

FireResistanceRating.name: Fire Resistance Rating
FireResistanceRating.Definition: Measure of the fire resistance rating in hours (e.g., 1.5 hours, 2 hours, etc.).

FusibleLinkTemperature.name: Fusible Link Temperature
FusibleLinkTemperature.Definition: The temperature that the fusible link melts.

IfcDamper.FIRESMOKEDAMPER.Definition: Combination fire and smoke damper used to prevent the spread of fire and smoke. Commonly operated by a fusable link and a smoke detector.
IfcDamper.FIRESMOKEDAMPER.Name: Fire Smoke Damper

ActuationType.name: Actuation Type
ActuationType.Definition: Enumeration that identifies the different types of dampers.

ClosureRatingEnum.name: Closure Rating Enum
ClosureRatingEnum.Definition: Enumeration that identifies the closure rating for the damper.

DamperControlType.name: Damper Control Type
DamperControlType.Definition: The type of control used to operate the damper (e.g., OpenClosed Indicator, Resettable Temperature Sensor, Temperature Override, etc.).

FireResistanceRating.name: Fire Resistance Rating
FireResistanceRating.Definition: Measure of the fire resistance rating in hours (e.g., 1.5 hours, 2 hours, etc.).

FusibleLinkTemperature.name: Fusible Link Temperature
FusibleLinkTemperature.Definition: The temperature that the fusible link melts.

IfcDamper.FUMEHOODEXHAUST.Definition: Fume hood exhaust damper. Commonly operated by actuator.
IfcDamper.FUMEHOODEXHAUST.Name: Fumehood Exhaust

IfcDamper.GRAVITYDAMPER.Definition: Gravity damper closes from the force of gravity. Commonly operated by gravitational weight.
IfcDamper.GRAVITYDAMPER.Name: Gravity Damper

IfcDamper.GRAVITYRELIEFDAMPER.Definition: Gravity-relief damper used to allow air to move upon a buildup of enough pressure to overcome the gravitational force exerted upon the damper blades. Commonly operated by gravitational weight.
IfcDamper.GRAVITYRELIEFDAMPER.Name: Gravity Relief Damper

IfcDamper.RELIEFDAMPER.Definition: Relief damper used to allow air to move upon a buildup of a specified pressure differential. Commonly operated by mechanical spring.
IfcDamper.RELIEFDAMPER.Name: Relief Damper

IfcDamper.SMOKEDAMPER.Definition: Smoke damper used to prevent the spread of smoke. Commonly operated by a smoke detector of a building automation system.
IfcDamper.SMOKEDAMPER.Name: Smoke Damper

ControlType.name: Control Type
ControlType.Definition: The type controller, signal modification effected and applicable ports

IfcDuctFitting.BEND.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
IfcDuctFitting.BEND.Name: Bend

BendAngle.name: Bend Angle
BendAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow.

BendRadius.name: Bend Radius
BendRadius.Definition: The radius of bending if circular arc or zero if sharp bend.

IfcDuctFitting.CONNECTOR.Definition: Connector fitting, typically used to join two ports together within a flow distribution system (e.g., a coupling used to join two duct segments).
IfcDuctFitting.CONNECTOR.Name: Connector

IfcDuctFitting.ENTRY.Definition: Entry fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., an outside air duct system intake opening).
IfcDuctFitting.ENTRY.Name: Entry

IfcDuctFitting.EXIT.Definition: Exit fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., an exhaust air discharge opening).
IfcDuctFitting.EXIT.Name: Exit

IfcDuctFitting.JUNCTION.Definition: A fitting with typically more than two ports used to redistribute flow among the ports andor to change the direction of flow between connected elements (e.g, tee, cross, wye, etc.).
IfcDuctFitting.JUNCTION.Name: Junction

JunctionLeftAngle.name: Junction Left Angle
JunctionLeftAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow for the left junction.

JunctionLeftRadius.name: Junction Left Radius
JunctionLeftRadius.Definition: The radius of bending for the left junction.

JunctionRightAngle.name: Junction Right Angle
JunctionRightAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow for the right junction where 0 indicates straight segment.

JunctionRightRadius.name: Junction Right Radius
JunctionRightRadius.Definition: The radius of bending for the right junction where 0 indicates sharp bend.

JunctionType.name: Junction Type
JunctionType.Definition: The type of junction. TEE3 ports, CROSS 4 ports.

IfcDuctFitting.OBSTRUCTION.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports used to obstruct or restrict flow between the connected elements (e.g., screen, perforated plate, etc.).
IfcDuctFitting.OBSTRUCTION.Name: Obstruction

IfcDuctFitting.TRANSITION.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports having different shapes or sizes. Can also be used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
IfcDuctFitting.TRANSITION.Name: Transition

EccentricityInY.name: Eccentricity In Y
EccentricityInY.Definition: Distance in y direction between the two points (or vertex points) engaged in the point connection.

EccentricityInZ.name: Eccentricity In Z
EccentricityInZ.Definition: Distance in z direction between the two points (or vertex points) engaged in the point connection.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcDuctSegment.FLEXIBLESEGMENT.Definition: A flexible segment is a continuous non-linear segment of duct that can be deformed and change the direction of flow.
IfcDuctSegment.FLEXIBLESEGMENT.Name: Flexible Segment

IfcDuctSegment.RIGIDSEGMENT.Definition: A rigid segment is a continuous linear segment of duct that cannot be deformed.
IfcDuctSegment.RIGIDSEGMENT.Name: Rigid Segment

IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVEAI.Definition: Direct evaporative air washer Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with spray-type air washer consist of a chamber or casing containing spray nozzles, and tank for collecting spray water, and an eliminator section for removing entrained drops of water from the air.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVEAI.Name: Direct Evaporative Air Washer

IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVEPA.Definition: Direct evaporative packaged rotary air cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers that wet and wash the evaporative pad by rotating it through a water bath.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVEPA.Name: Direct Evaporative Packaged Rotary Air Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVERA.Definition: Direct evaporative random media air cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with evaporative pads, usually of aspen wood or plastic fiberfoam.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVERA.Name: Direct Evaporative Random Media Air Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVERI.Definition: Direct evaporative rigid media air cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with sheets of rigid, corrugated material as the wetted surface.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVERI.Name: Direct Evaporative Rigid Media Air Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVESL.Definition: Direct evaporative slingers packaged air cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water dircectly into the air stream using coolers with a water slinger in an evaporative cooling section and a fan section.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.DIRECTEVAPORATIVESL.Name: Direct Evaporative Slingers Packaged Air Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTDIRECTCOMBI.Definition: IndirectDirect combination Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream using a two-stage cooler with a first-stage indirect evaporative cooler and second-stage direct evaporative cooler.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTDIRECTCOMBI.Name: Indirect Directcombination

IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Definition: Indirect evaporative cooling tower or coil cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream using a combination of a cooling tower or other evaporative water cooler with a water-to-air heat exchanger coil and water circulating pump.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Name: Indirect Evaporative Cooling Tower Or Coil Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Definition: Indirect evaporative package air cooler Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream. On one side of the heat exchanger, the secondary air stream is cooled by evaporation, while on the other side of heat exchanger, the primary air stream (conditioned air to be supplied to the room) is sensibly cooled by the heat exchanger surfaces.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Name: Indirect Evaporative Package Air Cooler

IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Definition: Indirect evaporative wet coil Cools the air stream by evaporating water indirectly and without adding moisture into the air stream. Water is sprayed directly on the tubes of the heat exchanger where latent cooling takes place and the vaporization of the water on the outside of the heat exchanger tubes allows the simultaneous heat and mass transfer which removes heat from the supply air on the tube side.
IfcEvaporativeCooler.INDIRECTEVAPORATIVE.Name: Indirect Evaporative Wet Coil

IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONBRAZEDPLATE.Definition: Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside plates brazed or welded together to make up an assembly of separate channels.
IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONBRAZEDPLATE.Name: Direct Expansion Brazed Plate

IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONSHELLANDTUB.Definition: Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside a series of baffles that channel the fluid throughout the shell side.
IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONSHELLANDTUB.Name: Direct Expansion Shell and Tube

IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONTUBEINTUBE.Definition: Direct-expansion evaporator where a refrigerant evaporates inside one or more pairs of coaxial tubes.
IfcEvaporator.DIRECTEXPANSIONTUBEINTUBE.Name: Direct Expansion Tube In Tube

IfcEvaporator.FLOODEDSHELLANDTUBE.Definition: Evaporator in which refrigerant evaporates outside tubes.
IfcEvaporator.FLOODEDSHELLANDTUBE.Name: Flooded Shell and Tube

IfcEvaporator.SHELLANDCOIL.Definition: Evaporator in which refrigerant evaporates inside a simple coiled tube immersed in the fluid to be cooled.
IfcEvaporator.SHELLANDCOIL.Name: Shell and Coil

IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALAIRFOIL.Definition: Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are airfoil shaped.
IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALAIRFOIL.Name: Centrifugal Air Foil

DirectionOfRotation.Definition: The direction of the centrifugal fan wheel rotation when viewed from the drive side of the fan.CLOCKWISE Clockwise.
