FanArrangement.name: Fan Arrangement
FanArrangement.Definition: Defines the fan and motor drive arrangement as defined by AMCA.ARRANGEMENT1 Arrangement 1.

IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALBACKWARDINCLINEDCURVED.Definition: Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are backward curved.
IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALBACKWARDINCLINEDCURVED.Name: Centrifugalbackwardinclined Curved

DirectionOfRotation.name: Direction of Rotation
DirectionOfRotation.Definition: The direction of the centrifugal fan wheel rotation when viewed from the drive side of the fan.CLOCKWISE Clockwise.

DischargePosition.name: Discharge Position
DischargePosition.Definition: Centrifugal fan discharge position.TOPHORIZONTAL Top horizontal discharge.

FanArrangement.name: Fan Arrangement
FanArrangement.Definition: Defines the fan and motor drive arrangement as defined by AMCA.ARRANGEMENT1 Arrangement 1.

IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALFORWARDCURVED.Definition: Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are forward curved.
IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALFORWARDCURVED.Name: Centrifugal Forward Curved

DirectionOfRotation.name: Direction of Rotation
DirectionOfRotation.Definition: The direction of the centrifugal fan wheel rotation when viewed from the drive side of the fan.CLOCKWISE Clockwise.

DischargePosition.name: Discharge Position
DischargePosition.Definition: Centrifugal fan discharge position.TOPHORIZONTAL Top horizontal discharge.

FanArrangement.name: Fan Arrangement
FanArrangement.Definition: Defines the fan and motor drive arrangement as defined by AMCA.ARRANGEMENT1 Arrangement 1.

IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALRADIAL.Definition: Air flows through the impeller radially using blades that are uncurved or slightly forward curved.
IfcFan.CENTRIFUGALRADIAL.Name: Centrifugal Radial

DirectionOfRotation.name: Direction of Rotation
DirectionOfRotation.Definition: The direction of the centrifugal fan wheel rotation when viewed from the drive side of the fan.CLOCKWISE Clockwise.

DischargePosition.name: Discharge Position
DischargePosition.Definition: Centrifugal fan discharge position.TOPHORIZONTAL Top horizontal discharge.

FanArrangement.name: Fan Arrangement
FanArrangement.Definition: Defines the fan and motor drive arrangement as defined by AMCA.ARRANGEMENT1 Arrangement 1.

IfcFan.PROPELLORAXIAL.Definition: Air flows through the impeller axially and small hub-to-tip ratio impeller mounted in an orifice plate or inlet ring.
IfcFan.PROPELLORAXIAL.Name: Propelloraxial

IfcFan.TUBEAXIAL.Definition: Air flows through the impeller axially with reduced tip clearance and operating at higher tip speeds.
IfcFan.TUBEAXIAL.Name: Tube Axial

IfcFan.VANEAXIAL.Definition: Air flows through the impeller axially with guide vanes and reduced running blade tip clearance.
IfcFan.VANEAXIAL.Name: Vaneaxial

IfcFilter.AIRPARTICLEFILTER.Definition: A filter used to remove particulates from air.
IfcFilter.AIRPARTICLEFILTER.Name: Air Particle Filter

AirParticleFilterType.name: Air Particle Filter Type
AirParticleFilterType.Definition: A panel dry type extended surface filter is a dry-type air filter with random fiber mats or blankets in the forms of pockets, V-shaped or radial pleats, and include the followingCoarse Filter Filter with a efficiency lower than 30 for atmosphere dust-spot.

CountedEfficiencyCurve.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
CountedEfficiencyCurve.name: Counted Efficiency Curve
CountedEfficiencyCurve.Definition: Counted efficiency curve as a function of dust holding weight, efficiency f (dust holding weight).

FrameMaterial.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
FrameMaterial.name: Frame Material

NominalCountedEfficiency.name: Nominal Counted Efficiency
NominalCountedEfficiency.Definition: Nominal filter efficiency based the particle count concentration before and after the filter against particles with a certain size distribution.

NominalWeightedEfficiency.name: Nominal Weighted Efficiency
NominalWeightedEfficiency.Definition: Nominal filter efficiency based the particle weight concentration before and after the filter against particles with a certain size distribution.

PressureDropCurve.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
PressureDropCurve.name: Pressure Drop Curve
PressureDropCurve.Definition: Under certain dust holding weight, Del Pressure f (fluidflow Rate)

SeparationType.name: Separation Type
SeparationType.Definition: Air particulate filter media separation type.

WeightedEfficiencyCurve.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
WeightedEfficiencyCurve.name: Weighted Efficiency Curve
WeightedEfficiencyCurve.Definition: Weighted efficiency curve as a function of dust holding weight, efficiency f (dust holding weight).

IfcFilter.COMPRESSEDAIRFILTER.Definition: A filter used to remove particulates from compressed air.
IfcFilter.COMPRESSEDAIRFILTER.Name: Compressed Air Filter

AutomaticCondensateDischarge.name: Automatic Condensate Discharge
AutomaticCondensateDischarge.Definition: Whether or not the condensing water or oil is discharged automatically from the filter.

CloggingIndicator.name: Clogging Indicator
CloggingIndicator.Definition: Whether the filter has an indicator to display the degree of clogging of the filter.

CompressedAirFilterType.name: Compressed Air Filter Type
CompressedAirFilterType.Definition: ACTIVATEDCARBON absorbs oil vapor and odor PARTICLEFILTER used to absorb solid particles of medium size COALESCENSEFILTER used to absorb fine solid, oil, and water particles, also called micro filter

OperationPressureMax.name: Operation Pressure Max
OperationPressureMax.Definition: Maximum pressure under normal operating conditions.

ParticleAbsorptionCurve.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
ParticleAbsorptionCurve.name: Particle Absorption Curve
ParticleAbsorptionCurve.Definition: Ratio of particles that are removed by the filter. Each entry describes the ratio of particles absorbed greater than equal to the specified size and less than the next specified size. For example, given for 3 significant particle sizes 0,1 micro m, 1 micro m, 5 micro m

IfcFilter.ODORFILTER.Definition: A filter used to remove odors from air.
IfcFilter.ODORFILTER.Name: Odor Filter

IfcFilter.OILFILTER.Definition: A filter used to remove particulates from oil.
IfcFilter.OILFILTER.Name: Oil Filter

IfcFilter.STRAINER.Definition: A filter used to remove particulates from a fluid.
IfcFilter.STRAINER.Name: Strainer

IfcFilter.WATERFILTER.Definition: A filter used to remove particulates from water.
IfcFilter.WATERFILTER.Name: Water Filter

WaterFilterType.name: Water Filter Type
WaterFilterType.Definition: Further qualifies the type of water filter. Filtration removes undissolved matter Purification removes dissolved matter Softening replaces dissolved matter.

IfcFlowMeter.ENERGYMETER.Definition: An electric meter or energy meter is a device that measures the amount of electrical energy supplied to or produced by a residence, business or machine.
IfcFlowMeter.ENERGYMETER.Name: Energy Meter

MaximumCurrent.name: Maximum Current
MaximumCurrent.Definition: The maximum allowed current that a device is certified to handle.

MultipleTarriff.name: Multiple Tarriff
MultipleTarriff.Definition: Indicates whether meter has built-in support for multiple tarriffs (variable energy cost rates).

NominalCurrent.name: Nominal Current
NominalCurrent.Definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

IfcFlowMeter.GASMETER.Definition: A device that measures the quantity of a gas or fuel.
IfcFlowMeter.GASMETER.Name: Gas Meter

ConnectionSize.name: Connection Size
ConnectionSize.Definition: The connection size of the object.

GasType.name: Gas Type
GasType.Definition: Defines the types of gas that may be specified.

MaximumFlowRate.name: Maximum Flow Rate
MaximumFlowRate.Definition: Maximum rate of flow which the meter is expected to pass.

MaximumPressureLoss.name: Maximum Pressure Loss
MaximumPressureLoss.Definition: Pressure loss expected across the meter under conditions of maximum flow.

IfcFlowMeter.OILMETER.Definition: A device that measures the quantity of oil.
IfcFlowMeter.OILMETER.Name: Oil Meter

ConnectionSize.name: Connection Size
ConnectionSize.Definition: The connection size of the object.

MaximumFlowRate.name: Maximum Flow Rate
MaximumFlowRate.Definition: Maximum rate of flow which the meter is expected to pass.

IfcFlowMeter.WATERMETER.Definition: A device that measures the quantity of water.
IfcFlowMeter.WATERMETER.Name: Water Meter

BackflowPreventerType.name: Backflow Preventer Type
BackflowPreventerType.Definition: Identifies the type of backflow preventer installed to prevent the backflow of contaminated or polluted water from an irrigationreticulation system to a potable water supply.

ConnectionSize.name: Connection Size
ConnectionSize.Definition: The connection size of the object.

MaximumFlowRate.name: Maximum Flow Rate
MaximumFlowRate.Definition: Maximum rate of flow which the meter is expected to pass.

MaximumPressureLoss.name: Maximum Pressure Loss
MaximumPressureLoss.Definition: Pressure loss expected across the meter under conditions of maximum flow.

Type.name: Type
Type.Definition: Defines the allowed values for selection of the flow meter operation type.

NumberOfPlates.name: Number of Plates
NumberOfPlates.Definition: Number of plates used by the plate heat exchanger.

IfcHeatExchanger.TURNOUTHEATING.Definition: A device used to remove snow from railways. E.g. electric heating device, gas heater
IfcHeatExchanger.TURNOUTHEATING.Name: Turnout Heating

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICAIRWASHER.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using an air washing element.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICAIRWASHER.Name: Adiabatic Air Washer

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICATOMIZING.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using an atomizing element.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICATOMIZING.Name: Adiabatic Atomizing

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICCOMPRESSEDAIRNOZZ.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using a compressed air nozzle.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICCOMPRESSEDAIRNOZZ.Name: Adiabatic Compressed Air Nozzle

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICPAN.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using a pan.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICPAN.Name: Adiabatic Pan

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICRIGIDMEDIA.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using a rigid media.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICRIGIDMEDIA.Name: Adiabatic Rigid Media

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICULTRASONIC.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using an ultrasonic element.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICULTRASONIC.Name: Adiabatic Ultrasonic

IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICWETTEDELEMENT.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through adiabatic evaporation using a wetted element.
IfcHumidifier.ADIABATICWETTEDELEMENT.Name: Adiabatic Wettedelement

IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDBUTANE.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through water heated evaporation using a butane heater.
IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDBUTANE.Name: Assisted Butane

IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDELECTRIC.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through water heated evaporation using an electric heater.
IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDELECTRIC.Name: Assisted Electric

IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDNATURALGAS.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through water heated evaporation using a natural gas heater.
IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDNATURALGAS.Name: Assisted Natural Gas

IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDPROPANE.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through water heated evaporation using a propane heater.
IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDPROPANE.Name: Assisted Propane

IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDSTEAM.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through water heated evaporation using a steam heater.
IfcHumidifier.ASSISTEDSTEAM.Name: Assisted Steam

IfcHumidifier.STEAMINJECTION.Definition: Water vapor is added into the airstream through direct steam injection.
IfcHumidifier.STEAMINJECTION.Name: Steam Injection

IfcMedicalDevice.AIRSTATION.Definition: Device that provides purified medical air, composed of an air compressor and air treatment line.
IfcMedicalDevice.AIRSTATION.Name: Air Station

IfcMedicalDevice.FEEDAIRUNIT.Definition: Device that feeds air to an oxygen generator, composed of an air compressor, air treatment line, and an air receiver.
IfcMedicalDevice.FEEDAIRUNIT.Name: Feed Air Unit

IfcMedicalDevice.OXYGENGENERATOR.Definition: Device that generates oxygen from air.
IfcMedicalDevice.OXYGENGENERATOR.Name: Oxygen Generator

IfcMedicalDevice.OXYGENPLANT.Definition: Device that combines a feed air unit, oxygen generator, and backup oxygen cylinders.
IfcMedicalDevice.OXYGENPLANT.Name: Oxygen Plant

IfcMedicalDevice.VACUUMSTATION.Definition: Device that provides suction, composed of a vacuum pump and bacterial filtration line.
IfcMedicalDevice.VACUUMSTATION.Name: Vacuum Station

IfcPipeFitting.BEND.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
IfcPipeFitting.BEND.Name: Bend

BendAngle.name: Bend Angle
BendAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow.

BendRadius.name: Bend Radius
BendRadius.Definition: The radius of bending if circular arc or zero if sharp bend.

IfcPipeFitting.CONNECTOR.Definition: Connector fitting, typically used to join two ports together within a flow distribution system (e.g., a coupling used to join two pipe segments).
IfcPipeFitting.CONNECTOR.Name: Connector

IfcPipeFitting.ENTRY.Definition: Entry fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., a breeching inlet).
IfcPipeFitting.ENTRY.Name: Entry

IfcPipeFitting.EXIT.Definition: Exit fitting, typically unconnected at one port and connected to a flow distribution system at the other (e.g., a hose bibb).
IfcPipeFitting.EXIT.Name: Exit

IfcPipeFitting.JUNCTION.Definition: A fitting with typically more than two ports used to redistribute flow among the ports andor to change the direction of flow between connected elements (e.g, tee, cross, wye, etc.).
IfcPipeFitting.JUNCTION.Name: Junction

JunctionLeftAngle.name: Junction Left Angle
JunctionLeftAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow for the left junction.

JunctionLeftRadius.name: Junction Left Radius
JunctionLeftRadius.Definition: The radius of bending for the left junction.

JunctionRightAngle.name: Junction Right Angle
JunctionRightAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow for the right junction where 0 indicates straight segment.

JunctionRightRadius.name: Junction Right Radius
JunctionRightRadius.Definition: The radius of bending for the right junction where 0 indicates sharp bend.

JunctionType.name: Junction Type
JunctionType.Definition: The type of junction. TEE3 ports, CROSS 4 ports.

IfcPipeFitting.OBSTRUCTION.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports used to obstruct or restrict flow between the connected elements (e.g., screen, perforated plate, etc.).
IfcPipeFitting.OBSTRUCTION.Name: Obstruction

IfcPipeFitting.TRANSITION.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports having different shapes or sizes. Can also be used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
IfcPipeFitting.TRANSITION.Name: Transition

EccentricityInY.name: Eccentricity In Y
EccentricityInY.Definition: Distance in y direction between the two points (or vertex points) engaged in the point connection.

EccentricityInZ.name: Eccentricity In Z
EccentricityInZ.Definition: Distance in z direction between the two points (or vertex points) engaged in the point connection.

NominalLength.name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

IfcPipeSegment.CULVERT.Definition: A covered channel or large pipe that forms a watercourse below ground level, usually under a road or railway.
IfcPipeSegment.CULVERT.Name: Culvert

InternalWidth.name: Internal Width
InternalWidth.Definition: The internal width of the culvert.

IfcPipeSegment.FLEXIBLESEGMENT.Definition: A flexible segment is a continuous non-linear segment of pipe that can be deformed and change the direction of flow.
IfcPipeSegment.FLEXIBLESEGMENT.Name: Flexible Segment

IfcPipeSegment.GUTTER.Definition: A gutter segment is a continuous open-channel segment of pipe.
IfcPipeSegment.GUTTER.Name: Gutter

Complementaryfunction.name: Complementaryfunction
Complementaryfunction.Definition: Indicates the complementary function of the drain channel.

FlowRating.name: Flow Rating
FlowRating.Definition: Actual flow capacity for the gutter. Value of 0.00 means this value has not been set.

IsCovered.name: Is Covered
IsCovered.Definition: This property defines if the drain channel has a cover (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

IsMonitored.name: Is Monitored
IsMonitored.Definition: This property defines if the Drain Channel is monitored (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

OrthometricHeight.name: Orthometric Height
OrthometricHeight.Definition: The orthometric height is the vertical distance H along the plumb line from a point of interest to a reference surface known as the geoid, the vertical datum that approximates mean sea level.

Slope.name: Slope
Slope.Definition: Slope angle - relative to horizontal (0.0 degrees).The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence. For geometry editing applications, like CAD this value should be write-only.

IfcPipeSegment.RIGIDSEGMENT.Definition: A rigid segment is continuous linear segment of pipe that cannot be deformed.
IfcPipeSegment.RIGIDSEGMENT.Name: Rigid Segment

IfcPipeSegment.SPOOL.Definition: A type of rigid segment that is typically shorter and used for providing connectivity within a piping network.
IfcPipeSegment.SPOOL.Name: Spool

IfcPump.CIRCULATOR.Definition: A Circulator pump is a generic low-pressure, low-capacity pump. It may have a wet rotor and may be driven by a flexible-coupled motor.
IfcPump.CIRCULATOR.Name: Circulator

IfcPump.ENDSUCTION.Definition: An End Suction pump, when mounted horizontally, has a single horizontal inlet on the impeller suction side and a vertical discharge. It may have a direct or close-coupled motor.
IfcPump.ENDSUCTION.Name: Endsuction

IfcPump.SPLITCASE.Definition: A Split Case pump, when mounted horizontally, has an inlet and outlet on each side of the impeller. The impeller can be easily accessed by removing the front of the impeller casing. It may have a direct or close-coupled motor.
IfcPump.SPLITCASE.Name: Splitcase

IfcPump.SUBMERSIBLEPUMP.Definition: A pump designed to be immersed in a fluid, typically a collection tank.
IfcPump.SUBMERSIBLEPUMP.Name: Submersible Pump

IfcPump.SUMPPUMP.Definition: A pump designed to sit above a collection tank with a suction inlet extending into the tank.
IfcPump.SUMPPUMP.Name: Sump Pump

IfcPump.VERTICALINLINE.Definition: A Vertical Inline pump has the pump and motor close-coupled on the pump casing. The pump depends on the connected, horizontal piping for support, with the suction and discharge along the piping axis.
IfcPump.VERTICALINLINE.Name: Verticalinline

IfcPump.VERTICALTURBINE.Definition: A Vertical Turbine pump has a motor mounted vertically on the pump casing for either
IfcPump.VERTICALTURBINE.Name: Vertical Turbine

IfcSpaceHeater.CONVECTOR.Definition: A heat-distributing unit that operates with gravity-circulated air.
IfcSpaceHeater.CONVECTOR.Name: Convector

ConvectorType.name: Convector Type
ConvectorType.Definition: Indicates the type of convector, whether forced air (mechanically driven) or natural (gravity).

IfcSpaceHeater.RADIATOR.Definition: A heat-distributing unit that operates with thermal radiation.
IfcSpaceHeater.RADIATOR.Name: Radiator

TubingLength.name: Tubing Length
TubingLength.Definition: Water tube length inside the component.

WaterContent.name: Water Content
WaterContent.Definition: Weight of water content within the heater.

IfcTank.BREAKPRESSURE.Definition: An open container that breaks the hydraulic pressure in a distribution system, typically located between the fluid reservoir and the fluid supply points. A typical break pressure tank allows the flow to discharge into the atmosphere, thereby reducing its hydrostatic pressure to zero.
IfcTank.BREAKPRESSURE.Name: Break Pressure

IfcTank.EXPANSION.Definition: A closed container used in a closed fluid distribution system to mitigate the effects of thermal expansion or water hammer. The tank is typically constructed with a diaphragm dividing the tank into two sections, with fluid on one side of the diaphragm and air on the other. One example application is when connected to the primary circuit of a hot water system to accommodate the increase in volume of the water when it is heated.
IfcTank.EXPANSION.Name: Expansion

ChargePressure.name: Charge Pressure
ChargePressure.Definition: Nominal or design operating pressure of the tank.

PressureRegulatorSetting.name: Pressure Regulator Setting
PressureRegulatorSetting.Definition: Pressure that is automatically maintained in the tank.

ReliefValveSetting.name: Relief Valve Setting
ReliefValveSetting.Definition: Pressure at which the relief valve activates.

IfcTank.FEEDANDEXPANSION.Definition: An open tank that is used for both storage and thermal expansion. A typical example is a tank used to store make-up water at ambient pressure for supply to a hot water system, simultaneously accommodating increases in volume of the water when heated.
IfcTank.FEEDANDEXPANSION.Name: Feedand Expansion

IfcTank.OILRETENTIONTRAY.Definition: An open container for environmental protection and storage of chemical products.
IfcTank.OILRETENTIONTRAY.Name: Oil Retention Tray

IfcTank.PRESSUREVESSEL.Definition: A closed container used for storing fluids or gases at a pressure different from the ambient pressure. A pressure vessel is typically rated by an authority having jurisdiction for the operational pressure.
IfcTank.PRESSUREVESSEL.Name: Pressure Vessel

ChargePressure.name: Charge Pressure
ChargePressure.Definition: Nominal or design operating pressure of the tank.

PressureRegulatorSetting.name: Pressure Regulator Setting
PressureRegulatorSetting.Definition: Pressure that is automatically maintained in the tank.

ReliefValveSetting.name: Relief Valve Setting
ReliefValveSetting.Definition: Pressure at which the relief valve activates.

IfcTank.STORAGE.Definition: An open or closed container used for storing a fluid at ambient pressure and from which it can be supplied to the fluid distribution system. There are many examples of storage tanks, such as potable water storage tanks, fuel storage tanks, etc.
IfcTank.STORAGE.Name: Storage

FinCorrugatedType.name: Fin Corrugated Type
FinCorrugatedType.Definition: Description of a fin corrugated type.

HasCoating.name: Has Coating
HasCoating.Definition: TRUE if the fin has a coating, FALSE if it does not.

Spacing.name: Spacing
Spacing.Definition: Distance between fins on a tube in the tube bundle.

ThermalConductivity.name: Thermal Conductivity
ThermalConductivity.Definition: The thermal conductivity of the object.

Thickness.name: Thickness
Thickness.Definition: The geometric thickness of the object.

IfcUnitaryEquipment.AIRCONDITIONINGUNIT.Definition: A unitary packaged air-conditioning unit typically used in residential or light commercial applications.
IfcUnitaryEquipment.AIRCONDITIONINGUNIT.Name: Air Conditioning Unit

CondenserFlowrate.name: Condenser Flowrate
CondenserFlowrate.Definition: Flow rate of fluid through the condenser.

CoolingEfficiency.name: Cooling Efficiency
CoolingEfficiency.Definition: Coefficient of Performance Ratio of cooling energy output to energy input under full load operating conditions.

HeatingEfficiency.name: Heating Efficiency
HeatingEfficiency.Definition: Heating efficiency under full load heating conditions.

OutsideAirFlowrate.name: Outside Air Flowrate
OutsideAirFlowrate.Definition: Flow rate of outside air entering the unit.

IfcUnitaryEquipment.AIRHANDLER.Definition: A unitary air handling unit typically containing a fan, economizer, and coils.
IfcUnitaryEquipment.AIRHANDLER.Name: Air Handler

AirHandlerConstruction.name: Air Handler Construction
AirHandlerConstruction.Definition: Enumeration defining how the air handler might be fabricated.

AirHandlerFanCoilArrangement.name: Air Handler Fan Coil Arrangement
AirHandlerFanCoilArrangement.Definition: Enumeration defining the arrangement of the supply air fan and the cooling coil.

DualDeck.name: Dual Deck
DualDeck.Definition: Does the Air Handler have a dual deck TRUE Yes, FALSE No.

IfcUnitaryEquipment.DEHUMIDIFIER.Definition: A unitary packaged dehumidification unit. Note units supporting multiple modes (dehumidification, cooling, andor heating) should use AIRCONDITIONINGUNIT.
IfcUnitaryEquipment.DEHUMIDIFIER.Name: Dehumidifier

IfcUnitaryEquipment.ROOFTOPUNIT.Definition: A packaged assembly that is either field-erected or manufactured atop the roof of a large residential or commercial building and acts as a unitary component.
IfcUnitaryEquipment.ROOFTOPUNIT.Name: Roof Top Unit

IfcUnitaryEquipment.SPLITSYSTEM.Definition: A system which separates the compressor from the evaporator, but acts as a unitary component typically within residential or light commercial applications.
IfcUnitaryEquipment.SPLITSYSTEM.Name: Split System

IfcValve.AIRRELEASE.Definition: Valve used to release air from a pipe or fitting.
IfcValve.AIRRELEASE.Name: Air Release

IsAutomatic.name: Is Automatic
IsAutomatic.Definition: Indication of whether the valve is automatically operated (TRUE) or manually operated (FALSE).

IfcValve.ANTIVACUUM.Definition: Valve that opens to admit air if the pressure falls below atmospheric pressure.
IfcValve.ANTIVACUUM.Name: Antivacuum

IfcValve.CHANGEOVER.Definition: Valve that enables flow to be switched between pipelines (3 or 4 port).
IfcValve.CHANGEOVER.Name: Change Over

IfcValve.CHECK.Definition: Valve that permits water to flow in one direction only and is enclosed when there is no flow (2 port).
IfcValve.CHECK.Name: Check

IfcValve.COMMISSIONING.Definition: Valve used to facilitate commissioning of a system (2 port).
IfcValve.COMMISSIONING.Name: Commissioning

IfcValve.DIVERTING.Definition: Valve that enables flow to be diverted from one branch of a pipeline to another (3 port).
IfcValve.DIVERTING.Name: Diverting

IfcValve.DOUBLECHECK.Definition: An assembly that incorporates two valves used to prevent backflow.
IfcValve.DOUBLECHECK.Name: Double Check

IfcValve.DOUBLEREGULATING.Definition: Valve used to facilitate regulation of fluid flow in a system.
IfcValve.DOUBLEREGULATING.Name: Double Regulating

IfcValve.DRAWOFFCOCK.Definition: A valve used to remove fluid from a piping system.
IfcValve.DRAWOFFCOCK.Name: Draw Off Cock

HasHoseUnion.name: Has Hose Union
HasHoseUnion.Definition: Indicates whether the object is fitted with a hose union connection ( TRUE) or not ( FALSE).

IfcValve.FAUCET.Definition: Faucet valve typically used as a flow discharge.
IfcValve.FAUCET.Name: Faucet

FaucetFunction.name: Faucet Function
FaucetFunction.Definition: Defines the operating temperature of a faucet that may be specified.

FaucetOperation.name: Faucet Operation
FaucetOperation.Definition: Defines the range of ways in which a faucet can be operated that may be specified whereCeramic Disc Quick action faucet with a ceramic seal to open or close the orifice

FaucetTopDescription.name: Faucet Top Description
FaucetTopDescription.Definition: Description of the operating mechanismtop of the faucet.

FaucetType.name: Faucet Type
FaucetType.Definition: Defines the range of faucet types that may be specified whereBib Faucet with a horizontal inlet and a nozzle that discharges downwards.

Finish.name: Finish
Finish.Definition: Description of the (surface) finish of the object for informational purposes.

IfcValve.FLUSHING.Definition: Valve that flushes a predetermined quantity of water to cleanse a toilet, urinal, etc.
IfcValve.FLUSHING.Name: Flushing

FlushingRate.name: Flushing Rate
FlushingRate.Definition: The predetermined quantity of water to be flushed.

HasIntegralShutOffDevice.name: Has Integral Shut Off Device
HasIntegralShutOffDevice.Definition: Indication of whether the flushing valve has an integral shut off device fitted (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE).

IsHighPressure.name: Is High Pressure
IsHighPressure.Definition: Indication of whether the flushing valve is suitable for use on a high pressure water main (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE).

IfcValve.GASCOCK.Definition: Valve that is used for controlling the flow of gas.
IfcValve.GASCOCK.Name: Gascock

IfcValve.GASTAP.Definition: Gas tap typically used for venting or discharging gas from a system.
IfcValve.GASTAP.Name: Gastap

HasHoseUnion.name: Has Hose Union
HasHoseUnion.Definition: Indicates whether the object is fitted with a hose union connection ( TRUE) or not ( FALSE).

IfcValve.ISOLATING.Definition: Valve that closes off flow in a pipeline.
IfcValve.ISOLATING.Name: Isolating

IsNormallyOpen.name: Is Normally Open
IsNormallyOpen.Definition: If TRUE, the valve is normally open. If FALSE is is normally closed.

IsolatingPurpose.name: Isolating Purpose
IsolatingPurpose.Definition: Defines the purpose for which the isolating valve is used since the way in which the valve is identified as an isolating valve may be in the context of its use. Note that unless there is a contextual name for the isolating valve (as in the case of a Landing Valve on a rising fire main), then the value assigned shoulkd be UNSET.

IfcValve.MIXING.Definition: Valve that enables flow from two branches of a pipeline to be mixed together (3 port).
IfcValve.MIXING.Name: Mixing

MixerControl.name: Mixer Control
MixerControl.Definition: Defines the form of control of the mixing valve.

OutletConnectionSize.name: Outlet Connection Size
OutletConnectionSize.Definition: Size of the outlet connection from the object.

IfcValve.PRESSUREREDUCING.Definition: Valve that reduces the pressure of a fluid immediately downstream of its position in a pipeline to a preselected value or by a predetermined ratio.
IfcValve.PRESSUREREDUCING.Name: Pressure Reducing

DownstreamPressure.name: Downstream Pressure
DownstreamPressure.Definition: The operating pressure of the fluid downstream of the pressure reducing valve.

UpstreamPressure.name: Upstream Pressure
UpstreamPressure.Definition: The operating pressure of the fluid upstream of the pressure reducing valve.

IfcValve.PRESSURERELIEF.Definition: Spring or weight loaded valve that automatically discharges to a safe place fluid that has built up to excessive pressure in pipes or fittings.
IfcValve.PRESSURERELIEF.Name: Pressure Relief

ReliefPressure.name: Relief Pressure
ReliefPressure.Definition: The pressure at which the spring or weight in the valve is set to discharge fluid.

IfcValve.REGULATING.Definition: Valve used to facilitate regulation of fluid flow in a system.
IfcValve.REGULATING.Name: Regulating

IfcValve.SAFETYCUTOFF.Definition: Valve that closes under the action of a safety mechanism such as a drop weight, solenoid etc.
IfcValve.SAFETYCUTOFF.Name: Safetycut Off

IfcValve.STEAMTRAP.Definition: Valve that restricts flow of steam while allowing condensate to pass through.
IfcValve.STEAMTRAP.Name: Steamtrap

IfcValve.STOPCOCK.Definition: An isolating valve used on a domestic water service.
IfcValve.STOPCOCK.Name: Stop Cock

IfcVibrationIsolator.BASE.Definition: Base isolator preventing transfer of energy from the ground to the structure.
IfcVibrationIsolator.BASE.Name: Base

IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.BREECHINGINLE.Definition: Symmetrical pipe fitting that unites two or more inlets into a single pipe. A breeching inlet may be used on either a wet or dry riser. Used by fire services personnel for fast connection of fire appliance hose reels. May also be used for foam.
IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.BREECHINGINLE.Name: Breeching Inlet

BreechingInletType.name: Breeching Inlet Type
BreechingInletType.Definition: Defines the type of breeching inlet.

CouplingType.name: Coupling Type
CouplingType.Definition: Defines the type coupling on the inlet of the breeching inlet.

HasCaps.name: Has Caps
HasCaps.Definition: Does the inlet connection have protective caps.

InletDiameter.name: Inlet Diameter
InletDiameter.Definition: The inlet diameter of the breeching inlet.

OutletDiameter.name: Outlet Diameter
OutletDiameter.Definition: The outlet diameter of the breeching inlet.

IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.FIREHYDRANT.Definition: Device, fitted to a pipe, through which a temporary supply of water may be provided. May also be termed a stand pipe.
IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.FIREHYDRANT.Name: Fire Hydrant

BodyColour.name: Body Colour
BodyColour.Definition: Colour of the body of the hydrant.Note Consult local fire regulations for statutory colours that may be required for hydrant bodies in particular circumstances.

CapColour.name: Cap Colour
CapColour.Definition: Colour of the caps of the hydrant.Note Consult local fire regulations for statutory colours that may be required for hydrant caps in particular circumstances.

DischargeFlowRate.name: Discharge Flow Rate
DischargeFlowRate.Definition: The volumetric rate of fluid discharge.

FireHydrantType.name: Fire Hydrant Type
FireHydrantType.Definition: Defines the range of hydrant types from which the required type can be selected where.Dry Barrel A hydrant that has isolating valves fitted below ground and that may be used where the possibility of water freezing is a consideration.

FlowClass.name: Flow Class
FlowClass.Definition: Alphanumeric indication of the flow class of a hydrant (may be used in connection with or instead of the Flow Rate property).

HoseConnectionSize.name: Hose Connection Size
HoseConnectionSize.Definition: The size of connections to which a hose may be connected (other than that to be linked to a pumping unit).

NumberOfHoseConnections.name: Number of Hose Connections
NumberOfHoseConnections.Definition: The number of hose connections on the hydrant (excluding the pumper connection).

PumperConnectionSize.name: Pumper Connection Size
PumperConnectionSize.Definition: The size of a connection to which a fire hose may be connected that is then linked to a pumping unit.

WaterIsPotable.name: Water Is Potable
WaterIsPotable.Definition: Indication of whether the water flow from the hydrant is potable (set TRUE) or non potable (set FALSE).

IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.HOSEREEL.Definition: A supporting framework on which a hose may be wound.
IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.HOSEREEL.Name: Hose Reel

ClassificationAuthority.name: Classification Authority
ClassificationAuthority.Definition: The name of the authority that applies the classification of service to the hose reel (e.g. NFPAFEMA).

ClassOfService.name: Class of Service
ClassOfService.Definition: A classification of usage of the hose reel that may be applied.

HoseLength.name: Hose Length
HoseLength.Definition: Notional length of the hose fitted to the hose reel when fully extended.

HoseNozzleType.name: Hose Nozzle Type
HoseNozzleType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of nozzle (in terms of spray pattern) fitted to the end of the hose from which the type required may be set.

HoseReelMountingType.name: Hose Reel Mounting Type
HoseReelMountingType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of hose reel mounting from which the type required may be set.

HoseReelType.name: Hose Reel Type
HoseReelType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of hose arrangement from which the type required may be set.

IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.SPRINKLER.Definition: Device for sprinkling water from a pipe under pressure over an area.
IfcFireSuppressionTerminal.SPRINKLER.Name: Sprinkler

Activation.name: Activation
Activation.Definition: Identifies the predefined methods of sprinkler activation from which that required may be set.

ActivationTemperature.name: Activation Temperature
ActivationTemperature.Definition: The temperature at which the object is designed to activate.

BulbLiquidColour.name: Bulb Liquid Colour
BulbLiquidColour.Definition: The colour of the liquid in the bulb for a bulb activated sprinkler. Note that the liquid colour varies according to the activation temperature requirement of the sprinkler head. FlushRate.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
FlushRate.name: Flush Rate
FlushRate.Definition: The minimum and maximum volume of water used at each flush. Where a single flush is used, the value of upper bound and lower bound should be equal. For a dual flush toilet, the lower bound should be used for the lesser flush rate and the upper bound for the greater flush rate. Where flush is achieved using mains pressure water through a flush valve, the value of upper and lower bound should be equal and should be the same as the flush rate property of the flush valve (see relevant valve property set). Alternatively, in this case, do not assert the flush rate property refer to the flush rate of the flush valve.

IsAutomaticFlush.name: Is Automatic Flush
IsAutomaticFlush.Definition: Boolean value that determines if the cistern is flushed automatically either after each use or periodically (TRUE) or whether manual flushing is required (FALSE).

IsSingleFlush.name: Is Single Flush
IsSingleFlush.Definition: Indicates whether the cistern is single flush TRUE (i.e. the same amount of water is used for each and every flush) or dual flush FALSE (i.e. the amount of water used for a flush may be selected by the user to be high or low depending on the waste material to be removed).

IfcMarineFacility.REVETMENT.Name: Revetment

IfcMarinePart.ABOVEWATERLINE.Name: Above Water Line

IfcMarinePart.ANCHORAGE.Definition: A region spatial part that represents a managed area for the anchorage of vessels awaiting space and conditions to enter a port.
IfcMarinePart.ANCHORAGE.Name: Anchorage

IfcMarinePart.APPROACHCHANNEL.Definition: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that covers the approach of the primary facility.
IfcMarinePart.APPROACHCHANNEL.Name: Approach Channel

IfcMarinePart.BELOWWATERLINE.Definition: A vertical spatial part that represents the part below the mean waterline defined within the site area.
IfcMarinePart.BELOWWATERLINE.Name: Below Water Line

IfcMarinePart.BERTHINGSTRUCTURE.Definition: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that provides facilities for the berthing of vessels while waiting for the waterway facility to become available. For example waiting for a lock cycle to complete and the lock gates to open.
IfcMarinePart.BERTHINGSTRUCTURE.Name: Berthing Structure

IfcMarinePart.CHAMBER.Definition: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that forms the impounded chamber of a facility, such as a ship lock, dry dock or hydrolift
IfcMarinePart.CHAMBER.Name: Chamber

EffectiveChamberSize.name: Effective Chamber Size
EffectiveChamberSize.Definition: Volumetric measure defining the effective chamber size for operational and design activities.

IfcMarinePart.CILL_LEVEL.Definition: A vertical spatial part that represents the elevation of the cill and floor level of an impounded facility such as a ship lock or dry lock.
IfcMarinePart.CILL_LEVEL.Name: Cill Level

IfcMarinePart.COPELEVEL.Definition: A vertical spatial part that represents the elevation working surface of the quay for the placement of quay furniture and plant.
IfcMarinePart.COPELEVEL.Name: Copelevel

IfcMarinePart.CORE.Definition: A lateral spatial part that sub divides the core structure of a facility such as a breakwater or embankment
IfcMarinePart.CORE.Name: Core

IfcMarinePart.CREST.Definition: A lateral spatial part that forms the crest area of breakwater or embankment where additional structures are placed such as access items or roads.
IfcMarinePart.CREST.Name: Crest

IfcMarinePart.GATEHEAD.Definition: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that forms the gate, supporting structure plant of an impounded facility such as a ship lock, dry dock or hydrolift.
IfcMarinePart.GATEHEAD.Name: Gatehead

IfcMarinePart.GUDINGSTRUCTURE.Definition: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that forms the guiding and assistive structures at the entrance to an impounded facility.
IfcMarinePart.GUDINGSTRUCTURE.Name: Guding Structure

IfcMarinePart.HIGHWATERLINE.Definition: A vertical spatial part that represents the elevation of the high waterline, multiple high waterlines can be used to represent the different high tide types.
IfcMarinePart.HIGHWATERLINE.Name: High Water Line

IfcMarinePart.LANDFIELD.Definition: A region or lateral facility part that covers the land field of a waterside facility such as a quay.
IfcMarinePart.LANDFIELD.Name: Landfield

IfcMarinePart.LEEWARDSIDE.Definition: A lateral spatial part that covers the side of protective structures that do not experience weather or wave effects.
IfcMarinePart.LEEWARDSIDE.Name: Leeward Side

IfcMarinePart.LOWWATERLINE.Definition: A vertical spatial part that represents the elevation of the low waterline, multiple low waterlines can be used to represent the different low tide types.
IfcMarinePart.LOWWATERLINE.Name: Low Water Line

IfcMarinePart.MANUFACTURING.Definition: A region spatial part that forms a sub division of a facility for the purpose of manufacturing. This covers areas that are open air and do not constitute a building or the building is only a small part of the entire area (in this case a child of type building can be used).
IfcMarinePart.MANUFACTURING.Name: Manufacturing

IfcMarinePart.NAVIGATIONALAREA.Definition: A region spatial part that covers a managed navigational area that is maintained for an operational reason, this could be a dredged turning circle or waiting area.
IfcMarinePart.NAVIGATIONALAREA.Name: Navigational Area

IfcMarinePart.PROTECTION.Definition: A lateral or region spatial part that forms the area which contains protective measures for scour and erosion of a facility.
IfcMarinePart.PROTECTION.Name: Protection

IfcMarinePart.SHIPTRANSFER.Definition: A region spatial part that represents a clear area used for the transfer and movement of vessels this area could include complex rail tracks and additional loading requirements.
IfcMarinePart.SHIPTRANSFER.Name: Shiptransfer

IfcMarinePart.STORAGEAREA.Definition: A region spatial part that forms a sub division of a facility for the purpose of storing cargo. For example container stacks, dry bulk storage yards, material storage yards.
IfcMarinePart.STORAGEAREA.Name: Storage Area

IfcMarinePart.VEHICLESERVICING.Definition: A region spatial part that represents a functional division designed for the maintenance andor storage of vehicles used for facility operations.
IfcMarinePart.VEHICLESERVICING.Name: Vehicle Servicing

IfcMarinePart.WATERFIELD.Definition: A region or lateral facility part that covers the water field of a waterside facility such as a quay.
IfcMarinePart.WATERFIELD.Name: Water Field

IfcMarinePart.WEATHERSIDE.Definition: A lateral spatial part that covers the side of protective structures that is designed to protect and be impacted by weather or wave effects. such as the outer side of breakwaters or the riverside of flood embankments.
IfcMarinePart.WEATHERSIDE.Name: Weather Side

IfcMooringDevice.BOLLARD.Definition: a short, thick post on the deck of a ship or a quay side, to which ships rope may be secured. not to be confused with traffic bollards.
IfcMooringDevice.BOLLARD.Name: Bollard

IfcMooringDevice.LINETENSIONER.Definition: A mechanical device used to apply a tensioning load to mooring lines to improve vessel stability for port operations.
IfcMooringDevice.LINETENSIONER.Name: Line Tensioner

IfcMooringDevice.MAGNETICDEVICE.Definition: Mooring device that uses magnets as the primary method of securing the vessel.
IfcMooringDevice.MAGNETICDEVICE.Name: Magnetic Device

IfcMooringDevice.MOORINGHOOKS.Definition: Quick release mooring hooks - an active device used to secure a vessel and provide automated release of vessels.
IfcMooringDevice.MOORINGHOOKS.Name: Mooring Hooks

IfcMooringDevice.VACUUMDEVICE.Definition: Mooring device that uses vacuum suction as the primary method of securing the vessel.
IfcMooringDevice.VACUUMDEVICE.Name: Vacuum Device

IfcNavigationElement.BEACON.Definition: a fixed vertical structure serving as a navigation mark, to show reefs or other hazards, or provide navigational directions.
IfcNavigationElement.BEACON.Name: Beacon

IfcNavigationElement.BUOY.Definition: an anchored floating structure serving as a navigation mark, to show reefs or other hazards, or provide navigational directions.
IfcNavigationElement.BUOY.Name: Buoy

IfcEvent.ENDEVENT.Definition: A terminating event of a process.
IfcEvent.ENDEVENT.Name: End Event

IfcEvent.INTERMEDIATEEVENT.Definition: An event that occurs at an intermediate stage of a process.
IfcEvent.INTERMEDIATEEVENT.Name: Intermediate Event

IfcEvent.STARTEVENT.Definition: An initiating event of a process.
IfcEvent.STARTEVENT.Name: Start Event

IfcProcedure.ADVICE_CAUTION.Definition: A caution that should be taken note of as a procedure or when carrying out a procedure.
IfcProcedure.ADVICE_CAUTION.Name: Advice Caution

IfcProcedure.ADVICE_NOTE.Definition: Additional information or advice that should be taken note of as a procedure or when carrying out a procedure.
IfcProcedure.ADVICE_NOTE.Name: Advice Note

IfcProcedure.ADVICE_WARNING.Definition: A warning of potential danger that should be taken note of as a procedure or when carrying out a procedure.
IfcProcedure.ADVICE_WARNING.Name: Advice Warning

IfcProcedure.CALIBRATION.Definition: A procedure undertaken to calibrate an artifact.
IfcProcedure.CALIBRATION.Name: Calibration

IfcProcedure.SHUTDOWN.Definition: A procedure undertaken to shutdown the operation of an artifact.
IfcProcedure.SHUTDOWN.Name: Shutdown

IfcProcedure.STARTUP.Definition: A procedure undertaken to start up the operation of an artifact.
IfcProcedure.STARTUP.Name: Startup

IfcTask.ADJUSTMENT.Definition: Making changes to the physical configuration of something.
IfcTask.ADJUSTMENT.Name: Adjustment

IfcTask.ATTENDANCE.Definition: Attendance or waiting on other things happening.
IfcTask.ATTENDANCE.Name: Attendance

IfcTask.CALIBRATION.Definition: Making changes to the operational configuration of something.
IfcTask.CALIBRATION.Name: Calibration

IfcTask.DISMANTLE.Definition: Taking something apart carefully so that it can be recycled or reused.
IfcTask.DISMANTLE.Name: Dismantle

IfcTask.DISPOSAL.Definition: Disposing or getting rid of something.
IfcTask.DISPOSAL.Name: Disposal

IfcTask.EMERGENCY.Definition: Tasks required when responding to, or ensuring the ability to respond to, an emergency situation.
IfcTask.EMERGENCY.Name: Emergency

IfcTask.INSPECTION.Definition: Check if something is installed and is operating within expected parameters.
IfcTask.INSPECTION.Name: Inspection

IfcTask.INSTALLATION.Definition: Installing something (equivalent to construction but more commonly used for engineering tasks).
IfcTask.INSTALLATION.Name: Installation

IfcTask.MAINTENANCE.Definition: Tasks required to keep an object in good working order.
IfcTask.MAINTENANCE.Name: Maintenance

IfcTask.MOVE.Definition: Moving things from one place to another.
IfcTask.MOVE.Name: Move

ContainerMaterial.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
ContainerMaterial.name: Container Material
ContainerMaterial.Definition: Special requirements for material used to contain an artefact.

PackingCareType.name: Packing Care Type
PackingCareType.Definition: Identifies the predefined types of care that may be required when handling the artefact during a move whereFragile artefact may be broken during a move through careless handling.

WrappingMaterial.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
WrappingMaterial.name: Wrapping Material
WrappingMaterial.Definition: Special requirements for material used to wrap an artefact.

IfcTask.OPERATION.Definition: A procedure undertaken to start up the operation an artifact.
IfcTask.OPERATION.Name: Operation

IfcTask.REMOVAL.Definition: Removal of an item from use and taking it from its place of use.
IfcTask.REMOVAL.Name: Removal

IfcTask.RENOVATION.Definition: Bringing something to an as-new state.
IfcTask.RENOVATION.Name: Renovation

IfcTask.SAFETY.Definition: Tasks required to ensure safe use of the object. For example electrical lock-out instructions.
IfcTask.SAFETY.Name: Safety

IfcTask.SHUTDOWN.Definition: The set of tasks required for an orderly shut down without adverse impacts, typically applied to systems.
IfcTask.SHUTDOWN.Name: Shutdown

IfcTask.STARTUP.Definition: The set of tasks required to begin or restart operation without adverse impacts, typically applied to systems.
IfcTask.STARTUP.Name: Startup

IfcTask.TESTING.Definition: The set of tasks required to evaluate the performance of an object, to ensure if something is installed and is operating within expected parameters.
IfcTask.TESTING.Name: Testing

IfcTask.TROUBLESHOOTING.Definition: The set of tasks required to diagnose commonly encountered performance problems, typically applied to element types and systems.
IfcTask.TROUBLESHOOTING.Name: Troubleshooting

IfcWorkPlan.ACTUAL.Definition: A control in which actual items undertaken are indicated.
IfcWorkPlan.ACTUAL.Name: Actual

IfcWorkPlan.BASELINE.Definition: A control that is a baseline from which changes that are made later can be recognized.
IfcWorkPlan.BASELINE.Name: Baseline

IfcWorkSchedule.ACTUAL.Definition: A process in which actual items undertaken are indicated.
IfcWorkSchedule.ACTUAL.Name: Actual

IfcWorkSchedule.BASELINE.Definition: A process that is a baseline from which changes that are made later can be recognized.
IfcWorkSchedule.BASELINE.Name: Baseline

IfcAnnotation.CONTOURLINE.Definition: Annotation used to illustrate lines connecting points of equal elevation or depth, on a map or chart.
IfcAnnotation.CONTOURLINE.Name: Contourline

ContourValue.name: Contour Value
ContourValue.Definition: Value of the elevation of the contour above or below a reference plane.

IfcAnnotation.DIMENSION.Definition: Annotation used to illustrate the measurement or size of an object, often accompanied by numerical values.
IfcAnnotation.DIMENSION.Name: Dimension

IfcAnnotation.ISOBAR.Definition: Annotation used to illustrate lines connecting points of equal pressure on a map or chart.
IfcAnnotation.ISOBAR.Name: Isobar

IfcAnnotation.ISOLUX.Definition: Annotation used to illustrate lines connecting points of equal illuminance or light intensity.
IfcAnnotation.ISOLUX.Name: Isolux

IfcAnnotation.ISOTHERM.Definition: Annotation used to illustrate lines connecting points of equal temperature on a map or chart.
IfcAnnotation.ISOTHERM.Name: Isotherm

IfcAnnotation.LEADER.Definition: Annotation that includes a line or arrow.
IfcAnnotation.LEADER.Name: Leader

IfcAnnotation.SURVEY.Definition: Annotation used for survey information, such as survey points, survey lines or survey areas.
IfcAnnotation.SURVEY.Name: Survey

AccuracyQualityExpected.name: Accuracy Quality Expected
AccuracyQualityExpected.Definition: A measure of the accuracy quality of survey points as expected expressed in percentage terms.

AccuracyQualityObtained.name: Accuracy Quality Obtained
AccuracyQualityObtained.Definition: A measure of the accuracy quality of survey points as obtained expressed in percentage terms.

AcquisitionMethod.name: Acquisition Method
AcquisitionMethod.Definition: The means by which survey data was acquired.

IfcAnnotation.SYMBOL.Definition: Annotation that employs graphical symbols or icons to represent specific meanings.
IfcAnnotation.SYMBOL.Name: Symbol

IfcBridge.ARCHED.Definition: ISO 6707 Bridge that has one or more arches as its main structure.
IfcBridge.ARCHED.Name: Arched

IfcBridge.CABLE_STAYED.Definition: ISO 6707 Bridge with one or more towers and inclined cables that are connected to the top or the shaft of the tower and support the deck.
IfcBridge.CABLE_STAYED.Name: Cable Stayed

IfcBridge.CANTILEVER.Definition: ISO 6707 Bridge, the main structural members of which are cantilevers.
IfcBridge.CANTILEVER.Name: Cantilever

IfcBridge.CULVERT.Definition: ISO 6707 Transverse drain or waterway construction under a road, railway, or canal, or through an embankment, in the form of a large pipe or enclosed channel.
IfcBridge.CULVERT.Name: Culvert

IfcBridge.GIRDER.Definition: A bridge that uses girders as the means of supporting its deck.
IfcBridge.GIRDER.Name: Girder

IfcBridge.SUSPENSION.Definition: ISO 6707 Bridge, the main structural members of which are catenary cables from which the deck is suspended.
IfcBridge.SUSPENSION.Name: Suspension

IfcBridge.TRUSS.Definition: ISO 6707 Bridge with braced triangulated frame designed to act as a beam.
IfcBridge.TRUSS.Name: Truss

IfcBridgePart.ABUTMENT.Definition: The substructures at the ends of a bridge, supporting its superstructure. They may be composed of wing walls (on each side), head wall, stem wall, and cone
IfcBridgePart.ABUTMENT.Name: Abutment

IfcBridgePart.DECK.Definition: A bridge deck is comprised of those elements used for conveying traffic but does not perform structural functions of the superstructure
IfcBridgePart.DECK.Name: Deck

IfcBridgePart.DECK_SEGMENT.Definition: A segment of the bridge deck. Segments may be separated by construction or expansion joints
IfcBridgePart.DECK_SEGMENT.Name: Deck Segment

IfcBridgePart.FOUNDATION.Definition: The structural elements that support and anchor the bridge to the ground, transmitting all loads to the supporting strata
IfcBridgePart.FOUNDATION.Name: Foundation

IfcBridgePart.PIER.Definition: A bridge pier is a type of structure that extends to the ground below or into the water. It is used to support bridge superstructure and transfer the loads to the foundation.
IfcBridgePart.PIER.Name: Pier

IfcBridgePart.PIER_SEGMENT.Definition: A segment of the bridge pier. Segments may be separated by construction or expansion joints
IfcBridgePart.PIER_SEGMENT.Name: Pier Segment

IfcBridgePart.PYLON.Definition: A vertical structure supporting cables in suspended or stayed structures
IfcBridgePart.PYLON.Name: Pylon

IfcBridgePart.SUBSTRUCTURE.Definition: The elements that transfer loads to the ground. It includes abutments and piers
IfcBridgePart.SUBSTRUCTURE.Name: Sub Structure

IfcBridgePart.SUPERSTRUCTURE.Definition: The part of the bridge that span horizontally and transfers the traffic load to the bridge substructures
IfcBridgePart.SUPERSTRUCTURE.Name: Super Structure

IfcBuiltSystem.EROSIONPREVENTION.Definition: A grouping of elements into a built system for preventing unwanted relocation of material particles in earthworks slopes or rock faces.
IfcBuiltSystem.EROSIONPREVENTION.Name: Erosion Prevention

IfcBuiltSystem.FENESTRATION.Definition: System of doors, windows, and other fillings in openings in a built envelope that are designed to permit the passage of air or light.
IfcBuiltSystem.FENESTRATION.Name: Fenestration

IfcBuiltSystem.FOUNDATION.Definition: System of shallow and deep foundation elements that transmit forces to the supporting ground.
IfcBuiltSystem.FOUNDATION.Name: Foundation

IfcBuiltSystem.LOADBEARING.Definition: System of built elements that transmit forces and stiffen the construction.
IfcBuiltSystem.LOADBEARING.Name: Loadbearing

IfcBuiltSystem.MOORING.Definition: System of components and elements responsible for keeping or holding an element (a vessel, platform or set of catenary lines) in a desired position.
IfcBuiltSystem.MOORING.Name: Mooring

IfcBuiltSystem.OUTERSHELL.Definition: System of built elements that provide the outer skin to protect the construction (such as the facade).
IfcBuiltSystem.OUTERSHELL.Name: Outer Shell

IfcBuiltSystem.PRESTRESSING.Definition: System of elements providing pre-stressing to the structure, including typically manufactured products such as tendons, anchorages (active, dead, coupling), ducts, vents and deviators, and in-situ concrete segments, tendon spacers, blisters and additional reinforcements.
IfcBuiltSystem.PRESTRESSING.Name: Prestressing

IfcBuiltSystem.RAILWAYLINE.Definition: A set of functional tracks with explicit terminals. It is usually composed of a set of tracks with continuous track parts and alignments.
IfcBuiltSystem.RAILWAYLINE.Name: Railway Line

IsElectrified.name: Is Electrified
IsElectrified.Definition: Indicates whether the track system is electrified or not.

LineCharacteristic.name: Line Characteristic
LineCharacteristic.Definition: Indicates the characteristic of the line.

LineID.name: Line Id
LineID.Definition: The unique identifier of the line.

IfcBuiltSystem.RAILWAYTRACK.Definition: Railway track system. It is usually composed of continuous sequences of track parts and alignments.
IfcBuiltSystem.RAILWAYTRACK.Name: Railway Track

TrackCharacteristic.name: Track Characteristic
TrackCharacteristic.Definition: Indicates the characteristic of the track.

TrackID.name: Track Id
TrackID.Definition: The unique identification number of the track.

TrackNumber.name: Track Number
TrackNumber.Definition: Indicates the local identification number of the track.

TrackUsage.name: Track Usage
TrackUsage.Definition: The expected primary usage of the track.

IfcBuiltSystem.REINFORCING.Definition: System of elements providing reinforcing to the structure.
IfcBuiltSystem.REINFORCING.Name: Reinforcing

IfcBuiltSystem.SHADING.Definition: System of shading elements (external or internal) that permits the limitation or control of impact of natural sun light.
IfcBuiltSystem.SHADING.Name: Shading

IfcBuiltSystem.TRACKCIRCUIT.Definition: A track circuit is an electric circuit of which the rails of a track section form a part, with usually a source of current connected at one end and a detection device at the other end for detecting whether this track section is clear or occupied by a vehicle. In a continuous signalling system, the track circuit can be used to transmit information between the ground and the train.
IfcBuiltSystem.TRACKCIRCUIT.Name: Trackcircuit

IfcBuiltSystem.TRANSPORT.Definition: System of all transport elements in a facility that enable the transport of people or goods.
IfcBuiltSystem.TRANSPORT.Name: Transport

IfcElementAssembly.ABUTMENT.Definition: A bridge abutment built up of walls, beams, slabs etc.
IfcElementAssembly.ABUTMENT.Name: Abutment

IfcElementAssembly.BEAM_GRID.Definition: Interconnected beams, located in one (typically horizontal) plane.
IfcElementAssembly.BEAM_GRID.Name: Beam Grid

IfcElementAssembly.BRACED_FRAME.Definition: A rigid frame with additional bracing members.
IfcElementAssembly.BRACED_FRAME.Name: Braced Frame

IfcElementAssembly.CROSS_BRACING.Definition: A Structural linear member or assembly of members inside a box girder or between girders, typically on a pier, to resist lateral forces and transfer them to the support.
IfcElementAssembly.CROSS_BRACING.Name: Cross Bracing

IfcElementAssembly.DECK.Definition: A platform (such as floor or bridge deck) built up of beams, slabs.
IfcElementAssembly.DECK.Name: Deck

IfcElementAssembly.DILATATIONPANEL.Definition: Device which permits longitudinal relative rail movement of two adjacent rails, while maintaining correct guidance and support.
IfcElementAssembly.DILATATIONPANEL.Name: Dilatation Panel

DilatationLength.name: Dilatation Length
DilatationLength.Definition: Length dilatation admitted by the element.

ExpansionDirection.name: Expansion Direction
ExpansionDirection.Definition: The expansion direction, e.g. single direction, bi-direction

InstallationPlan.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
InstallationPlan.name: Installation Plan
InstallationPlan.Definition: Reference to external information source about installation or construction plan of the element.

TechnicalStandard.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
TechnicalStandard.name: Technical Standard
TechnicalStandard.Definition: The technical standard which the element should comply with.

IfcElementAssembly.ENTRANCEWORKS.Definition: An assembly forming the support structure of a chamber (lock, dock) gate and associated elements, plus the containment of operational equipment.
IfcElementAssembly.ENTRANCEWORKS.Name: Entrance Works

IfcElementAssembly.GIRDER.Definition: A beam-like superstructure, such as bridge main girder extending between abutments and piers built up of beams, braces (as Members) etc. - may also be an aggregation of girder segments.
IfcElementAssembly.GIRDER.Name: Girder

IfcElementAssembly.GRID.Definition: A framework of spaced cables or bars that are parallel to or cross each other.
IfcElementAssembly.GRID.Name: Grid

IfcElementAssembly.MAST.Definition: An assembly of plates, members, cables or fasteners that form a vertical structure for the support or mounting of other equipment such as lights, sonar or wireless transmitters.
IfcElementAssembly.MAST.Name: Mast

WithLightningRod.name: With Lightning Rod
WithLightningRod.Definition: Indicates whether the element is equipped with a lightning rod (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

IfcElementAssembly.PIER.Definition: An intermediate support e.g. in a bridge, built up of walls, columns, beams etc.
IfcElementAssembly.PIER.Name: Pier

IfcElementAssembly.PYLON.Definition: A vertical structure supporting cables in suspended or stayed structure.
IfcElementAssembly.PYLON.Name: Pylon

IfcElementAssembly.RAIL_MECHANICAL_EQUIP.Definition: A complex assembly made up of several components like blocking device, speed regulator, bias loaded inspector, track scale or controllable retarder.
IfcElementAssembly.RAIL_MECHANICAL_EQUIP.Name: Rail Mechanical Equipment Assembly

IfcElementAssembly.RIGID_FRAME.Definition: A structure built up of beams, columns, etc. with moment-resisting joints, such as gantry
IfcElementAssembly.RIGID_FRAME.Name: Rigid Frame

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system equipment facility is assembled.

LoadCapacity.name: Load Capacity
LoadCapacity.Definition: Indicates the highest permissible load capacity.

NumberOfTracksCrossed.name: Number of Tracks Crossed
NumberOfTracksCrossed.Definition: Indicates the number of tracks which OCS supporting system crosses.

Span.name: Span
Span.Definition: Clear span for this object.The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence. For geometry editing applications, like CAD this value should be write-only.

IfcElementAssembly.SHELTER.Definition: A structure, fairly quick to setup, move or dismantle, used to give protection, especially from the weather or intrusion.
IfcElementAssembly.SHELTER.Name: Shelter

IfcElementAssembly.SIGNALASSEMBLY.Definition: An assembly to physically aggregate together one or more signal instances (and also sign instances) including any supporting structural elements such as a simple pole or a rigid frame gantry.
IfcElementAssembly.SIGNALASSEMBLY.Name: Signal Assembly

ApproachSpeed.name: Approach Speed
ApproachSpeed.Definition: The design speed of trains approaching the signal if different from the line speed.

MarkerType.name: Marker Type
MarkerType.Definition: The type of marker (sign) e.g. stop signal, restriction signal, track circuit tuning zone sign or others specified in PEnumMarker Type.

NominalHeight.name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Symbol.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Symbol.name: Symbol
Symbol.Definition: Content which is shown on the sign, e.g. text, number, arrow or icon. The string can also be a pointer to a symbol catalog.

IfcElementAssembly.SLAB_FIELD.Definition: Slabs, laid out in one plane.
IfcElementAssembly.SLAB_FIELD.Name: Slab Field

IfcElementAssembly.SUMPBUSTER.Definition: An obstacle (with oil catchment basin) installed typically in a bus lane to prevent other traffic with lower ground clearance from using it. Also Sump breaker or Sump trap.
IfcElementAssembly.SUMPBUSTER.Name: Sumpbuster

TypeDesignation.name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. Bull nose, Half batter, Dropper, Chamfer etc

IfcElementAssembly.SUPPORTINGASSEMBLY.Definition: An assembly intends to support Overhead Contact Line System. It includes foundation, supporting elements and suspension assembly.
IfcElementAssembly.SUPPORTINGASSEMBLY.Name: Supporting Assembly

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system equipment facility is assembled.

NumberOfTracksCrossed.name: Number of Tracks Crossed
NumberOfTracksCrossed.Definition: Indicates the number of tracks which OCS supporting system crosses.

Span.name: Span
Span.Definition: Clear span for this object.The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence. For geometry editing applications, like CAD this value should be write-only.

NumberOfCantilevers.name: Number of Cantilevers
NumberOfCantilevers.Definition: Indicates the number of cantilevers in the OCS supporting system.

TypeOfSupportingSystem.name: Type of Supporting System
TypeOfSupportingSystem.Definition: Type of foundation in the OCS supporting system.

IfcElementAssembly.SUSPENSIONASSEMBLY.Definition: A complex assembly of components used to suspend elements or cable segments.
IfcElementAssembly.SUSPENSIONASSEMBLY.Name: Suspension Assembly

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system equipment facility is assembled.

ContactWireStagger.name: Contact Wire Stagger
ContactWireStagger.Definition: Lateral displacement of the contact wire to opposite sides of the track centre at successive supports.

SystemHeight.name: System Height
SystemHeight.Definition: Vertical distance between the main catenary wire and the contact wire measured at a support point.

ContactWireHeight.name: Contact Wire Height
ContactWireHeight.Definition: Distance from the top of the rail to the lower face of the contact wire, measured perpendicular to the track.

ContactWireStagger.name: Contact Wire Stagger
ContactWireStagger.Definition: Lateral displacement of the contact wire to opposite sides of the track centre at successive supports.

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system equipment facility is assembled.

ContactWireStagger.name: Contact Wire Stagger
ContactWireStagger.Definition: Lateral displacement of the contact wire to opposite sides of the track centre at successive supports.

IsSetOnWorkingWire.name: Is Set On Working Wire
IsSetOnWorkingWire.Definition: Indicates whether the steady device is set on the working wire.

SteadyDeviceType.name: Steady Device Type
SteadyDeviceType.Definition: Type of Steady Device To indicate the mode of registration.

IfcElementAssembly.TRACKPANEL.Definition: Trackwork ensuring the support and guidance of a vehicle along a route. It consists of assembly of rail, sleepers and fastenings.
IfcElementAssembly.TRACKPANEL.Name: Track Panel

InstallationPlan.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
InstallationPlan.name: Installation Plan
InstallationPlan.Definition: Reference to external information source about installation or construction plan of the element.

IsAccessibleByVehicle.name: Is Accessible By Vehicle
IsAccessibleByVehicle.Definition: Indicates whether the element is accessible by a vehicle or not.

TrackExpansion.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
TrackExpansion.name: Track Expansion
TrackExpansion.Definition: In curvature context, bounded value of the expansion distance that can be added to rail gauge.

IfcElementAssembly.TRACTION_SWITCHING_AS.Definition: A common assembly used to insure the switching function. It is composed of switches, control instruments and other components.
IfcElementAssembly.TRACTION_SWITCHING_AS.Name: Traction Switching Assembly

DesignAmbientTemperature.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
DesignAmbientTemperature.name: Design Ambient Temperature
DesignAmbientTemperature.Definition: The highest and lowest local ambient temperature likely to be encountered.

NominalCurrent.name: Nominal Current
NominalCurrent.Definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

NominalPower.name: Nominal Power
NominalPower.Definition: A conventional value of apparent power determining a value of the rated current that may be carried with rated voltage applied, under specified conditions. ( IEV ref 421-04-04)

RatedVoltage.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
RatedVoltage.name: Rated Voltage
RatedVoltage.Definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

IfcElementAssembly.TRAFFIC_CALMING_DEVIC.Definition: A structure on the carriageway to control the speed of vehicles.
IfcElementAssembly.TRAFFIC_CALMING_DEVIC.Name: Traffic Calming Device

TypeDesignation.name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. Bull nose, Half batter, Dropper, Chamfer etc

IfcElementAssembly.TRUSS.Definition: A structure built up of members with (quasi) pinned joint.
IfcElementAssembly.TRUSS.Name: Truss

IfcElementAssembly.TURNOUTPANEL.Definition: Trackwork ensuring the support and guidance of a vehicle along any given route among various diverging or intersecting tracks.
IfcElementAssembly.TURNOUTPANEL.Name: Turnout Panel

BranchLineDirection.name: Branch Line Direction
BranchLineDirection.Definition: Describes the direction associated to the branch line of the turnout (deviated branch).

InstallationPlan.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
InstallationPlan.name: Installation Plan
InstallationPlan.Definition: Reference to external information source about installation or construction plan of the element.

IsAccessibleByVehicle.name: Is Accessible By Vehicle
IsAccessibleByVehicle.Definition: Indicates whether the element is accessible by a vehicle or not.

IsSharedTurnout.name: Is Shared Turnout
IsSharedTurnout.Definition: Indicates if the turnout makes a connection to another infrastructure owner (for sharing costs).

MaximumSpeedLimitOfDivergingLine.name: Maximum Speed Limit of Diverging Line
MaximumSpeedLimitOfDivergingLine.Definition: Maximum speed for diverging line that corresponds to the type of turnout and design constraints.

PercentShared.name: Percent Shared
PercentShared.Definition: Percent of costs paid by the other infrastructure owner.

TrackElementOrientation.name: Track Element Orientation
TrackElementOrientation.Definition: Turnout panels can be placed in 2 mirror-symmetric directions in the field. To distinguish both ends of the turnout panel, a definition of an orientation system with respect to the panel is necessary. The orientation defines, if the panel is oriented in a way or opposite with respect to the direction of the alignmentstationing.

TrackExpansion.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
TrackExpansion.name: Track Expansion
TrackExpansion.Definition: In curvature context, bounded value of the expansion distance that can be added to rail gauge.

TrackGaugeLength.name: Track Gauge Length
TrackGaugeLength.Definition: Basic track gauge of permanent way.

TurnoutCurvedRadius.name: Turnout Curved Radius
TurnoutCurvedRadius.Definition: If turnout is curved, the main branch radius of curvature.

TurnoutHeaterType.name: Turnout Heater Type
TurnoutHeaterType.Definition: Defines the kind of turnout heater installed.

TurnoutPointMachineCount.name: Turnout Point Machine Count
TurnoutPointMachineCount.Definition: Count of point machines inside turnout panel.

TypeOfCurvedTurnout.name: Type of Curved Turnout
TypeOfCurvedTurnout.Definition: Turnouts that are positioned in the curved part of the alignment.

TypeOfDrivingDevice.name: Type of Driving Device
TypeOfDrivingDevice.Definition: Type of the driving device used for the turnout.

TypeOfJunction.name: Type of Junction
TypeOfJunction.Definition: The turnout part of the continuous welded rail.

IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL.Definition: External air space around the building.
IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL.Name: External

IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_EARTH.Definition: External volume covered by earth around the building.
IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_EARTH.Name: External Earth

IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_FIRE.Definition: Space occupied by a neighboring building.
IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_FIRE.Name: External Fire

IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_WATER.Definition: External volume covered with water around the building.
IfcExternalSpatialElement.EXTERNAL_WATER.Name: External Water

IfcFacilityPartCommon.ABOVEGROUND.Definition: A vertical facility part for elements belonging to the space above the finished ground.
IfcFacilityPartCommon.ABOVEGROUND.Name: Above Ground

IfcFacilityPartCommon.BELOWGROUND.Definition: A vertical facility part for the containment of elements below the finished ground. This may include for example earthworks elements and elements in a pavement structure.
IfcFacilityPartCommon.BELOWGROUND.Name: Below Ground

IfcFacilityPartCommon.JUNCTION.Definition: A longitudinal facility part providing an at grade junction between two or more segments of longitudinal facilities usually of the same type.
IfcFacilityPartCommon.JUNCTION.Name: Junction

Crossfall.name: Crossfall
